      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 1 (December 2021 Session) Page 3 of 5 Question 2 (9 marks – approximately 16 minutes) Gateway Online Mall was established a month ago with the vision of providing a 24-hour online supermarket in Hong Kong. The Chief Executive Officer (CEO) has just recruited you as an accountant with the principal task of setting up an accounting system for the company, and has proposed the following treatments for your consideration: (1) To save storage space, Gateway Online Mall adopts a \"just-in-time\" inventory system. Goods are purchased and delivered from suppliers only when a customer's order is placed. In view of this, the CEO proposes to net off the invoiced price with cost of goods for each transaction and to record only the profit amount in the accounting records. (2) Since the majority of the transactions of the company are settled on a credit basis, to simplify the accounting treatments, the CEO also proposes that all transactions should be recorded based on the date when cash is received or paid. Required: State and explain which of the accounting basis/ concepts have been violated, and suggest the appropriate accounting treatment to the CEO of Gateway Online Mall. (9 marks)",
