      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 1 (December 2021 Session) Page 4 of 5 Question 3 (24 marks – approximately 43 minutes) On 5 March 2021, the account manager of CoWork Limited received the draft of financial statements as at 31 December 2020. He found that the company made a profit of HK$1,780,000 for the year but a suspense account was shown under the current assets of the statement of financial position. He was quite surprised and asked his assistant manager to examine the accounting records. Upon further investigation, it was found that the following mistakes were made in the accounts: (1) The company purchased a motor vehicle for HK$450,000 on 1 October 2020 and a car loan at an interest rate of 6% per annum was established on the same date. However, the company debited the purchases account and credited the suspense account. CoWork Limited depreciates the motor vehicle using a reducing balance method at a depreciation rate of 20% per annum. Depreciation is charged in a pro-rata basis. (2) The sales journal had been undercast by HK$5,000. (3) Rent payment of HK$40,000 had been incorrectly recorded in the utility account. (4) One of the customers settled his outstanding balance of HK$66,000 through bank transfer. The company had completely reversed the double entries in the books. (5) Return of goods to supplier amounting to HK$12,000 was correctly recorded in the returns outwards account but was incorrectly recorded in the trade payables subsidiary ledger as HK$21,000. Required: (a) Prepare the journal entries (with narratives) to correct the above errors. (No control accounts were maintained.) (20 marks) (b) Compute the revised profit for CoWork Limited for the year ended 31 December 2020. Show all your workings. (4 marks)",
