      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 1 (December 2021 Session) Page 5 of 5 Question 4 (14 marks – approximately 25 minutes) Walton Limited received a bank statement issued by Hong Kong Bank on 6 November 2020 and found that the monthly balance as at 31 October 2020 did not agree with the company's bank account balance on the same date. In the cash book of Walton Limited, the bank account had a balance of HK$4,500. The accountant of the company discovered the following: (1) Cheques received amounting to HK$103,500 were put inside a cheque box of the bank on Saturday and had been processed by the bank on 2 November 2020. (2) The accounts clerk drew cheques amounting to HK$45,000 for settlement of invoices with suppliers, but these cheques were received and banked by suppliers after 2 November 2020. (3) On 31 October 2020, Hong Kong Bank informed Walton Limited that a cheque received from a customer for HK$56,000 was returned and marked \"Non-sufficient Fund\". The company had not yet recorded the return of this cheque in the cash book. (4) A payment of electricity for HK$7,000 had been entered in the opposite side of the cash book. (5) A cheque drawn for HK$5,800 in payment of utilities had been entered in the cash book as HK$4,500. (6) The credit side of the cash book had been overcast by HK$42,000. (7) It was found that Hong Kong Bank had mistakenly recorded a receipt of HK$5,000 into the account of Walton Limited. However, this receipt belonged to another client - Walter Limited. This receipt should be recorded in the bank account of Walter Limited instead of Walton Limited. Required: (a) Prepare the bank ledger account of Walton Limited for October 2020. (7 marks) (b) Prepare a bank reconciliation statement for Walton Limited as at 31 October 2020. (7 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
