      "prompt": "Module 1 (June 2022 Session) Page 1 of 6 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 MARKS) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Unicorn Company was set up a few months ago. You, as an auditor, would like to understand the accounting system of the company and hence arranged a meeting with its accountant. After the discussion, the following matters were raised: (1) The accountant believed that the financial statements of the company should be presented in a true and correct manner in order to accurately reflect and present the financial information of the company. Whenever judgement is needed, the company must make decisions within the context of the company's financial reporting guidelines and policies. (2) Owing to the ongoing pandemic situation, the business environment was faced with uncertainty. The accountant was very nervous about the operations of the company and hence believed that the preparation of the financial statements can be exempted from the assumption of going concern. Required: State and explain the appropriateness of the above-mentioned two matters for Unicorn Company with the support of the relevant accounting assumptions/ basis/ concepts/ qualitative characteristics. (10 marks)",
      "full": "Module 1 (June 2022 Session) Page 1 of 6 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 MARKS) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Unicorn Company was set up a few months ago. You, as an auditor, would like to understand the accounting system of the company and hence arranged a meeting with its accountant. After the discussion, the following matters were raised: (1) The accountant believed that the financial statements of the company should be presented in a true and correct manner in order to accurately reflect and present the financial information of the company. Whenever judgement is needed, the company must make decisions within the context of the company's financial reporting guidelines and policies. (2) Owing to the ongoing pandemic situation, the business environment was faced with uncertainty. The accountant was very nervous about the operations of the company and hence believed that the preparation of the financial statements can be exempted from the assumption of going concern. Required: State and explain the appropriateness of the above-mentioned two matters for Unicorn Company with the support of the relevant accounting assumptions/ basis/ concepts/ qualitative characteristics. (10 marks)",
      "options": [],
      "sourcePage": 1,
      "sourceMode": "text",
      "ocrUsed": false,
