      "prompt": "Module 1 (June 2022 Session) Page 4 of 6 Question 3 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) The Oppo Company prepared the financial statements and recorded a profit of HK$672,900 for the year ended 31 December 2021. However, after careful examination, the accountant found that the following mistakes were made: (1) Commission income of HK42,000 was incorrectly recorded in the credit side of bank account as HK$24,000. (2) The returns inwards journal had been overcasted by HK$5,000. (3) The bank interest expense of HK$21,000 was debited twice to the bank interest expense account. (4) The expenses for entertainment of HK$55,000 were wrongly recorded in the electricity account. (5) One piece of equipment was sold at a price of HK$367,800 on 31 December 2021. The equipment was acquired at cost of HK$600,000 on 1 January 2019 and depreciation is charged at 20% on a reducing balance method. The company recorded the disposal by debiting the bank account and crediting the sales account. Required: (a) Prepare the journal entries with narratives to correct the above errors. (17 marks) (b) Calculate the adjusted profit for the year ended 31 December 2021. (3 marks)",
