      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/M1-10LP+Past%20paper/1-10%20Past%20paper/module1/Module%201%20Question%20Dec%202022.pdf#question-q-p001-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 1 (December 2022 Session) Page 1 of 6 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (12 marks – approximately 21 minutes) WE Beauty Company engages in retail industry specialising in selling cosmetics. On 3 April 2022, the company received its bank statement issued by Asia Bank. The company found that the monthly balance as at 31 March 2022 did not agree with its bank account in the ledger which showed a credit balance of HK$11,560. After investigation, the accountant of the company found out the following reasons: (1) Two cheques amounting to HK$8,800 received from customers were put inside the cheque box of Asia Bank at the mid-night of 31 March 2022, and Asia Bank processed the two cheques on 1 April 2022. (2) Electricity charges of HK$3,500 were directly transferred from Asia Bank via standard instruction on 31 March 2022, but the company had not yet recorded these in the bank account in the ledger. (3) On 4 April 2022, Asia Bank informed WE Beauty Company that the cheque drawn to settle a payment to a supplier for HK$45,000 could not be processed by the supplier's bank due to a wrong signature. The company had not yet recorded the return of this cheque in the bank account in the ledger. (4) A cheque amounting to HK$7,900 drawn had not been processed by Asia Bank until 2 April 2022. (5) A payment of HK$3,200 had been entered in the debit side of the bank account in the ledger as HK$2,300. (6) It was found that a cheque drawn by ME Pretty Company in the amount of HK$9,000 had been wrongly recorded in the bank statement of WE Beauty Company. (7) It was found that the credit balance of the bank account in the ledger as at 31 March 2022 was overstated by HK$1,200. Required: (a) Prepare the bank account in the ledger for March 2022 for WE Beauty Company. (6 marks) (b) Prepare the bank reconciliation statement as at 31 March 2022 for WE Beauty Company. (6 marks)",
      "full": "Module 1 (December 2022 Session) Page 1 of 6 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (12 marks – approximately 21 minutes) WE Beauty Company engages in retail industry specialising in selling cosmetics. On 3 April 2022, the company received its bank statement issued by Asia Bank. The company found that the monthly balance as at 31 March 2022 did not agree with its bank account in the ledger which showed a credit balance of HK$11,560. After investigation, the accountant of the company found out the following reasons: (1) Two cheques amounting to HK$8,800 received from customers were put inside the cheque box of Asia Bank at the mid-night of 31 March 2022, and Asia Bank processed the two cheques on 1 April 2022. (2) Electricity charges of HK$3,500 were directly transferred from Asia Bank via standard instruction on 31 March 2022, but the company had not yet recorded these in the bank account in the ledger. (3) On 4 April 2022, Asia Bank informed WE Beauty Company that the cheque drawn to settle a payment to a supplier for HK$45,000 could not be processed by the supplier's bank due to a wrong signature. The company had not yet recorded the return of this cheque in the bank account in the ledger. (4) A cheque amounting to HK$7,900 drawn had not been processed by Asia Bank until 2 April 2022. (5) A payment of HK$3,200 had been entered in the debit side of the bank account in the ledger as HK$2,300. (6) It was found that a cheque drawn by ME Pretty Company in the amount of HK$9,000 had been wrongly recorded in the bank statement of WE Beauty Company. (7) It was found that the credit balance of the bank account in the ledger as at 31 March 2022 was overstated by HK$1,200. Required: (a) Prepare the bank account in the ledger for March 2022 for WE Beauty Company. (6 marks) (b) Prepare the bank reconciliation statement as at 31 March 2022 for WE Beauty Company. (6 marks)",
