      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 1 (December 2022 Session) Page 3 of 6 Additional information: (1) The cost of inventory as at 31 March 2022 was HK$777,000. (2) The following information is available for non-current assets:  The company adopts the revaluation model for building while it adopts the cost model for all other tangible non-current assets.  Building is depreciated on a straight-line basis over their estimated useful economic life of 40 years.  It is the policy of the company to eliminate the accumulated depreciation against the gross carrying amount of the asset in a revaluation.  The building was revalued at HK$9,600,000 on 31 March 2022 but this has not yet been recorded in the books of the company.  Furniture and equipment are depreciated using the reducing balance method at the annual depreciation rate of 10%.  Depreciation for the year ended 31 March 2022 had not yet been provided. (3) Salaries amounting to HK $ 60,000 for the month of March 2022 were settled and recorded on 6 April 2022 while rent of HK$90,000 for three months ended 30 April 2022 were paid and recorded on 2 February 2022 . (4) The bank loan was borrowed one year ago and should be repaid in full in 2026. Interest for the year ended 31 March 2022 has still not yet been recorded in the books of the company. (5) The company performs impairment assessment on trade receivables at the end of each year, and the allowance for impairment loss on trade receivables as at 31 March 2022 was assessed at HK$20,000. (6) On 2 April 2022, the accountant of the company found that entertainment expenses amounting to HK$30,000 were wrongly classified as selling and distribution costs. (7) Income tax on current year profit was estimated to be HK$220,000. (8) On 31 March 2022, the directors of the company recommended transferring HK$ 800 ,000 to the general reserve. Required: (a) Prepare the statement of profit or loss and other comprehensive income for the year ended 31 March 2022 for Marvel Limited. (16 marks) (b) Prepare the statement of financial position as at 31 March 2022 for Marvel Limited. (13 marks) (Show all your workings.)",
      "full": "Module 1 (December 2022 Session) Page 3 of 6 Additional information: (1) The cost of inventory as at 31 March 2022 was HK$777,000. (2) The following information is available for non-current assets:  The company adopts the revaluation model for building while it adopts the cost model for all other tangible non-current assets.  Building is depreciated on a straight-line basis over their estimated useful economic life of 40 years.  It is the policy of the company to eliminate the accumulated depreciation against the gross carrying amount of the asset in a revaluation.  The building was revalued at HK$9,600,000 on 31 March 2022 but this has not yet been recorded in the books of the company.  Furniture and equipment are depreciated using the reducing balance method at the annual depreciation rate of 10%.  Depreciation for the year ended 31 March 2022 had not yet been provided. (3) Salaries amounting to HK $ 60,000 for the month of March 2022 were settled and recorded on 6 April 2022 while rent of HK$90,000 for three months ended 30 April 2022 were paid and recorded on 2 February 2022 . (4) The bank loan was borrowed one year ago and should be repaid in full in 2026. Interest for the year ended 31 March 2022 has still not yet been recorded in the books of the company. (5) The company performs impairment assessment on trade receivables at the end of each year, and the allowance for impairment loss on trade receivables as at 31 March 2022 was assessed at HK$20,000. (6) On 2 April 2022, the accountant of the company found that entertainment expenses amounting to HK$30,000 were wrongly classified as selling and distribution costs. (7) Income tax on current year profit was estimated to be HK$220,000. (8) On 31 March 2022, the directors of the company recommended transferring HK$ 800 ,000 to the general reserve. Required: (a) Prepare the statement of profit or loss and other comprehensive income for the year ended 31 March 2022 for Marvel Limited. (16 marks) (b) Prepare the statement of financial position as at 31 March 2022 for Marvel Limited. (13 marks) (Show all your workings.)",
