      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 1 (December 2022 Session) Page 4 of 6 Question 3 (25 marks – approximately 45 minutes) Planet Limited engages in wholesale industry and ends its financial year on 31 March. On 31 March 2022, it had the following account balances: HK$ Non-current assets: Furniture - Cost 4,200,000 - Accumulated depreciation 1,400,000 Current assets: Inventory 424,000 The accountant of Planet Limited found that the following transactions had not yet been recorded/ considered in the books of Planet Limited: (1) Additional furniture was acquired on 1 October 2021, and the costs were as follows: HK$ Invoice price 200,000 Delivery cost 15,000 Installation cost 10,000 Insurance fee on delivery of furniture from the supplier to the head office of Planet Limited 1,000 1-year warranty 2,000 Planet Limited settled the above costs by two means, with half of the amount being settled by cash while the remaining half by a 4% bank loan. Bank loan interest is payable half-yearly on 1 April and 1 October each year. On 31 March 2022, a sofa was sold for cash at HK$50,000. The sofa had been acquired at cost of HK$100,000 on 1 April 2018. It is the policy of Planet Limited to depreciate furniture at the rate of 10% per annum using the straight-line method. Depreciation is charged on a monthly basis. (2) Inventory balance as shown on 31 March 2022 was actually extracted from the record as at 3 April 2022. However, Planet Limited did not take into consideration of the following movement of inventory: (i) Inventory item no. \"AK223\" had been missed in the value of closing inventory. Here is the movement record for inventory item no. \"AK223\" for the year ended 31 March 2022:",
      "full": "Module 1 (December 2022 Session) Page 4 of 6 Question 3 (25 marks – approximately 45 minutes) Planet Limited engages in wholesale industry and ends its financial year on 31 March. On 31 March 2022, it had the following account balances: HK$ Non-current assets: Furniture - Cost 4,200,000 - Accumulated depreciation 1,400,000 Current assets: Inventory 424,000 The accountant of Planet Limited found that the following transactions had not yet been recorded/ considered in the books of Planet Limited: (1) Additional furniture was acquired on 1 October 2021, and the costs were as follows: HK$ Invoice price 200,000 Delivery cost 15,000 Installation cost 10,000 Insurance fee on delivery of furniture from the supplier to the head office of Planet Limited 1,000 1-year warranty 2,000 Planet Limited settled the above costs by two means, with half of the amount being settled by cash while the remaining half by a 4% bank loan. Bank loan interest is payable half-yearly on 1 April and 1 October each year. On 31 March 2022, a sofa was sold for cash at HK$50,000. The sofa had been acquired at cost of HK$100,000 on 1 April 2018. It is the policy of Planet Limited to depreciate furniture at the rate of 10% per annum using the straight-line method. Depreciation is charged on a monthly basis. (2) Inventory balance as shown on 31 March 2022 was actually extracted from the record as at 3 April 2022. However, Planet Limited did not take into consideration of the following movement of inventory: (i) Inventory item no. \"AK223\" had been missed in the value of closing inventory. Here is the movement record for inventory item no. \"AK223\" for the year ended 31 March 2022:",
