      "sourceMatch": "Module 1 (December 2022 Session) Page 6 of 6 Question 4 (14 marks – approximately 25 minutes) iMall Limited operates an e-shop in Hong Kong and ends its financial year ended 31 Mar",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/M1-10LP+Past%20paper/1-10%20Past%20paper/module1/Module%201%20Question%20Dec%202022.pdf#question-q-p006-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 1 (December 2022 Session) Page 6 of 6 Question 4 (14 marks – approximately 25 minutes) iMall Limited operates an e-shop in Hong Kong and ends its financial year ended 31 March. The accountant of the company is now considering the following accounting treatments: (1) Over the years, all motor vehicles have been depreciated using the reducing balance method with a depreciation rate of 10%. Due to the growth in online purchase in Hong Kong, the company acquired two more motor vehicles for arranging delivery of goods to customers. These two new motor vehicles are to be depreciated using the straight-line method with an estimated useful life of five years. (2) On 28 February 2022, the company was being sued by a customer on his damage caused by the sofa sold in the e-shop. It was confirmed that the company had lost the case but the settlement had not yet been finalised by the court. Based on the estimation made by the accountant, the company recorded a provision for legal claim of HK$60,000 as expense for the year ended 31 March 2022. Required: Analyse whether the above-mentioned accounting treatments are appropriate for iMall Limited. In each case, you are required to support your analysis with ONE relevant accounting principle/ basis/ concept and ONE enhancing qualitative characteristic. (14 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
      "full": "Module 1 (December 2022 Session) Page 6 of 6 Question 4 (14 marks – approximately 25 minutes) iMall Limited operates an e-shop in Hong Kong and ends its financial year ended 31 March. The accountant of the company is now considering the following accounting treatments: (1) Over the years, all motor vehicles have been depreciated using the reducing balance method with a depreciation rate of 10%. Due to the growth in online purchase in Hong Kong, the company acquired two more motor vehicles for arranging delivery of goods to customers. These two new motor vehicles are to be depreciated using the straight-line method with an estimated useful life of five years. (2) On 28 February 2022, the company was being sued by a customer on his damage caused by the sofa sold in the e-shop. It was confirmed that the company had lost the case but the settlement had not yet been finalised by the court. Based on the estimation made by the accountant, the company recorded a provision for legal claim of HK$60,000 as expense for the year ended 31 March 2022. Required: Analyse whether the above-mentioned accounting treatments are appropriate for iMall Limited. In each case, you are required to support your analysis with ONE relevant accounting principle/ basis/ concept and ONE enhancing qualitative characteristic. (14 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
