      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2023 Session) Page 1 of 6 WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 100 MARKS) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 100% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (15 marks – approximately 27 minutes) Sunny has been working as a truck driver for Quick Service Company Limited (\"QSL\") for the past year. His main duty is to transport QSL goods to customers according to instructions given by QSL. Sunny is not paid a monthly salary. QSL does not have any obligation to assign any work to Sunny, and Sunny does not have any obligation to take up work assigned to him by QSL. When Sunny is assigned work on a particular day, he is paid a daily wage and a commission based on the quantity of the goods delivered. The truck Sunny uses to transport goods is owned and maintained by QSL, and Sunny is reimbursed for the petrol consumed by the truck when he delivers goods for QSL. Sunny must use the route prescribed by QSL and must seek permission from QSL if he wishes to use another route. For the last two months, Sunny has not received from QSL the wages owed to him. The total amount owed to Sunny is HK$22,000, and this amount has already been overdue for more than two months. When Sunny asked Mary, the manager of QSL, about the outstanding wages last week, Mary said that QSL was undergoing financial difficulty and he should wait patiently. Required: (a) Apply the employment law of Hong Kong with reference to relevant case law, and analyse the employment status between Sunny and QSL. (10 marks) (b) On the basis of your answer in part (a), analyse which court/ tribunal has jurisdiction to deal with Sunny's case, and describe the jurisdiction of the court/ tribunal if Sunny's claim involves an amount of HK$22,000. (5 marks)",
