      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2023 Session) Page 2 of 6 Question 2 (15 marks – approximately 27 minutes) Larry is a collector of vintage luxury watches of a few famous brands. He runs and operates a reputable antique shop called Wonderful Antiques (\"WA\"). Larry regularly checks the market value of each watch in his shop. One of Larry's friends, Winnie, has expressed a strong interest in buying a vintage watch (the \"Vintage Watch\") displayed in his shop which is without a price tag. On Christmas Eve last year, Larry offered the Vintage Watch to Winnie via email at the market price of HK$200,000. Winnie replied by email on Christmas Day that she could only afford to pay HK$140,000 for the Vintage Watch. Larry did not reply to Winnie's email sent to him on Christmas Day. Winnie then sent a second email to Larry on Boxing Day to tell him that she would be willing to pay HK$200,000 for the Vintage Watch. Larry refused to sell the Vintage Watch to Winnie. Winnie was very disappointed and wondered whether Larry could refuse to sell her the Vintage Watch at HK$200,000. Subsequently, Larry sold the Vintage Watch to Mrs. Lee, the aunt of his girlfriend, Susan, at HK$120,000 in order to please Susan. Mrs. Lee was very pleased and introduced her rich friend, Mrs. Money, to Larry. Mrs. Money bought the most expensive watch (the \"Expensive Watch\") available at WA. Recently, Larry broke up with Susan and he now regrets having sold the Vintage Watch to Mrs. Lee for HK$120,000, which was significantly below the market price. He now wants to find out whether she must pay the market price for the Vintage Watch from a legal point of view. A week ago, Mrs. Money received a call from the police and was told that the Expensive Watch she had bought from WA was stolen goods. Mrs. Money was very surprised to learn that the Expensive Watch was stolen goods because WA is known to be a reputable antique shop. Mrs. Money is wondering whether she has to surrender the Expensive Watch to the true owner, Mr. Wealthy. Required: (a) Apply contract law and analyse whether Larry was bound to sell the Vintage Watch to Winnie when she sent the second email to Larry on Boxing Day last year to tell him that she would be willing to pay HK$200,000 for the Vintage Watch. (5 marks) (b) Apply contract law and analyse whether the price of HK$120,000 which Mrs. Lee paid for the Vintage Watch is valid consideration. (5 marks) (c) In relation to the law of the sale of goods, analyse whether Mrs. Money must surrender the Expensive Watch to its true owner, Mr. Wealthy. (5 marks)",
