      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/M1-10LP+Past%20paper/1-10%20Past%20paper/m10/Module%2010%20Question%20Dec%202024.pdf#question-q-p004-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2024 Session) Page 4 of 7 Question 4 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Jerry is a well-established, wealthy and well-known businessman. His good friend Johanna is a renowned independent financial analyst. Johanna gives Jerry investment advice from time to time. Several weeks ago, Jerry expressed interest in investing in an app company known as High Gains Company Limited (\"HGL\"), the business of which is growing very fast. However, Jerry was worried that the sole owner of the shares in HGL, Ms Koh, may ask him to pay an inflated price for shares because she believed that he was a rich person. Therefore, Jerry did not want Ms Koh to know that he was interested in buying her shares. Jerry suggested that Johanna should contact Ms Koh and negotiate for a purchase of shares in HGL in her own name without telling Ms Koh that she was buying those shares on his behalf. Jerry offered to pay Johanna a handsome commission if she agreed to do this for him. Following months of negotiations with Ms Koh, Johanna managed to enter into a Share Purchase Agreement (the \"Agreement\") with Ms Koh involving an amount of HK$8 million. However, about a week before the completion date of the sale and purchase of the shares under the Agreement, Jerry learned that HGL's business had been substantially declining because the talented app designer Eric had left HGL. Jerry does not want to buy shares in HGL anymore. Ms Koh has just found out that Johanna is the agent of Jerry, and Jerry has instructed Johanna to buy shares in HGL on his behalf. Required: (a) In relation to agency law, analyse whether Ms Koh is entitled to enforce the contract against Jerry and/ or Johanna. (5 marks) (b) Regardless of whether Ms Koh wishes to enforce the Agreement against Jerry or Johanna, analyse which court/ tribunal has jurisdiction to deal with Ms Koh's case which involves an amount of HK$8 million. Explain the jurisdiction of that court/ tribunal. (5 marks)",
      "full": "Module 10 (December 2024 Session) Page 4 of 7 Question 4 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Jerry is a well-established, wealthy and well-known businessman. His good friend Johanna is a renowned independent financial analyst. Johanna gives Jerry investment advice from time to time. Several weeks ago, Jerry expressed interest in investing in an app company known as High Gains Company Limited (\"HGL\"), the business of which is growing very fast. However, Jerry was worried that the sole owner of the shares in HGL, Ms Koh, may ask him to pay an inflated price for shares because she believed that he was a rich person. Therefore, Jerry did not want Ms Koh to know that he was interested in buying her shares. Jerry suggested that Johanna should contact Ms Koh and negotiate for a purchase of shares in HGL in her own name without telling Ms Koh that she was buying those shares on his behalf. Jerry offered to pay Johanna a handsome commission if she agreed to do this for him. Following months of negotiations with Ms Koh, Johanna managed to enter into a Share Purchase Agreement (the \"Agreement\") with Ms Koh involving an amount of HK$8 million. However, about a week before the completion date of the sale and purchase of the shares under the Agreement, Jerry learned that HGL's business had been substantially declining because the talented app designer Eric had left HGL. Jerry does not want to buy shares in HGL anymore. Ms Koh has just found out that Johanna is the agent of Jerry, and Jerry has instructed Johanna to buy shares in HGL on his behalf. Required: (a) In relation to agency law, analyse whether Ms Koh is entitled to enforce the contract against Jerry and/ or Johanna. (5 marks) (b) Regardless of whether Ms Koh wishes to enforce the Agreement against Jerry or Johanna, analyse which court/ tribunal has jurisdiction to deal with Ms Koh's case which involves an amount of HK$8 million. Explain the jurisdiction of that court/ tribunal. (5 marks)",
