      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2024 Session) Page 5 of 7 Question 5 (30 marks – approximately 54 minutes) April, Billy and Cedric are good friends. About a year ago, they incorporated a company in Hong Kong, Best Style Limited (\"BSL\"), which specialises in designing and making avant garde bridal gowns. All three of them are the shareholders of BSL. April studied fashion design in Europe and was put in charge of the design and production of the bridal gowns. April was appointed as the sole director of BSL. Billy studied marketing and was appointed Marketing Manager. April and Billy are in a relationship and will be getting married soon. Cedric comes from a wealthy family. As Cedric does not know much about fashion, he only wants to provide capital to BSL in return for dividends. While BSL was being incorporated, Cedric told April and Billy that he trusted them both and was happy to be just a shareholder. Although Billy was not a director of BSL, he started to give instructions to April as regards the operation of the business right after the incorporation of BSL, and April always followed Billy's instructions. Soon after the incorporation of BSL, April received a lot of enquiries and the business of BSL flourished. One day, Billy suggested to April that they should set up their own bridal gown business. Billy said to April that it was not fair that Cedric received dividends without having to do anything. April and Billy then incorporated another company, Best of the Best Style Limited (\"BBL\") and began to divert the business of BSL to BBL. A few months ago, Cedric left Hong Kong because his mother fell sick in Canada. Before Cedric left Hong Kong, he told April and Billy that he might be away from Hong Kong for quite some time and thanked them for taking care of the business of BSL while he was away. The business of BSL began to decline. As April and Billy spent much of their time on the business of BBL, they hardly noticed that BSL was heavily indebted. After Cedric had returned to Hong Kong, he was surprised to accidentally hear from the General Manager of a supplier, Bobo, an old classmate of his, that BSL owed a few suppliers a substantial amount of money and seemed to be in grave financial difficulty. Required: In relation to company law in Hong Kong: (a) Explain what the different types of directors of a company are and analyse which type(s) of director April is. (8 marks) (b) Analyse the role played by Billy (apart from that of a Marketing Manager), given the fact that he has not been appointed as a director of BSL. (2 marks) (c) Explain the fiduciary duties owed by April to BSL, if any. (10 marks)",
