      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2024 Session) Page 7 of 7 Question 6 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Two months ago, Vivian received a huge amount of money from her rich grandmother as dowry for her marriage. Vivian wanted to make use of the money to make some investments in the stock market and she therefore decided to acquire 5% of the shares in Good Prospects Company Limited (\"GPL\"), a company listed on the Main Board of the Hong Kong Stock Exchange (\"HKSE\"), through her stockbroker, Jason. Vivian has been advised of the disclosure obligation of a substantial shareholder of a listed company. As Jason handled the transaction of acquisition of the shares for her, Vivian delegated the duty of disclosure to Jason. Due to a misunderstanding of the requirements of the law, Jason only gave notice to the HKSE but not GPL. Required: In relation to the laws relating to securities and futures: (a) Analyse under what circumstances a shareholder has the obligation to disclose his/ her interest in the shares of a listed company. (6 marks) (b) Analyse whether Vivian's delegation of the task of disclosure to Jason, her stockbroker, will constitute a defence for her non-compliance with the disclosure of interest requirements under Part XV of the Securities and Futures Ordinance (Cap.571). (4 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
