      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2020 Session) Page 2 of 6 Required: (a) Apply contract law and analyse whether there is a valid contract between the Company and Judy. (10 marks) (b) Apply anti-corruption laws and analyse what law(s) and provision(s) has/ have been violated by Sam. (5 marks) (c) Apply employment law (common law and statute) and analyse whether the Company can terminate its employment with Sam without notice with regard to Sam's conduct. (5 marks) (d) In relation to agency law, explain how agency can be created and analyse how agency is created in Sam's case. (5 marks) Question 2 (25 marks – approximately 45 minutes) Alvin, Beckham and Christopher were good friends, and a private company was incorporated by them in Hong Kong. The company adopted the Model Articles for Private Companies Limited by Shares as the articles. It was agreed that Alvin, Beckham and Christopher shall participate in the management of the company. Alvin, Beckham and Christopher are the directors of the company and each owns 2,000 issued shares in the company. They each have a director's salary in the sum of HK$50,000 per month. In addition, Alvin lent HK$500,000 to the company as a shareholder's loan. Recently, Alvin, Beckham and Christopher had strong arguments over the management of a company project. As a result, Alvin, Beckham and Christopher were engaged in a serious dispute. Beckham and Christopher decided that they were unable to work with Alvin. Alvin also requested repayment of the shareholder's loan while Beckham and Christopher refused to repay the loan to Alvin. Alvin was removed from the directorship by Beckham and Christopher. Alvin would like to bring an action against Beckham and Christopher. Required: In relation to company and winding-up laws: (a) Analyse whether Alvin may apply for an unfair prejudicial remedy under the company law. (10 marks)",
      "full": "Module 10 (December 2020 Session) Page 2 of 6 Required: (a) Apply contract law and analyse whether there is a valid contract between the Company and Judy. (10 marks) (b) Apply anti-corruption laws and analyse what law(s) and provision(s) has/ have been violated by Sam. (5 marks) (c) Apply employment law (common law and statute) and analyse whether the Company can terminate its employment with Sam without notice with regard to Sam's conduct. (5 marks) (d) In relation to agency law, explain how agency can be created and analyse how agency is created in Sam's case. (5 marks) Question 2 (25 marks – approximately 45 minutes) Alvin, Beckham and Christopher were good friends, and a private company was incorporated by them in Hong Kong. The company adopted the Model Articles for Private Companies Limited by Shares as the articles. It was agreed that Alvin, Beckham and Christopher shall participate in the management of the company. Alvin, Beckham and Christopher are the directors of the company and each owns 2,000 issued shares in the company. They each have a director's salary in the sum of HK$50,000 per month. In addition, Alvin lent HK$500,000 to the company as a shareholder's loan. Recently, Alvin, Beckham and Christopher had strong arguments over the management of a company project. As a result, Alvin, Beckham and Christopher were engaged in a serious dispute. Beckham and Christopher decided that they were unable to work with Alvin. Alvin also requested repayment of the shareholder's loan while Beckham and Christopher refused to repay the loan to Alvin. Alvin was removed from the directorship by Beckham and Christopher. Alvin would like to bring an action against Beckham and Christopher. Required: In relation to company and winding-up laws: (a) Analyse whether Alvin may apply for an unfair prejudicial remedy under the company law. (10 marks)",
