      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (June 2023 Session) Page 1 of 6 WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 100 MARKS) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 100% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (15 marks – approximately 27 minutes) Mr. Lee set up a private limited company, B & B Company Limited (\"B & B\"), to operate a beverage business two years ago. Mr. Lee left the operation of the business to two of his employees, namely Susan, the Sales and Marketing Manager and Peter, the Purchasing Manager. About a year ago, Mr. Lee introduced a substantial client, W & W Company Limited (\"W & W\"), to Susan and put her in charge of business dealings with W & W. Being greatly impressed by Susan's knowledge of wine, the Managing Director of W & W said to Susan during a business dinner that he hoped Susan could serve his company exclusively. Susan then resigned from her position and set up a private limited company to take up the business W & W promised to give her. One day, Mr. Lee suggested that Peter should source some exotic drinks to cater for young adult clients. In order to persuade Peter to purchase its products, one beverage supplier T & T Company Limited (\"T & T\") offered to pay Peter a commission if he agreed to buy its products on behalf of B & B. Peter subsequently agreed to purchase T & T's products and received a secret commission from T & T without asking for Mr. Lee's prior approval. Soon after T & T had started to supply its products to B & B, Mr. Lee was told by one of his employees in the Purchasing Department of B & B that Peter had been accepting secret commission from T & T. Recently, Mr. Lee was told by one of the employees of W & W that they had been ordering substantial quantities of wine from Susan's company for some time instead of ordering from B & B. Mr. Lee subsequently found in the employment contract signed between B & B and Susan a restrictive covenant prohibiting Susan from competing with B & B after the termination of her employment. Required: (a) In relation to employment law, analyse whether Susan's act of setting up her own company to take up the business of W & W would result in breach of any fiduciary duties owed to B & B and the legal consequences, if any. (You can assume that the restrictive covenant in her employment contract with her former employer B & B is valid.) (5 marks) (b) Apply anti-corruption laws and analyse whether Peter may have committed any criminal offence by accepting the secret commission from T & T. (5 marks) (c) Apply employment law, including employment legislation and common law, and analyse whether B & B is entitled to terminate the employment of Peter by summary dismissal and on what grounds if B & B is entitled to do so. (5 marks)",
