      "full": "Question 1 (15 marks — approximately 27 minutes)\nMr. Lee set up a private limited company, B & B Company Limited (\"B & B\"), to operate\na beverage business two years ago. Mr. Lee left the operation of the business to two of\nhis employees, namely Susan, the Sales and Marketing Manager and Peter, the Purchasing\nManager. About a year ago, Mr. Lee introduced a substantial client, W & W Company\nLimited (\"W & W\"), to Susan and put her in charge of business dealings with W & W.\nBeing greatly impressed by Susan's knowledge of wine, the Managing Director of W & W\nsaid to Susan during a business dinner that he hoped Susan could serve his company\nexclusively. Susan then resigned from her position and set up a private limited company to\ntake up the business W & W promised to give her.\nOne day, Mr. Lee suggested that Peter should source some exotic drinks to cater for young\nadult clients. In order to persuade Peter to purchase its products, one beverage supplier\nT & T Company Limited (\"T & T\") offered to pay Peter a commission if he agreed to buy its\nproducts on behalf of B & B. Peter subsequently agreed to purchase T & T's products and\nreceived a secret commission from T & T without asking for Mr. Lee's prior approval.\nSoon after T & T had started to supply its products to B & B, Mr. Lee was told by one of\nhis employees in the Purchasing Department of B & B that Peter had been accepting secret\ncommission from T & T.\nRecently, Mr. Lee was told by one of the employees of W & W that they had been ordering\nsubstantial quantities of wine from Susan's company for some time instead of ordering from\nB & B. Mr. Lee subsequently found in the employment contract signed between B & B\nand Susan a restrictive covenant prohibiting Susan from competing with B & B after\nthe termination of her employment.\nRequired:\n(a) In relation to employment law, analyse whether Susan's act of setting up her\nown company to take up the business of W & W would result in breach of any\nfiduciary duties owed to B & B and the legal consequences, if any. (You can\nassume that the restrictive covenant in her employment contract with her former\nemployer B & B is valid.)\n(5 marks)\n(b) Apply anti-corruption laws and analyse whether Peter may have committed any\ncriminal offence by accepting the secret commission from T & T.\n(5 marks)\n(c) Apply employment law, including employment legislation and common law, and\nanalyse whether B & B is entitled to terminate the employment of Peter by\nsummary dismissal and on what grounds if B & B is entitled to do so.\n(5 marks)\nModule 10 (June 2023 Session) Page 1 of 6\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
