      "number": "3",
      "prompt": "(15 marks — approximately 27 minutes)\nDavid is the sole shareholder of a small private limited company, Treasures Company Limited\n(\"TCL\") set up to deal in precious stones.\nSandy is employed as a director of TCL and her responsibilities include ordering precious\nstones from different suppliers and reselling them to clients. Sandy is authorised by TCL to\nsign contracts with both suppliers and clients. About a month ago, Sandy tendered\nher resignation with the required notice period to David. When Sandy tendered\nher resignation, David asked Sandy to hand over the work she was doing to other colleagues\nand not to engage in any new business with any suppliers or clients. Two days after\nher resignation, Sandy placed an order for a few expensive precious stones with one of\nthe suppliers, ABD Company Limited (\"ABD\"). Sandy then went to ABD to pick up the stones,\nwhich she did so from time to time on behalf of TCL. ABD knew nothing about\nSandy's resignation because none of the suppliers were informed of Sandy's resignation.\nSandy subsequently left TCL after the expiry of the notice period and disappeared with the\nprecious stones ordered from ABD.\nRecently, TCL has been suffering from serious financial problems and one of\nthe suppliers, XYZ Company Limited (\"XYZ\"), has threatened to wind up TCL if TCL fails\nto repay the debt in the amount of HK$50,000 owed to it. The debt is already overdue.\nDavid does not think TCL owes XYZ any debt because the goods delivered by XYZ to TCL\nnot long ago were defective and not worth the price of HK$50,000.\nRequired:\n(3 marks)\n(ii) analyse whether Sandy had the authority to order the precious stones on\nbehalf of TCL after her resignation.\n(4 marks)\n(iii) analyse whether TCL is liable to pay for those precious stones.\n(3 marks)\npetition for the winding-up of TCL if TCL fails to repay the debt owed to XYZ.\n(5 marks)\nModule 10 (June 2023 Session) Page 3 of 6\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
      "full": "Question 3 (15 marks — approximately 27 minutes)\nDavid is the sole shareholder of a small private limited company, Treasures Company Limited\n(\"TCL\") set up to deal in precious stones.\nSandy is employed as a director of TCL and her responsibilities include ordering precious\nstones from different suppliers and reselling them to clients. Sandy is authorised by TCL to\nsign contracts with both suppliers and clients. About a month ago, Sandy tendered\nher resignation with the required notice period to David. When Sandy tendered\nher resignation, David asked Sandy to hand over the work she was doing to other colleagues\nand not to engage in any new business with any suppliers or clients. Two days after\nher resignation, Sandy placed an order for a few expensive precious stones with one of\nthe suppliers, ABD Company Limited (\"ABD\"). Sandy then went to ABD to pick up the stones,\nwhich she did so from time to time on behalf of TCL. ABD knew nothing about\nSandy's resignation because none of the suppliers were informed of Sandy's resignation.\nSandy subsequently left TCL after the expiry of the notice period and disappeared with the\nprecious stones ordered from ABD.\nRecently, TCL has been suffering from serious financial problems and one of\nthe suppliers, XYZ Company Limited (\"XYZ\"), has threatened to wind up TCL if TCL fails\nto repay the debt in the amount of HK$50,000 owed to it. The debt is already overdue.\nDavid does not think TCL owes XYZ any debt because the goods delivered by XYZ to TCL\nnot long ago were defective and not worth the price of HK$50,000.\nRequired:\n(a) In relation to agency law,\n(i) explain the different types of an agent's authority.\n(3 marks)\n(ii) analyse whether Sandy had the authority to order the precious stones on\nbehalf of TCL after her resignation.\n(4 marks)\n(iii) analyse whether TCL is liable to pay for those precious stones.\n(3 marks)\n(b) In relation to company and winding-up laws, analyse whether XYZ is entitled to\npetition for the winding-up of TCL if TCL fails to repay the debt owed to XYZ.\n(5 marks)\nModule 10 (June 2023 Session) Page 3 of 6\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
