      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (June 2024 Session) Page 5 of 6 Question 5 (25 marks – approximately 45 minutes) Adam, Bobo, and Celine are the sole shareholders and directors of a private limited company, Good Deal Limited (\"GDL\"), incorporated in Hong Kong to run an eco-friendly and sustainable garment business. Part of their corporate strategy is to borrow money from banks to finance their business by creating fixed and floating charges over assets of GDL such as property, inventories, and book debts. Therefore, they intend to seek professional advice on debt financing soon after the commencement of the operation of their business. Unfortunately, GDL has not been able to get any business for six months after its incorporation despite the hard work of Adam, Bobo, and Celine. They are very disappointed, and Adam has suggested that GDL should apply for dormant status to save some costs if they are still unable to obtain any business in the following three months. Bobo and Celine have agreed with Adam's suggestion. Celine has even proposed that they should dissolve their company by de-registration to minimise their losses if GDL does not get any business within one year after its incorporation. Nevertheless, they have agreed to continue to work hard for the next six months. Required: In relation to company law: (a) (i) Explain what a debenture is. (2 marks) (ii) Explain and analyse what a fixed charge is and how a valid fixed charge can be created. (5 marks) (iii) Explain and analyse what a floating charge is and how a valid floating charge can be created. (8 marks) (b) With reference to the Companies Ordinance (Cap.622), explain how a company can apply for dormant status and explain the advantages of being a dormant company from the Companies Ordinance perspective. (4 marks) (c) Explain the requirements for deregistering a company. (6 marks)",
      "full": "Module 10 (June 2024 Session) Page 5 of 6 Question 5 (25 marks – approximately 45 minutes) Adam, Bobo, and Celine are the sole shareholders and directors of a private limited company, Good Deal Limited (\"GDL\"), incorporated in Hong Kong to run an eco-friendly and sustainable garment business. Part of their corporate strategy is to borrow money from banks to finance their business by creating fixed and floating charges over assets of GDL such as property, inventories, and book debts. Therefore, they intend to seek professional advice on debt financing soon after the commencement of the operation of their business. Unfortunately, GDL has not been able to get any business for six months after its incorporation despite the hard work of Adam, Bobo, and Celine. They are very disappointed, and Adam has suggested that GDL should apply for dormant status to save some costs if they are still unable to obtain any business in the following three months. Bobo and Celine have agreed with Adam's suggestion. Celine has even proposed that they should dissolve their company by de-registration to minimise their losses if GDL does not get any business within one year after its incorporation. Nevertheless, they have agreed to continue to work hard for the next six months. Required: In relation to company law: (a) (i) Explain what a debenture is. (2 marks) (ii) Explain and analyse what a fixed charge is and how a valid fixed charge can be created. (5 marks) (iii) Explain and analyse what a floating charge is and how a valid floating charge can be created. (8 marks) (b) With reference to the Companies Ordinance (Cap.622), explain how a company can apply for dormant status and explain the advantages of being a dormant company from the Companies Ordinance perspective. (4 marks) (c) Explain the requirements for deregistering a company. (6 marks)",
