      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (June 2024 Session) Page 6 of 6 Question 6 (15 marks – approximately 27 minutes) Ricky is one of the general partners of a solicitor firm, Man, Chin, & Co (\"MCC\"), a limited partnership. MCC is the legal advisor of Sure Win Company Limited (\"SWL\"), a company listed on the Main Board of the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong. Ricky is a member of the project team of a colossal construction project in which SWL has been involved for months. A week ago, the Project Manager appointed by SWL, Michelle, disclosed to the project team that SWL had won the tender for the colossal construction project and the management of SWL should expect the share price of SWL to rise substantially after announcement of this piece of information. This piece of information was only known to the members of the project team and the management of SWL. Before the announcement of this piece of information to the public, Ricky bought a substantial number of shares of SWL. Three days ago, this piece of information was announced and the share price of SWL rose substantially. Ricky made considerable profit after selling the shares of SWL and thought of going into retirement. The other partners of MCC in the partnership did not want Ricky to retire because Ricky was the most experienced partner of MCC in the partnership and had a good relationship with all the clients. Ricky proposed that he could change his status from a general partner to a limited partner and thereby limit his risk. Required: (a) In relation to securities and futures law of Hong Kong: (i) Analyse the nature of the information disclosed by Michelle to Ricky. (3 marks) (ii) Analyse whether Ricky might have committed a criminal offence by dealing in the shares of SWL, and what are the legal consequences, if any. (7 marks) (b) In relation to partnership law in Hong Kong: (i) Explain the difference(s) in the liability of a general partner and a limited partner of a limited partnership. (3 marks) (ii) Explain what MCC needs to do to comply with the legal requirements if Ricky decides to change his status from being a general partner to that of being a limited partner. (2 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
