      "number": "4",
      "prompt": "(15 marks — approximately 27 minutes)\nBenny is a newly qualified chartered financial analyst working in a corporate finance\ncompany as a financial analyst.\nBenny is also lecturing corporate finance at a local university in the evening on a part-time\nbasis. In one of his lectures, he discussed and analysed the business prospect of a listed\ncompany in Hong Kong, and concluded that this listed company has good potential to grow\nin the next 12 months.\nTwo of his students, Sam and Danny, learned from this information in the class, and they\ndecided to invest in this listed company and buy its shares from the stock market.\nAfter about 10 months, the share price of this listed company collapsed. Sam and Danny\nsuffered from serious financial losses. They wanted to sue Benny for negligent\nmisstatement.\nRequired:\nIn relation to tort of negligence:\n(5 marks)\n(10 marks)\nModule 10 (June 2021 Session) Page 3 of 6\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
      "full": "Question 4 (15 marks — approximately 27 minutes)\nBenny is a newly qualified chartered financial analyst working in a corporate finance\ncompany as a financial analyst.\nBenny is also lecturing corporate finance at a local university in the evening on a part-time\nbasis. In one of his lectures, he discussed and analysed the business prospect of a listed\ncompany in Hong Kong, and concluded that this listed company has good potential to grow\nin the next 12 months.\nTwo of his students, Sam and Danny, learned from this information in the class, and they\ndecided to invest in this listed company and buy its shares from the stock market.\nAfter about 10 months, the share price of this listed company collapsed. Sam and Danny\nsuffered from serious financial losses. They wanted to sue Benny for negligent\nmisstatement.\nRequired:\nIn relation to tort of negligence:\n(a) Explain the term \"negligent misstatement”.\n(5 marks)\n(b) Analyse whether Benny is liable for negligent misstatement.\n(10 marks)\nModule 10 (June 2021 Session) Page 3 of 6\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
