      "full": "Question 5 (15 marks — approximately 27 minutes)\nEdward and Samuel are brothers. Edward is a good chef for Chinese cuisine and Samuel\nis good at making coffee and tea. They both had their own restaurants. Five years ago,\nthey decided to merge the two restaurants into one big restaurant for the purpose of listing\non the stock exchange.\nAs a result of the merger, a private company was incorporated by Edward and Samuel in\nHong Kong. The company adopted the Model Articles for Private Companies Limited by\nShares as the articles. The corporate governance structure is that Samuel, Edward and\nhis wife Thalia are directors. It was agreed that Samuel, Edward and Thalia shall\nparticipate in the management of the company. Only Samuel and Edward are working\nfull-time and Thalia is assisting the paper works on a part-time basis. They each have\na director's salary in the sum of HK$100,000 per month. Samuel, Edward and Thalia each\nowns one share in the company.\nRecently, Samuel, Edward and Thalia had strong arguments over the issue of listing on\nthe stock exchange. As a result, Edward and Thalia decided that they were unable to work\nwith Samuel. Samuel was removed from the directorship by Edward and Thalia.\nIn this regard, Samuel would like to bring an action against Edward and Thalia\nand/ or the company.\nRequired:\nIn relation to company and winding-up laws:\n(a) Analyse whether Samuel may apply for an unfair prejudicial remedy under\nthe company law.\n(10 marks)\n(b) Analyse whether Samuel may petition to wind up the company under\nthe winding-up law.\n(5 marks)\nModule 10 (June 2021 Session) Page 4 of 6\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
