      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2025 Session) Page 1 of 6 WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 100 MARKS) You should allocate approximately 3 hours in total for SIX compulsory written questions in this examination (i.e. approximately 1.8 minutes for each mark). Question 1 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) You are required to complete the following tasks in this question: (a) In relation to the employment law in Hong Kong, explain the fiduciary duties owed by an employee to his/ her employer and analyse whether John's act of disclosing confidential information of his employer High Tech Company Limited (\"HTL\") to WinWin Company Limited (\"WWL\") and his diverting of HTL's business opportunities to WWL amounted to a breach of any fiduciary duties owed to HTL, as well as the legal consequences, if any. (10 marks) (b) Apply anti-corruption laws in Hong Kong and analyse whether John may have committed any criminal offence by offering a monetary reward to Beatrice. (5 marks) (c) Regardless of your answer in part (a), explain to HTL which court/ tribunal will hear its case if HTL wishes to sue John for damages in the amount of HK$2.5 million. (5 marks) Case Background: John is a software engineer, who was hired by High Tech Company Limited (\"HTL\") two years ago as Sales Manager due to his rich experience and connections in the software industry. John was popular with HTL's clients who had great respect for his industry experience. Matthew, the Managing Director of HTL, was quite satisfied with John's work performance too. A few months ago, John managed to persuade a substantial client, Great Advance Company Limited (\"GAL\") to enter into a Service Agreement with HTL pursuant to which HTL was engaged to be GAL's exclusive service provider of software applications. One day, John and Matthew had a heated argument about HTL's future company strategy and the relationship between John and Matthew turned sour. John then decided to resign from his position. Before he tendered his resignation, John approached Beatrice, the Marketing Director of GAL, to persuade her to terminate the Service Agreement with HTL and engage Great Prospects Company Limited (\"GPL\"), a private limited company newly incorporated by him, to be GAL's exclusive service provider of software applications. Although Beatrice had high regard for John's knowledge and experience in the software industry, she hesitated to engage a newly incorporated company to be GAL's exclusive service provider of software applications. John then offered to give a monetary reward to Beatrice in return for GAL's engaging GPL to be its exclusive service provider of software applications. Furthermore, it was found that John had disclosed some confidential information of HTL to another company, WinWin Company Limited (\"WWL\") and diverted some of HTL's business opportunities to WWL. ∗ ∗ ∗ END OF SCENARIO ∗ ∗ ∗",
