      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2025 Session) Page 2 of 6 Question 2 (15 marks – approximately 27 minutes) You are required to complete the following tasks in this question: In relation to the contract law in Hong Kong: (a) Explain the different ways to discharge a contract. (10 marks) (b) Analyse whether the tenancy agreement entered into between Sam and Mrs Rich was frustrated by the fire which had resulted in reduced pedestrian flows and reduced business. (5 marks) Case Background: After having worked as a chef at a hotel for a few years, Sam decided to open his own restaurant. About a year ago, Sam entered into a tenancy agreement with Mrs Rich pursuant to which Mrs Rich leased to Sam a shop in a mall at Causeway Bay. Due to the weak economy, Sam's restaurant business was not very good. One day, a fire accidentally broke out and as a result the mall had to be closed for about two weeks. Sam's shop was not badly damaged by the fire but he wishes to stop paying the rent and rates soon after the fire. Soon after the re-opening of the mall, Sam asked his landlord Mrs Rich for a 50% reduction in rent on the grounds of reduced pedestrian flows which made doing business very difficult. While Sam was having a chat with a friend who was a lawyer, he was advised that a contract could be discharged by frustration. When Mrs Rich refused Sam's request, Sam stopped paying the rent and rates. Later Mrs Rich threatened to sue Sam for the outstanding rent and rates, Sam argued that the tenancy agreement he had entered into with Mrs Rich was frustrated due to the temporary closure of the mall which in turn led to reduced pedestrian flows and therefore reduced business. Sam also alleged that there were structural defects in the mall without providing any proof for this allegation. ∗ ∗ ∗ END OF SCENARIO ∗ ∗ ∗",
