      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2025 Session) Page 4 of 6 Question 4 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) You are required to complete the following tasks in this question: In relation to Hong Kong company law: (a) Explain how a company can apply for dormant status and what the advantages of being a dormant company are. (6 marks) (b) Explain the requirements and procedures for deregistering a company. (6 marks) (c) Explain the procedures as to how High Precision Company Limited can be dissolved. (8 marks) Case Background: Leo and Janice are good friends. Leo is an Interior Designer. He incorporated a private company, Versatile Design Company Limited (\"VDL\"), to run his interior design business about eight months ago. Janice is an AI Solutions Engineer. She incorporated a private company, High Precision Company Limited (\"HPL\") about two years ago to provide AI solutions to various industries in Hong Kong. HPL has been profitable since its incorporation. Owing to the sluggish property market, VDL has not got any business since its incorporation. Leo is very upset and is considering closing his business. Leo's sister Lucy, who is a lawyer, suggested the following to him: (i) Leo's company should apply for a dormant status so that Leo can save some costs while waiting for the property market to recover. (ii) Leo can dissolve his company by de-registration to minimise his losses if he is tired of waiting for the property market to recover. A few days ago, Janice called Leo to tell him that she would be leaving Hong Kong for good in order to look after her parents who emigrated to Canada a few years ago. Knowing that Lucy is a lawyer, Janice would like Leo to ask Lucy how to dissolve her company HPL which is solvent and still in normal operation. ∗ ∗ ∗ END OF SCENARIO ∗ ∗ ∗",
      "full": "Module 10 (December 2025 Session) Page 4 of 6 Question 4 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) You are required to complete the following tasks in this question: In relation to Hong Kong company law: (a) Explain how a company can apply for dormant status and what the advantages of being a dormant company are. (6 marks) (b) Explain the requirements and procedures for deregistering a company. (6 marks) (c) Explain the procedures as to how High Precision Company Limited can be dissolved. (8 marks) Case Background: Leo and Janice are good friends. Leo is an Interior Designer. He incorporated a private company, Versatile Design Company Limited (\"VDL\"), to run his interior design business about eight months ago. Janice is an AI Solutions Engineer. She incorporated a private company, High Precision Company Limited (\"HPL\") about two years ago to provide AI solutions to various industries in Hong Kong. HPL has been profitable since its incorporation. Owing to the sluggish property market, VDL has not got any business since its incorporation. Leo is very upset and is considering closing his business. Leo's sister Lucy, who is a lawyer, suggested the following to him: (i) Leo's company should apply for a dormant status so that Leo can save some costs while waiting for the property market to recover. (ii) Leo can dissolve his company by de-registration to minimise his losses if he is tired of waiting for the property market to recover. A few days ago, Janice called Leo to tell him that she would be leaving Hong Kong for good in order to look after her parents who emigrated to Canada a few years ago. Knowing that Lucy is a lawyer, Janice would like Leo to ask Lucy how to dissolve her company HPL which is solvent and still in normal operation. ∗ ∗ ∗ END OF SCENARIO ∗ ∗ ∗",
