      "full": "Question 4 (20 marks — approximately 36 minutes)\nYou are required to complete the following tasks in this question:\nIn relation to Hong Kong company law:\n(a) Explain how a company can apply for dormant status and what the advantages\nof being a dormant company are. (6 marks)\n(b) Explain the requirements and procedures for deregistering a company.\n(6 marks)\n(c) Explain the procedures as to how High Precision Company Limited can be\ndissolved. (8 marks)\nCase Background:\nLeo and Janice are good friends. Leo is an Interior Designer. He incorporated a private\ncompany, Versatile Design Company Limited (\"VDL\"), to run his interior design business\nabout eight months ago. Janice is an Al Solutions Engineer. She incorporated a private\ncompany, High Precision Company Limited (\"HPL\") about two years ago to provide Al\nsolutions to various industries in Hong Kong. HPL has been profitable since its\nincorporation.\nOwing to the sluggish property market, VDL has not got any business since its incorporation.\nLeo is very upset and is considering closing his business. Leo's sister Lucy, who is a lawyer,\nsuggested the following to him:\n(i) Leo's company should apply for a dormant status so that Leo can save some costs\nwhile waiting for the property market to recover.\n(ii) Leo can dissolve his company by de-registration to minimise his losses if he is tired of\nwaiting for the property market to recover.\nAfew days ago, Janice called Leo to tell him that she would be leaving Hong Kong for good\nin order to look after her parents who emigrated to Canada a few years ago. Knowing that\nLucy is a lawyer, Janice would like Leo to ask Lucy how to dissolve her company HPL which\nis solvent and still in normal operation.\n+ + * ENDOFSCENARIO x * =x\nModule 10 (December 2025 Session) Page 4 of 6\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
