      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 10 (December 2025 Session) Page 6 of 6 Question 6 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) You are required to complete the following tasks in this question: In relation to Hong Kong securities law: Analyse whether Maggie, Sam and Nancy may be liable for any criminal/ civil offence. (10 marks) Case Background: A few months ago, Maggie, the Managing Director of Healthy and Goodie Company Limited (\"HGL\"), a company listed on the GEM Board of the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong engaged in sale and purchase of health supplements, was actively involved in negotiations about the acquisition of a majority stake in HGL by High Win Company Limited, a wholly owned subsidiary of a company listed in the Stock Exchange of Shanghai. Maggie expected the share price of HGL to rise substantially if the acquisition could materialise. Therefore, she bought a substantial number of shares of HGL through the securities accounts of her brother Sam and Sam's wife Nancy during the period of negotiations when the news about the acquisition was not yet announced. Both Sam and Nancy allowed Maggie to operate and control their securities accounts. Sam also bought some shares of HGL through his own securities account. A few weeks ago, the acquisition of shares of HGL was completed and announced. Subsequently, the price of the shares of HGL rose substantially. Maggie sold all the shares of HGL which she had bought and made a handsome profit of about HK$5 million. The Securities and Futures Commission has recently started to conduct investigations into Maggie's purchase and sale of the shares of HGL. Maggie and Sam are now very worried. Nancy is not worried because she may raise the defence that she was busy looking after her sick mother in the last few months and was not concerned about what shares were bought or sold through her securities account. ∗ ∗ ∗ END OF SCENARIO ∗ ∗ ∗ * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
