      "full": "Module 9 (December 2020 Session) Page 1 of 11 Table A: Personal allowances and deductions Year of assessment 2017/18 2018/19 Personal allowances HK$ HK$ Basic 132,000 132,000 Married person's 264,000 264,000 Single parent 132,000 132,000 Child 1 st to 9 th child (each) 100,000 120,000 Additional allowance in the year of birth (each) 100,000 120,000 Dependent parent/ grandparent (aged 60 or above or is eligible to claim an allowance under the Government's Disability Allowance Scheme) Basic 46,000 50,000 Additional (for dependant residing with taxpayer continuously throughout the whole year) 46,000 50,000 Dependent parent/ grandparent (aged 55 – 59) Basic 23,000 25,000 Additional (for dependant residing with taxpayer continuously throughout the whole year) 23,000 25,000 Dependent brother/ sister 37,500 37,500 Personal disability - 75,000 Disabled dependant 75,000 75,000 Deductions/ Concessionary deductions HK$ HK$ Self-education expenses 100,000 100,000 Home loan interest 100,000 100,000 Elderly residential care expenses 92,000 100,000 Contributions to recognised retirement schemes 18,000 18,000 Approved charitable donations 35% 35% Depreciation allowances (For all years of assessment in this paper) Plant and machinery: Initial allowance (\"I.A.\") 60% Annual allowance (\"A.A.\") Given in question Industrial building: I.A. 20% A.A. 4% Commercial building: A.A. 4%",
      "options": [],
