      "ocrUsed": false,
      "answer": "Module 9 (December 2020 Session) Page 7 of 7 Answer 6 The agreement for sale and purchase (\"ASP\"): Ad valorem duty (\"AVD\") The ASP executed on 15 July 2018 is chargeable with AVD at the scale 2 rates because the purchaser, Peter, is a Hong Kong permanent resident, he did not own any residential property in Hong Kong at the time of purchase and he purchased the property on his own behalf. The amount of AVD is as follows: AVD = HK$9,000,000 x 3.75% = HK$337,500 Special stamp duty (\"SSD\") Although the vendor Tony purchased the residential property after 27 October 2012, he owned the property for over 36 months, he is not liable to SSD. Buyer's stamp duty (\"BSD\") The ASP is not chargeable with BSD as the purchaser Peter is a Hong Kong permanent resident. The conveyance on sale (\"COS\"): Ad valorem duty (\"AVD\") The COS dated 1 September 2018 is executed not in conformity with the earlier APS because the nominee Mary is not a close relative of the purchaser Peter and therefore Mary and Peter cannot be treated as the same person. The COS is chargeable with AVD at the scale 1 rates at 15% for the half share interest assigned by Peter to Mary by reference to the value of the property at the date of conveyance, because Mary is not a Hong Kong permanent resident. The amount of AVD is as follows: AVD = HK$9,500,000 x 15% x 1/2 = HK$712,500 Special stamp duty (\"SSD\") Peter assigned half share of the property to Mary within 2 months after acquisition on 15 July 2018, he is liable to SSD as follows: SSD = HK$9,500,000 x 20% x 1/2 = HK$950,000 Buyer's stamp duty (\"BSD\") As Mary is not a close relative of Peter and she is not a Hong Kong permanent resident, there is no exemption from BSD. BSD is based on the value of the property as follows: BSD = HK$9,500,000 x 15% = HK$1,425,000 * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *\nThe agreement for sale and purchase (\"ASP\"):\nAd valorem duty (\"AVD\")\nThe ASP executed on 15 July 2018 is chargeable with AVD at the scale 2 rates because the\npurchaser, Peter, is a Hong Kong permanent resident, he did not own any residential property\nin Hong Kong at the time of purchase and he purchased the property on his own behalf.\nThe amount of AVD is as follows:\nAVD = HK$9,000,000 x 3.75% = HK$337,500\nSpecial stamp duty (\"SSD\")\nAlthough the vendor Tony purchased the residential property after 27 October 2012, he\nowned the property for over 36 months, he is not liable to SSD.\nBuyer's stamp duty (\"BSD\")\nThe ASP is not chargeable with BSD as the purchaser Peter is a Hong Kong permanent\nresident.\nThe conveyance on sale (\"COS\"):\nAd valorem duty (\"AVD\")\nThe COS dated 1 September 2018 is executed not in conformity with the earlier APS\nbecause the nominee Mary is not a close relative of the purchaser Peter and therefore Mary\nand Peter cannot be treated as the same person. The COS is chargeable with AVD at the\nscale 1 rates at 15% for the half share interest assigned by Peter to Mary by reference to the\nvalue of the property at the date of conveyance, because Mary is not a Hong Kong\npermanent resident. The amount of AVD is as follows:\nAVD = HK$9,500,000 x 15% x 1/2 = HK$712,500\nSpecial stamp duty (\"SSD\")\nPeter assigned half share of the property to Mary within 2 months after acquisition on\n15 July 2018, he is liable to SSD as follows:\nSSD = HK$9,500,000 x 20% x 1/2 = HK$950,000\nBuyer's stamp duty (\"BSD\")\nAs Mary is not a close relative of Peter and she is not a Hong Kong permanent resident,\nthere is no exemption from BSD. BSD is based on the value of the property as follows:\nBSD = HK$9,500,000 x 15% = HK$1,425,000\n* * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
