      "prompt": "Module 9 (December 2022 Session) Page 9 of 11 Question 4 (9 marks – approximately 16 minutes) Raymond and Judy are husband and wife and are ordinarily residents in Hong Kong. They own a residential flat in North Point (the flat) with ownership ratio of 2:1. The flat was let out at a monthly rent of HK$28,000. Rates of HK$2,000 per quarter were payable by the tenant. They purchased the flat by means of a mortgage loan from Hang Seng Bank in Hong Kong. During the year ended 31 March 2021, they paid mortgage loan interest of HK$57,000. You have also been supplied with the following information regarding Raymond's income and expenses for the year ended 31 March 2021: (1) Raymond is the director/shareholder of Spring Limited, a company incorporated and caries on business in Hong Kong. He received the following income from Spring Limited: HK$ Director's remuneration 1,500,000 Dividends 420,000 Interest on loan to Spring Limited 80,000 (2) Net assessable profit from his sole - proprietorship business in Hong Kong: HK$299,000 (3) Share of business loss from a partnership business in Hong Kong: (HK$400,000) Expenses: (4) Mortgage loan interest paid of HK$189,000 to Hong Kong Bank in respect of his solely-owned dwelling. (5) He had made total cash donations of HK$500,000 to approved charitable organisations, out of which HK$161,000 had been allowed under his sole-proprietorship profits tax assessment. (6) Contributions to an MPF scheme of HK$18,000. Other information: (7) Judy is not working during the year. (8) Judy made cash donations of HK$300,000 to approved charitable organisations. (9) Raymond and Judy jointly elected for personal assessment for the year of assessment 2020/21. Required: (a) Compute the respective amounts of net assessable value of the flat attributable to Raymond and Judy for the year of assessment 2020/21. (3 marks) (b) Calculate the reduced total income (before personal allowances) in respect of Raymond and Judy under personal assessment for the year of assessment 2020/21. (6 marks)",
