      "prompt": "Module 9 (December 2023 Session) Page 11 of 12 Question 5 (9 marks – approximately 16 minutes) Bruce and Betty are husband and wife and they are ordinarily residents in Hong Kong. They own a residential flat in Hong Kong with ownership ratio of 2:1. The flat has been let to Daniel at a monthly rent of HK$20,000 since January 2001. Rates are payable by the landlord. During the year ended 31 March 2022, Bruce and Betty paid the following in relation to the residential flat: (1) Rates (after rates concession). HK$4,800 (2) Mortgage loan interest for the purchase of the residential flat to Hang Seng Bank. HK$60,000 Betty is a housewife and has no other income. Bruce has the following income and expenses for the year of assessment 2021/22: (3) Profits from his sole-proprietorship business in Hong Kong (before deduction of any approved charitable donations). HK$600,000 (4) Share of losses from a partnership business in Hong Kong. (HK$200,000) (5) Cash donations to approved charitable organisations in Hong Kong. HK$320,000 (6) Home loan interest. HK$120,000 Other information: (7) Only Bruce elects for personal assessment for the year of assessment 2021/22. (8) Bruce's donations were claimed under his sole-proprietorship business. Required: (a) State the time limit for the election for personal assessment as provided under the IRO. (2 marks) (b) Compute the amount of property tax payable in respect of Betty's share of the residential flat for the year of assessment 2021/22. Ignore provisional property tax. (3 marks) (c) Compute Bruce's net chargeable income under personal assessment for the year of assessment 2021/22. (4 marks)",
