      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 9 (June 2022 Session) Page 9 of 12 Question 3 (9 marks – approximately 16 minutes) Joe purchased a residential flat for his own use in August 2013. 70% of the purchase price was financed by a mortgage loan obtained from a bank in Hong Kong with repayment terms of 25 years, and the balance was made from his past savings. Joe had no history of purchase and sale of property. In March 2020, he sold the residential flat and obtained huge gain. He used the proceeds to purchase a new residential property as his residence. He approached you for advice and wondered whether he was required to pay tax on the disposal. You told Joe that only gain from a transaction constituted an adventure in the nature of trade will be taxable. Required: (a) List out the factors for considering whether a transaction constitutes an adventure in the nature of trade. (6 marks) (b) Based on the above information, analyse whether the gain on disposal of the residential flat by Joe is likely to be subject to profits tax. (3 marks)",
      "full": "Module 9 (June 2022 Session) Page 9 of 12 Question 3 (9 marks – approximately 16 minutes) Joe purchased a residential flat for his own use in August 2013. 70% of the purchase price was financed by a mortgage loan obtained from a bank in Hong Kong with repayment terms of 25 years, and the balance was made from his past savings. Joe had no history of purchase and sale of property. In March 2020, he sold the residential flat and obtained huge gain. He used the proceeds to purchase a new residential property as his residence. He approached you for advice and wondered whether he was required to pay tax on the disposal. You told Joe that only gain from a transaction constituted an adventure in the nature of trade will be taxable. Required: (a) List out the factors for considering whether a transaction constitutes an adventure in the nature of trade. (6 marks) (b) Based on the above information, analyse whether the gain on disposal of the residential flat by Joe is likely to be subject to profits tax. (3 marks)",
      "options": [],
      "sourcePage": 9,
      "sourceMode": "text",
      "ocrUsed": false,
      "answer": "Module 9 (June 2022 Session) Page 7 of 7 * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * * Answer 6(b) The conveyance on sale (\"COS\") Ad valorem stamp duty (\"AVD\") The COS dated 31 October 2019 is executed not in conformity with the earlier ASP because Simon's spouse Judy owned another residential property in Hong Kong on 31 October 2019. As the nominee Judy is a close relative of the purchaser Simon, the COS is ch argeable with AVD at the scale 2 rates based on the half share interest assigned by Simon to Judy by reference to the value of the Property at the date of conveyance. The amount of AVD is as follows: AVD = HK$9,000,000 x 3.75% x ½ = HK$168,750 Special stamp duty (\"SSD\") Simon assigned half share of the Property to his spouse Judy within 36 months after acquisition on 1 September 2019 but is exempt from SSD because the nominee Judy is the purchaser's close relative. Buyer's stamp duty (\"BSD\") The COS is not chargeable with BSD as the nominee Judy is a close relative of the purchaser.\nThe conveyance on sale (\"COS\")\nAd valorem stamp duty (\"AVD\")\nThe COS dated 31 October 2019 is executed not in conformity with the earlier ASP because\nSimon's spouse Judy owned another residential property in Hong Kong on 31 October 2019.\nAs the nominee Judy is a close relative of the purchaser Simon, the COS is chargeable with\nAVD at the scale 2 rates based on the half share interest assigned by Simon to Judy by\nreference to the value of the Property at the date of conveyance. The amount of AVD is as\nfollows:\nAVD = HK$9,000,000 x 3.75% x > = HK$168,750\nSpecial stamp duty (\"SSD\")\nSimon assigned half share of the Property to his spouse Judy within 36 months after\nacquisition on 1 September 2019 but is exempt from SSD because the nominee Judy is the\npurchaser's close relative.\nBuyer's stamp duty (\"BSD\")\nThe COS is not chargeable with BSD as the nominee Judy is a close relative of the\npurchaser.\n* * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *\nModule 9 (June 2022 Session) Page 7 of 7\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
