      "answer": "409,000\nLess: 20% statutory deduction (81,800)\nNet assessable value 327,200\nProperty tax @15% 49,080\nThe agreement for sale and purchase (\"ASP\")\nAD valorem stamp duty (\"AVD\")\nThe ASP executed on 1 September 2019 is chargeable with AVD at the scale two rates\nbecause the purchaser, Simon, is a Hong Kong permanent resident, he did not own any\nresidential property in Hong Kong at the time of purchase of the Property and he purchased\nthe Property on his own behalf. The amount of AVD is computed as follows:\nAVD = HK$10,000,000 x 3.75% = HK$375,000\nSpecial stamp duty (\"SSD\")\nAny residential property resold within 36 months will be subject to SSD. The vendor Peter\npurchased the Property on 1 July 2017 and sold it to Simon on 1 September 2019. Since\nhe held the Property for more than 24 months but less than 36 months, SSD is payable as\nfollows:\nSSD = HK$10,000,000 x 10% = HK$1,000,000\nBuyer's stamp duty (\"BSD\")\nBSD is payable where the purchaser of the property is not a Hong Kong permanent resident\nor a close relative of the vendor. The ASP is not chargeable with BSD because the\npurchaser Simon is a Hong Kong permanent resident.\nModule 9 (June 2022 Session) Page 6 of 7",
