      "full": "Question 1 (26 marks — approximately 47 minutes)\nBB Limited (\"the Company\") is incorporated and carries on trading of plastic products in Hong\nKong. It commenced its trading business on 1 November 2017 and prepared its first set of\naccounts to 31 January 2019. All its trading profits are sourced in Hong Kong. Mr and Mrs\nLee are the directors of the Company. In respect of the period from 1 November 2017 to 31\nJanuary 2019, the Company has the following results:\nHK$ HK$\nGross trading profit 12,258,000\nInterest income (Note 1) 75,000\nRental income (Note 2) 150,000\n12,483,000\nLess: Auditor's fees 80,000\nDirectors’ remuneration (Note 3) 1,200,000\nSalaries and allowances 6,500,000\nContributions to MPF schemes (Note 4) 1,295,000\nAdvertising 300,000\nOffice rent (Note 5) 425,000\nLegal fees (Note 6) 29,000\nMotor vehicles expenses (Note 7) 572,000\nDonations (Note 8) 260,000\nDepreciation (Note 9) 454,000\nSundry expenses (Note 10) 760,000 (11,875,000)\nNet profit 608,000\nNotes:\n(1) Interest from overseas customers on overdue accounts 60,000\nInterest on loan to Mr Lee in Hong Kong 15,000\n75,000\n(2) The property is situated in Macau. The Company let out the property starting from\n1 November 2017 at a monthly rent of HK$10,000.\n(3) MrlLee 750,000\nMrs Lee 450,000\n1,200,000\nModule 9 (June 2021 Session) Page 4 of 11\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
