      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 9 (June 2021 Session) Page 11 of 11 Required: (a) Compute the net assessable value of John's Property A under property tax for the year of assessment 2018/19. (3 marks) (b) Compute John's reduced total income under personal assessment for the year of assessment 2018/19. (6 marks) Question 6 (9 marks – approximately 16 minutes) Red Limited owns 75% of the issued shares in Blue Limited, which in turns owns 95% of the issued shares in Yellow Limited. Red Limited, Blue Limited and Yellow Limited are al l incorporated in Hong Kong. In July 2016, Red Limited borrowed HK$8 million from Blue Limited. As Red Limited is unable to repay the loan, it conveyed to Blue Limited its office property in the settlement of the loan on 10 July 2018. The office property is a non-residential property and Red Limited purchased it on 1 February 2016. The market value of the office property on 10 July 2018 is HK$7 million. As such, Blue Limited waived the balance of the outstanding loan of HK$1 million. On 1 August 2018, Blue Limited leased the office property to Yellow Limited at a fair market rent of HK$40,000 per month for a term of 4 years. Blue Limited and Yellow Limited executed the lease agreement on 31 July 2018. Required: Analyse, with reference to the relevant provisions under the Stamp Duty Ordinance, (a) whether ad valorem duty, special stamp duty and buyer's stamp duty are payable on the conveyance of the office property; and (6 marks) (b) whether ad valorem duty is payable on the lease agreement. (3 marks) If so, compute the respective amounts payable. * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
