      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (June 2021 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (Total: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (22 marks – approximately 40 minutes) ABC Limited is an established operator of residential care homes for the elderly in Hong Kong. The operations of ABC Limited are subject to various laws and regulations which mainly relate to, among others, the requirements for licensing, operation, management, and supervision of care and attention homes, and registration of health workers in Hong Kong. ABC operations have to comply with certain other laws and regulations, such as building safety, fire safety, labour, physiotherapists, registered nurses, dealing in and storage of pharmaceutical products, and dangerous drugs in order to renew its license to operate. During the audit for the year ended 31 December 2020, the auditors found that there were instances where ABC Limited failed to comply with certain applicable laws and regulations in Hong Kong. Required: (a) The entire board of directors is elected to represent the company and its shareholders. List the directors' responsibilities in general. (8 marks) (b) Explain how this non-compliance with laws and regulations can affect the financial statements of ABC Limited. (2 marks) (c) List the audit procedures when non-compliance with laws and regulations is identified or suspected. (5 marks) (d) Control environment has been considered the most important component of internal control setting of an organisation. List the SEVEN elements of the control environment that auditors have to understand for the evaluation of the internal control of ABC Limited. (7 marks)",
      "full": "Module 8 (June 2021 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (Total: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (22 marks – approximately 40 minutes) ABC Limited is an established operator of residential care homes for the elderly in Hong Kong. The operations of ABC Limited are subject to various laws and regulations which mainly relate to, among others, the requirements for licensing, operation, management, and supervision of care and attention homes, and registration of health workers in Hong Kong. ABC operations have to comply with certain other laws and regulations, such as building safety, fire safety, labour, physiotherapists, registered nurses, dealing in and storage of pharmaceutical products, and dangerous drugs in order to renew its license to operate. During the audit for the year ended 31 December 2020, the auditors found that there were instances where ABC Limited failed to comply with certain applicable laws and regulations in Hong Kong. Required: (a) The entire board of directors is elected to represent the company and its shareholders. List the directors' responsibilities in general. (8 marks) (b) Explain how this non-compliance with laws and regulations can affect the financial statements of ABC Limited. (2 marks) (c) List the audit procedures when non-compliance with laws and regulations is identified or suspected. (5 marks) (d) Control environment has been considered the most important component of internal control setting of an organisation. List the SEVEN elements of the control environment that auditors have to understand for the evaluation of the internal control of ABC Limited. (7 marks)",
