      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/M1-10LP+Past%20paper/1-10%20Past%20paper/m8/Module%208%20Jun%202021%20Question.pdf#question-q-p002-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (June 2021 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 2 (25 marks – approximately 45 minutes) On 2 February 2021, Jenny Wong, an audit partner of a reputable audit firm, ADE & Co, was approached by the managing director, Tom Wong, who is also the major shareholder of a new audit client, HQ Mask Limited (\"HML\"), to discuss the audit engagement. HML was incorporated in January 2020. HML runs a small business with one factory in Hong Kong for masks manufacturing and the wholesaling of masks. HML ordered mask production machines and equipment from Mainland China in February 2020. Due to the high demand of mask production line machines during that period, the purchase price was exceptionally high. However, Tom Wong had confidence in the sales of Hong Kong manufactured masks in Hong Kong, thus HML bought the mask production line machines and the packing machines. The arrival of the machines was in early April 2020. Unluckily, the quality of the machines was poor. All the machines did not function properly. Tom Wong has a friend who is an engineer, Jack Li, who spent one month adjusting the machinery of the mask production line. After this adjustment, the production line worked as expected. No machine has been disposed of and all have been recorded in the accounting system. The company adopted a cost model to account for the machineries. The company started production in May 2020. HML is facing keen competition and there are few purchase orders from customers due to their price, which is higher than those of masks produced from Mainland China due to the high production cost. HML is now running at a loss. HML leased from a landlord an industrial property as its factory for a five-year term which was effective from 1 January 2020. HML kept a large amount of inventory, face masks, which have an expiry period of three years. Required: (a) List the terms of the audit engagement that shall be recorded in an audit engagement letter. (4 marks) (b) In the case of audit engagements, it is required by the HKICPA's Code of Ethics that members of audit teams, firms, and network firms shall be independent of audit clients. Describe the conceptual framework approach required by the HKICPA's Code of Ethics . (3 marks) (c) Determine the inherent risk of misstatement of the lease liability with explanation. (3 marks)",
      "full": "Module 8 (June 2021 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 2 (25 marks – approximately 45 minutes) On 2 February 2021, Jenny Wong, an audit partner of a reputable audit firm, ADE & Co, was approached by the managing director, Tom Wong, who is also the major shareholder of a new audit client, HQ Mask Limited (\"HML\"), to discuss the audit engagement. HML was incorporated in January 2020. HML runs a small business with one factory in Hong Kong for masks manufacturing and the wholesaling of masks. HML ordered mask production machines and equipment from Mainland China in February 2020. Due to the high demand of mask production line machines during that period, the purchase price was exceptionally high. However, Tom Wong had confidence in the sales of Hong Kong manufactured masks in Hong Kong, thus HML bought the mask production line machines and the packing machines. The arrival of the machines was in early April 2020. Unluckily, the quality of the machines was poor. All the machines did not function properly. Tom Wong has a friend who is an engineer, Jack Li, who spent one month adjusting the machinery of the mask production line. After this adjustment, the production line worked as expected. No machine has been disposed of and all have been recorded in the accounting system. The company adopted a cost model to account for the machineries. The company started production in May 2020. HML is facing keen competition and there are few purchase orders from customers due to their price, which is higher than those of masks produced from Mainland China due to the high production cost. HML is now running at a loss. HML leased from a landlord an industrial property as its factory for a five-year term which was effective from 1 January 2020. HML kept a large amount of inventory, face masks, which have an expiry period of three years. Required: (a) List the terms of the audit engagement that shall be recorded in an audit engagement letter. (4 marks) (b) In the case of audit engagements, it is required by the HKICPA's Code of Ethics that members of audit teams, firms, and network firms shall be independent of audit clients. Describe the conceptual framework approach required by the HKICPA's Code of Ethics . (3 marks) (c) Determine the inherent risk of misstatement of the lease liability with explanation. (3 marks)",
