      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (June 2021 Session) Page 3 of 4 (d) Determine the audit approach for the audit of lease liability of HML with explanation. (3 marks) (e) Determine the inherent risk of misstatement of the machineries included in property, plant, and equipment with explanation. (3 marks) (f) Determine the audit approach for the audit of machineries of HML with explanation. (3 marks) (g) Determine the business risk and inherent risk of misstatement of the inventory with explanation. (6 marks) Question 3 (18 marks – approximately 32 minutes) Local Holdings Limited (\"LHL\") is a Hong Kong based trading company that has many overseas subsidiaries. Trading Abroad Limited (\"TAL\"), being a 100% owned subsidiary of LHL, is located in Australia and is audited by a local audit firm. LHL is audited by ABC & Co, which is the principal auditor of the group located in Hong Kong. TAL is a significant component of the group and the accounts receivable of TAL is considered a significant asset of the group. ABC & Co decided to give detailed audit procedures in the group audit instructions document for the local auditor of TAL to follow. Required: (a) Explain the objectives of ABC & Co in relation to the audit of a group. (6 marks) (b) In addition to classification and presentation, list and explain FOUR other assertions for auditing accounts receivable. (4 marks) (c) Determine the possible audit procedures for the accounts receivable of TAL. (8 marks)",
