      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (June 2021 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 4 (15 marks – approximately 27 minutes) You are the audit manager of PQY & Co, the external auditor of Luxury Jewellery Limited (\"LJL\") for the year ended 31 December 2020. LJL is a manufacturer and wholesaler of precious jewellery. The accounts receivable is a significant account balance in the company's statement of financial position. The management does not allow the audit team to request external confirmation of several accounts receivable because there are lawsuit cases between LJL and its customers. You considered that the possible effects on the financial statements of undetected misstatements are not immaterial. Required: (a) List the contents to be included in the auditor's responsibilities section in the auditor's report. (8 marks) (b) Management does not allow the audit team to request external confirmation of several accounts receivable. List potential types of modified audit opinions and the nature of matter giving rise to the modifications. (4 marks) (c) For this part only: assume the effect of misstatements of accounts receivable on the financial statements is material but not pervasive and there are no other major misstatements found in the audit of the financial statements. State the type of audit opinion and the essential elements that would be included in the basis for opinion section. (3 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
