      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (June 2024 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 4 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) Intelligent Limited (\"IL\") is engaged in the wholesale of superior dried seafood. The major customers of IL are dried seafood retail shops and Chinese food restaurants. In 2022, many restaurants closed due to the pandemic. The amount of accounts receivable written off is significant and the directors expect IL will have more accounts receivable to be written off. The accounts receivable amount after impairment loss still represents 30% of the current assets in the statement of financial position. The auditor has gathered sufficient appropriate audit evidence and drawn the conclusion that the measurement of expected credit loss is reasonable. The auditor has suggested issuing an auditor ' s report with the Key Audit Matters section for explaining why the impairment assessment of accounts receivable is a key audit matter and how it is addressed in the audit. Required: (a) Define Key Audit Matters. (2 marks) (b) Explain the purpose of including the Key Audit Matters section in the auditor's report. (4 marks) (c) Analyse the inherent risk of accounts receivable of IL. (3 marks) (d) Assume that the expected credit loss is considered by the auditor as materially underestimated in the financial statements, describe potential types of auditor's opinion and explain the nature of the matter giving rise to each potential types of auditor's opinion. (4 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
