      "sourceMatch": "Module 8 (December 2021 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. ",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/M1-10LP+Past%20paper/1-10%20Past%20paper/m8/Module%208%20Question%20Dec%202021.pdf#question-q-p001-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (December 2021 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (27 marks – approximately 49 minutes) JC Limited is a private company engaged in the operation of a small high end frozen, dry, and preserve food store, which is owned and run by two directors with experience in this industry. The store provides high end food. Most customers buy expensive frozen, dry, and preserve food in this store. The average spending per customer is HK$5,000. On 2 January 2021, May Chan, a partner of an audit firm, ABC & Co, was approached by a director of JC Limited, Mike Wong to replace the outgoing auditor, PQJ & Co. PQJ & Co retired in October 2020 after submitting the auditor's report for JC Limited's financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2019. JC Limited kept a large amount of inventory including high end frozen, dry and preserve food. The directors asked ABC & Co to commence the audit immediately because audited financial statements must be submitted to the bank by 20 January 2021 for the renewal of one of the bank loans. JC Limited will be unable to continue its operation if the renewal of the bank loan is unsuccessful. In order to motivate the audit team to work more efficiently to meet the tight deadline, the directors would like to provide a coupon with a HK$5,000 face value to each of the audit team members for redemption of food if JC Limited succeeded in renewal of the bank loan. Due to the urgency of submitting the financial statements to the bank, the directors of JC Limited asked the auditors not to carry out the inventory count, nor to send confirmation to the suppliers. The directors said that the year-end day had passed and therefore it was impractical to carry out the inventory count. To substitute, the directors will provide a written representation to ABC & Co as an evidence for their inventory amount as at the year-end date. Mike Wong advised that the suppliers' monthly statements would be available for inspection. Therefore, it is not necessary to send the confirmation to the suppliers to confirm the year-end accounts payable balances since it would have a very long turnaround time. The directors believe that the major objective of an audit is to enhance the survival of the client which is most beneficial to the shareholders. Required: (a) Audit is one type of assurance engagement. Describe the objective of an assurance engagement. (3 marks) (b) Explain whether the auditor should or should not accept the proposed coupon for food redemption arrangement, taking into consideration the Code of Ethics for Professional Accountants and the potential threat to the independence of the CPA firm. (5 marks) (c) Determine the possible audit procedures for the bank loans and interest expense of JC Limited. (7 marks)",
      "full": "Module 8 (December 2021 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (27 marks – approximately 49 minutes) JC Limited is a private company engaged in the operation of a small high end frozen, dry, and preserve food store, which is owned and run by two directors with experience in this industry. The store provides high end food. Most customers buy expensive frozen, dry, and preserve food in this store. The average spending per customer is HK$5,000. On 2 January 2021, May Chan, a partner of an audit firm, ABC & Co, was approached by a director of JC Limited, Mike Wong to replace the outgoing auditor, PQJ & Co. PQJ & Co retired in October 2020 after submitting the auditor's report for JC Limited's financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2019. JC Limited kept a large amount of inventory including high end frozen, dry and preserve food. The directors asked ABC & Co to commence the audit immediately because audited financial statements must be submitted to the bank by 20 January 2021 for the renewal of one of the bank loans. JC Limited will be unable to continue its operation if the renewal of the bank loan is unsuccessful. In order to motivate the audit team to work more efficiently to meet the tight deadline, the directors would like to provide a coupon with a HK$5,000 face value to each of the audit team members for redemption of food if JC Limited succeeded in renewal of the bank loan. Due to the urgency of submitting the financial statements to the bank, the directors of JC Limited asked the auditors not to carry out the inventory count, nor to send confirmation to the suppliers. The directors said that the year-end day had passed and therefore it was impractical to carry out the inventory count. To substitute, the directors will provide a written representation to ABC & Co as an evidence for their inventory amount as at the year-end date. Mike Wong advised that the suppliers' monthly statements would be available for inspection. Therefore, it is not necessary to send the confirmation to the suppliers to confirm the year-end accounts payable balances since it would have a very long turnaround time. The directors believe that the major objective of an audit is to enhance the survival of the client which is most beneficial to the shareholders. Required: (a) Audit is one type of assurance engagement. Describe the objective of an assurance engagement. (3 marks) (b) Explain whether the auditor should or should not accept the proposed coupon for food redemption arrangement, taking into consideration the Code of Ethics for Professional Accountants and the potential threat to the independence of the CPA firm. (5 marks) (c) Determine the possible audit procedures for the bank loans and interest expense of JC Limited. (7 marks)",
