      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (December 2021 Session) Page 3 of 4 Question 3 (25 marks – approximately 45 minutes) The management of an entity has the responsibility to prepare the financial statements and the financial statements are required to be audited by an independent auditor to ensure fair presentation of financial statements in conformity with the generally accepted accounting principles (\"GAAP\"). Currently, many entities' management believe that a \" good \" IT system will enable the entity to produce meaningful and accurate financial data as the basis for the financial statements. Management may also request auditors to perform systems audit during the process of audit ing financial statements. A well-planned audit will ensure that the auditor obtains sufficient and appropriate audit evidence for those areas of the financial statements which are most at risk of material misstatement. As part of the planning phase, auditors have to carry out the preliminary risk assessment procedures and devise risk responses. Required: (a) Describe the management's responsibilities throughout the audit process. (3 marks) (b) List five attributes of a \" good \" IT system that improves the meaningfulness and accuracy of financial data . (5 marks) (c) Describe systems audit and list two reasons for conducting systems audit. (5 marks) (d) Describe the risk assessment procedures to be performed by auditors for understanding of the entity's information system and communication relevant to the preparation of the financial statements. (12 marks)",
