      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (December 2021 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 4 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) You are the senior in charge working for the audit of the financial statements of Happy Limited for the year ended 31 December 2020. Happy Limited runs a retail business of health products. Due to economic downturn in 2019 and 2020, Happy Limited kept on making losses. The directors believe that Happy Limited can survive in the following six months after the year ended 31 December 2020 even though the revenue of Happy Limited was significantly reduced due to the downward trend of the economy. The directors are not certain about the continuing viability of their business after six months. The directors agreed to include a statement highlighting the doubt over Happy Limited's ability to continue as a going concern due to significant uncertainty of the continuing viability of their business. Required: (a) Describe the objectives of performing audit work on going concern assumption. (2 marks) (b) Explain how to evaluate the appropriateness of the management's assessment of the entity's ability to continue as a going concern. (4 marks) (c) Describe the audit report if the auditor considered that there is no disagreement as to the basis of preparation or disclosure regarding the going concern issue and the financial statements are not materially misstated. (7 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
