      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (June 2025 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 MARKS) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (17 marks – approximately 30 minutes) You are an audit manager working for one of the sizable audit firms in Hong Kong. You have been approached by your friend, Andy, who is looking for an audit firm to carry out the first financial statement audit for his company, Asia Pacific Limited (\"APL\"), in accordance with the Hong Kong Companies Ordinance. APL is a newly incorporated private company in Hong Kong, engaging in the food and beverage business. It is scheduled to hold its first annual general meeting within nine months after its first year-end date. Andy has no idea about how to appoint the first auditor of APL and the overall objectives of the auditor in conducting a financial statement audit. He would also like to know the rights of the auditor appointed to carry out a financial statement audit in Hong Kong. Required: (a) Explain to Andy in detail who could appoint the first auditor of APL. (6 marks) (b) Describe the overall objectives of the auditor in conducting a financial statement audit. (5 marks) (c) Describe FOUR key rights of the auditor in carrying out a financial statement audit in Hong Kong. (4 marks) (d) Apart from the Hong Kong Companies Ordinance, list TWO other most important ordinances in Hong Kong that governing the auditor in Hong Kong. (2 marks)",
