      "prompt": "Module 8 (June 2025 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 4 (25 marks – approximately 46 minutes) You are the auditor of Sunshine Limited (\"SL\"), a private manufacturing company of small household appliances, for the year ended 31 December 2024. SL is a Hong Kong company but has most of its factories and warehouses located in different provinces in China. In performing subsequent event review, you have learned from SL's management that their factory and warehouse in Henan Province of China were damaged by flooding and landslides caused by heavy rainfall in late January and early February 2025. As a result, SL has halted its production in Hebei Province since the deadly floods and landslides. You are now in the process of finalizing your audit opinion on SL's financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2024. Required: (a) Explain the objectives of carrying out review of events occurring between the date of the financial statements and the date of the auditor's report. (4 marks) (b) Describe FOUR possible audit procedures in carrying out subsequent event review. (6 marks) (c) Contrast an emphasis of matter paragraph with an other matter paragraph. (4 marks) (d) Explain the type of auditors' opinion you will issue, and the additional information you will include in the auditor's report, in respect of the following independent outcomes of your assessment of the impact of destroyed factory and warehouse on SL and the responses of SL's management. (i) Management has agreed to disclose the loss caused by the flooding and landslides in the financial statements and you have considered the disclosure by management is appropriate. (5 marks) (ii) Management is not willing to provide adequate information regarding the loss caused by the flooding and landslides and you also find that alternative audit procedures performed do not provide adequate and appropriate evidence regarding the loss caused by the flooding and landslides. (6 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
      "full": "Module 8 (June 2025 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 4 (25 marks – approximately 46 minutes) You are the auditor of Sunshine Limited (\"SL\"), a private manufacturing company of small household appliances, for the year ended 31 December 2024. SL is a Hong Kong company but has most of its factories and warehouses located in different provinces in China. In performing subsequent event review, you have learned from SL's management that their factory and warehouse in Henan Province of China were damaged by flooding and landslides caused by heavy rainfall in late January and early February 2025. As a result, SL has halted its production in Hebei Province since the deadly floods and landslides. You are now in the process of finalizing your audit opinion on SL's financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2024. Required: (a) Explain the objectives of carrying out review of events occurring between the date of the financial statements and the date of the auditor's report. (4 marks) (b) Describe FOUR possible audit procedures in carrying out subsequent event review. (6 marks) (c) Contrast an emphasis of matter paragraph with an other matter paragraph. (4 marks) (d) Explain the type of auditors' opinion you will issue, and the additional information you will include in the auditor's report, in respect of the following independent outcomes of your assessment of the impact of destroyed factory and warehouse on SL and the responses of SL's management. (i) Management has agreed to disclose the loss caused by the flooding and landslides in the financial statements and you have considered the disclosure by management is appropriate. (5 marks) (ii) Management is not willing to provide adequate information regarding the loss caused by the flooding and landslides and you also find that alternative audit procedures performed do not provide adequate and appropriate evidence regarding the loss caused by the flooding and landslides. (6 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
