      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (December 2020 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (Total: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (27 marks – approximately 49 minutes) In April 2020, Kitty Cheung, a partner of a five-partners firm, CCA & Co, was approached by New Sun Limited (\"NSL\") to replace its previous auditor, ABC & Co. ABC & Co retired in February 2020 after submitting the auditor's report for NSL's financial statements for the year ended 30 June 2019, wherein ABC & Co expressed an unqualified opinion. The major reason of NSL for changing the auditor is to reduce the audit fee. Kitty Cheung believes that she can complete the audit and charge NSL for an audit fee 20% lower than ABC & Co by performing the audit in an cost-effective way. Kitty Cheung emphasised that cost-effective audits can be achieved by having a proper audit strategy and adequate planning as well as effective two-way communication with those charged with governance. During the auditing planning process, the auditor has the responsibility to communicate with those charged with governance. Required: (a) List the matters that should be considered by CCA & Co for the acceptance of a new client. (5 marks) (b) List the procedures in order to assess whether the preconditions for an audit engagement are present. (5 marks) (c) List the benefits of audit planning. (5 marks) (d) List the important elements of the audit planning process. (5 marks) (e) List the matters to be communicated to those charged with governance regarding the planned scope and timing of the audit. (7 marks)",
