      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (December 2020 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 2 (15 marks – approximately 27 minutes) The role of the auditor is to enhance the creditability of the financial statements. The general public expects the auditors to detect most intentional misstatements in the financial statements that arise from fraud. The auditor is concerned with fraud that causes a material misstatement in the financial statements. The two types of intentional misstatements are relevant to the auditor: (a) misstatement resulting from fraudulent financial reporting and (b) misstatement resulting from misappropriation of assets. Required: (a) Explain the overall objectives of the independent auditor in conducting an audit of financial statements. (4 marks) (b) Explain fraudulent financial reporting. (3 marks) (c) List THREE fraud risk factors for fraudulent financial reporting. (3 marks) (d) List FIVE fraud risk factors for misappropriation of assets. (5 marks)",
