      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 8 (December 2020 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 4 (23 marks – approximately 41 minutes) The CPA firm, BC & Co is the external auditor of Clear Mind Limited (\"CML\"), which is a company that carries out a trading business. CML purchases goods from mainland China and sells them to overseas customers. All the sales are credit sales. You are the manager in charge of the audit of the financial statements of CML, and have been working on this audit engagement for a few years. CML has effective internal control over the sales cycle and trade receivables. James Chow is assigned as your assistant. From an in-house auditing training programme, James learnt that business risk and audit risk were the two important factors in determining the scope of audit works to be performed by auditors in conducting audits of financial statements. You decided to assign James to audit the sales and trade receivables. You have assessed the risk of material misstatement of trade receivables at the valuation assertion level as low, with an expectation that the relevant internal controls operate effectively throughout the year. Required: (a) State the audit risk model and explain each of the components. (6 marks) (b) List the FIVE components of internal control. (5 marks) (c) Explain to James the business risk and inherent risk of the trade receivables of CML. (4 marks) (d) List the possible substantive audit procedures to audit sales revenue. (8 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
