      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 7 (December 2020 Session) Page 3 of 4 Question 3 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) The Relaxing Recreation Club (\"RRC\") has two clubhouses. The main clubhouse is situated in Sai Kung on four and half acres of luxuriant grassland facing a picturesque and paradisiac beach and the second clubhouse is just 15 minutes' drive from the central business district and the best location on Hong Kong Island for water sports. RRC is considering a four-year renovation project to improve its facilities and equipment. You are the Chief Financial Officer of RRC and are responsible for estimating the discount rate, which is the cost of capital, used for capital budgeting appraisal. The capital structure of RRC with relevant market information is shown as below: Common stock: 50 million shares outstanding of HK$5 par selling for HK$12 per share. The stock has a beta coefficient of 1.6. Preferred stock: 8 million shares selling for HK$94 per share, with dividend rate of 6% and face value of HK$100. Debt: Five years ago, RRC issued 7 million 15-year zero coupon bonds (assume compound semi-annually for bond price computation as compared with normal semi-annual coupon bonds) with par value of HK$1,000 that are still outstanding now. The bonds are currently selling for HK$620. Market: The current Exchange Fund Bills yield 3% and the expected return on the market is 12%. RRC is in the 20% corporate tax bracket. The detailed information of the initial cash outflow and cash inflows of the two mutually exclusive four-year renovation projects for evaluation is listed as below: Year Project A Project B HK$ HK$ 0 -1,280,000 -738,000 1 289,000 138,000 2 336,000 258,000 3 570,800 301,000 4 823,400 598,000 Required: (a) Compute the cost of equity (R E ), cost of preferred stock (R P ) and pre-tax cost of debt (R D ) for RRC. (6 marks) (b) Assuming that RRC is going to maintain the current capital structure, compute the weighted average cost of capital (\"WACC\") for project evaluation. (3 marks) (c) Compute the net present value (\"NPV\") for Project A and Project B and determine which project RRC should choose with brief explanation. (5 marks)",
      "full": "Module 7 (December 2020 Session) Page 3 of 4 Question 3 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) The Relaxing Recreation Club (\"RRC\") has two clubhouses. The main clubhouse is situated in Sai Kung on four and half acres of luxuriant grassland facing a picturesque and paradisiac beach and the second clubhouse is just 15 minutes' drive from the central business district and the best location on Hong Kong Island for water sports. RRC is considering a four-year renovation project to improve its facilities and equipment. You are the Chief Financial Officer of RRC and are responsible for estimating the discount rate, which is the cost of capital, used for capital budgeting appraisal. The capital structure of RRC with relevant market information is shown as below: Common stock: 50 million shares outstanding of HK$5 par selling for HK$12 per share. The stock has a beta coefficient of 1.6. Preferred stock: 8 million shares selling for HK$94 per share, with dividend rate of 6% and face value of HK$100. Debt: Five years ago, RRC issued 7 million 15-year zero coupon bonds (assume compound semi-annually for bond price computation as compared with normal semi-annual coupon bonds) with par value of HK$1,000 that are still outstanding now. The bonds are currently selling for HK$620. Market: The current Exchange Fund Bills yield 3% and the expected return on the market is 12%. RRC is in the 20% corporate tax bracket. The detailed information of the initial cash outflow and cash inflows of the two mutually exclusive four-year renovation projects for evaluation is listed as below: Year Project A Project B HK$ HK$ 0 -1,280,000 -738,000 1 289,000 138,000 2 336,000 258,000 3 570,800 301,000 4 823,400 598,000 Required: (a) Compute the cost of equity (R E ), cost of preferred stock (R P ) and pre-tax cost of debt (R D ) for RRC. (6 marks) (b) Assuming that RRC is going to maintain the current capital structure, compute the weighted average cost of capital (\"WACC\") for project evaluation. (3 marks) (c) Compute the net present value (\"NPV\") for Project A and Project B and determine which project RRC should choose with brief explanation. (5 marks)",
