      "answer": "Module 7 (December 2020 Session) Page 7 of 7 Answer 4(c) There are four basic types of responsibility centres: cost centres, revenue centres, profit centres and investment centres. These centres indicate the degree of responsibility the manager has for performance and accountability. Managers of cost centres are evaluated on their ability to control costs and expenses through budgeting and budgetary control. Managers of revenue centres are evaluated by meeting revenue forecasts while controlling related selling costs. Managers of profit centres are accountable for both revenue and cost, hence are judged on the level of profitability of their centres. Lastly, managers of investment centres are evaluated on both the profitability of the centres and the rate of return earned on the funds invested. The Badminton Rackets segment belongs to profit centre because it incurs costs and expenses, and generates revenue. * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
