      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 6 (December 2020 Session) Page 2 of 7 On 1 October 2018, PYL also acquired 30% of the share capital of Lotus Limited (\"LOL\") for HK$1.8 million cash when the share capital and retained earnings of LOL were HK$4.5 million and HK$850,000, respectively. PYL has no control or joint control over LOL, but has significant influence over its financial and operating policy decisions. At 1 October 2018, all the identifiable assets and liabilities of LOL were recorded at fair value, except for a plant which had a carrying amount of HK$600,000 but was measured at HK$750,000 in fair value. This plant was assessed to have a remaining 10-year life. Additional information: (i) PYL measures the non-controlling interests in CUL at fair value of HK$1.5 million. (ii) All acquisition valuation adjustments are made on consolidation. (iii) All of the companies adopt straight-line depreciation policy on their property, plant and equipment. (iv) During the current year, CUL sold inventory to PYL for HK$260,000. The cost of this inventory was HK$200,000. By the end of the current year, PYL has only resold 60% of these items to external parties at a profit of HK$85,000. (v) No additional shares have been issued by CUL and LOL since 1 October 2018. (vi) For the year ended 30 September 2019, LOL recorded a net profit of HK$165,400. (vii) PYL had no subsidiaries and associates and recorded no goodwill as of 30 September 2018. Required: (a) Prepare the consolidated statement of profit or loss and other comprehensive income for PYL Group for the year ended 30 September 2019 in accordance with HKFRS 10 Consolidated Financial Statements and HKAS 28 Investment in Associates and Joint Ventures . Ignore the effect of deferred taxation. (12 marks) (b) Compute the balances of the following accounts in the consolidated statement of financial position of PYL Group as of 30 September 2019: (1) Investment in CUL. (2) Investment in LOL. (3) Goodwill. (4) Non-controlling interests. (8 marks) (c) Explain how non-controlling interests are measured and presented according to HKFRS 3 Business Combinations . (5 marks)\nOn 1 October 2018, PYL also acquired 30% of the share capital of Lotus Limited (\"LOL\") for",
