      "prompt": "(20 marks — approximately 36 minutes)\nSunlight Cosmetics Limited (\"SUL\") is a toy manufacturer. SUL manufactures toys in its own\nplants and distributes the finished products through its own networks. The unadjusted trial\nbalance for SUL at 31 March 2019 is as follows:\nDR CR\nHK$'000 HK$'000\nSales - 155,400\nCosts of goods manufactured in the year to 31 March 2019 104,500 -\n(excluding depreciation)\nDistribution costs 10,560 -\nAdministrative expenses 23,120 -\nOther expenses 3,400 -\nInterest received - 11,700\n8% bank loan interest paid 1,120 -\nLand and buildings (including land HK$60 million) 80,800 -\nPlant and equipment 15,220 -\nAccumulated depreciation as at 31 March 2018\nBuildings - 7,560\nPlant and equipment - 3,170\nInventories as at 31 March 2018 6,352 -\nTrade receivables 24,830 -\nBank and cash 23,190 -\nOrdinary shares, fully paid - 33,930\n7% redeemable preference shares - 2,600\nRevaluation surplus - 4,635\nRetained earnings, 31 March 2018 - 38,637\nOrdinary dividends paid 2,500 -\nPreference dividends paid 182 -\n8% bank loan - 28,000\nTrade payables - 10,142\n295,774 295,774\nAdditional information:\nThe supplier sued the company for a claim of HK$10 million. According to the legal\nopinion, it is highly likely that the company will lose the case and be required to pay\nthe claimed amount. The case will be concluded within the next accounting period.\ndividends are paid on 31 March each year.\n(ii) Buildings are depreciated on a straight-line basis at a rate of 5% per annum.\nDepreciation on buildings is classified as administrative expenses.\nModule 6 (December 2020 Session) Page 3 of 7\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
      "full": "Question 2 (20 marks — approximately 36 minutes)\nSunlight Cosmetics Limited (\"SUL\") is a toy manufacturer. SUL manufactures toys in its own\nplants and distributes the finished products through its own networks. The unadjusted trial\nbalance for SUL at 31 March 2019 is as follows:\nDR CR\nHK$'000 HK$'000\nSales - 155,400\nCosts of goods manufactured in the year to 31 March 2019 104,500 -\n(excluding depreciation)\nDistribution costs 10,560 -\nAdministrative expenses 23,120 -\nOther expenses 3,400 -\nInterest received - 11,700\n8% bank loan interest paid 1,120 -\nLand and buildings (including land HK$60 million) 80,800 -\nPlant and equipment 15,220 -\nAccumulated depreciation as at 31 March 2018\nBuildings - 7,560\nPlant and equipment - 3,170\nInventories as at 31 March 2018 6,352 -\nTrade receivables 24,830 -\nBank and cash 23,190 -\nOrdinary shares, fully paid - 33,930\n7% redeemable preference shares - 2,600\nRevaluation surplus - 4,635\nRetained earnings, 31 March 2018 - 38,637\nOrdinary dividends paid 2,500 -\nPreference dividends paid 182 -\n8% bank loan - 28,000\nTrade payables - 10,142\n295,774 295,774\nAdditional information:\n(i) On 31 March 2019, the company is being sued by a supplier for breach of contract.\nThe supplier sued the company for a claim of HK$10 million. According to the legal\nopinion, it is highly likely that the company will lose the case and be required to pay\nthe claimed amount. The case will be concluded within the next accounting period.\n(i) The preference shares will be redeemed for HK$2,600,000 in 2022. Preference\ndividends are paid on 31 March each year.\n(ii) Buildings are depreciated on a straight-line basis at a rate of 5% per annum.\nDepreciation on buildings is classified as administrative expenses.\nModule 6 (December 2020 Session) Page 3 of 7\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
