      "number": "3",
      "prompt": "(10 marks — approximately 18 minutes)\nBob Limited (\"BOL\") is a toy manufacturer and retailer operating in Hong Kong. During the\nreporting period ended 31 December 2019, the following events occurred.\nMachinery:\nBOL decided to revise the useful life and residual value of its machinery due to wear and tear.\nThe machinery was purchased on 1 January 2015 at a cost of HK$2,600,000. At the time of\nacquisition, the estimated useful life of the machinery was 10 years and the residual value was\nHK$500,000. On 31 December 2018, the estimated useful life was revised from 10 years to\n8 years and residual value became HK$300,000. The machinery is depreciated on a straight-\nline basis.\nInventory:\nBOL changed its inventory valuation method from FIFO to weighted average cost for the\npurpose of providing more relevant and comparable information to financial statement users.\nSuch change has resulted in the following revision of financial figures:\nrT] For the period ending 31 December 2018 |For all periods prior to 2018\nCost of Goods Sold HK$600,000 increase HK$2,800,000 increase\nHK$600,000 decrease | HK$2,800,000 decrease\nThe following additional information is also available to BOL:\n° Retained earnings at 31 December 2017 was HK$15,700,000.\n. Profit (after taxes) for the year ended 31 December 2018 and 31 December 2019 was\nHK$1,430,000 and HK$1,690,000, respectively.\n. The income tax rate is 16.5%.\n. No dividends have been declared or paid during the current period.\n. Assume all amounts are material.\nRequired:\nIn accordance with HKAS 8 Accounting Policies, Changes in Accounting Estimates and\nErrors, ignoring deferred tax,\nthe financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2019. Support your\nanswers with calculations.\n(4 marks)\nfinancial statements for the year ended 31 December 2019. Prepare an extract of\nthe statement of changes in equity for the year ended 31 December 2019 to\ndemonstrate the inventory effects.\n(6 marks)\nModule 6 (December 2020 Session) Page 5 of 7\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
      "full": "Question 3 (10 marks — approximately 18 minutes)\nBob Limited (\"BOL\") is a toy manufacturer and retailer operating in Hong Kong. During the\nreporting period ended 31 December 2019, the following events occurred.\nMachinery:\nBOL decided to revise the useful life and residual value of its machinery due to wear and tear.\nThe machinery was purchased on 1 January 2015 at a cost of HK$2,600,000. At the time of\nacquisition, the estimated useful life of the machinery was 10 years and the residual value was\nHK$500,000. On 31 December 2018, the estimated useful life was revised from 10 years to\n8 years and residual value became HK$300,000. The machinery is depreciated on a straight-\nline basis.\nInventory:\nBOL changed its inventory valuation method from FIFO to weighted average cost for the\npurpose of providing more relevant and comparable information to financial statement users.\nSuch change has resulted in the following revision of financial figures:\nrT] For the period ending 31 December 2018 |For all periods prior to 2018\nCost of Goods Sold HK$600,000 increase HK$2,800,000 increase\nHK$600,000 decrease | HK$2,800,000 decrease\nThe following additional information is also available to BOL:\n° Retained earnings at 31 December 2017 was HK$15,700,000.\n. Profit (after taxes) for the year ended 31 December 2018 and 31 December 2019 was\nHK$1,430,000 and HK$1,690,000, respectively.\n. The income tax rate is 16.5%.\n. No dividends have been declared or paid during the current period.\n. Assume all amounts are material.\nRequired:\nIn accordance with HKAS 8 Accounting Policies, Changes in Accounting Estimates and\nErrors, ignoring deferred tax,\n(a) Explain how BOL should account for the machinery in the preparation of\nthe financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2019. Support your\nanswers with calculations.\n(4 marks)\n(b) Explain how BOL should account for the inventory in the preparation of the\nfinancial statements for the year ended 31 December 2019. Prepare an extract of\nthe statement of changes in equity for the year ended 31 December 2019 to\ndemonstrate the inventory effects.\n(6 marks)\nModule 6 (December 2020 Session) Page 5 of 7\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
