      "full": "Question 4 (20 marks — approximately 36 minutes)\nWood Property Limited (\"WPL\") owns a small shopping mall located in Mongkok, Hong Kong.\nOn 1 September 2018, WPL leased a 1,000 square feet of retail space in this shopping mall\n(space no. 308) to Kaya Limited (\"KAL\") for four years. The retail space is available for use\nby KAL on 1 January 2019.\nThe lease agreement contained the following clauses:\n. KAL has exclusive rights to use the retail space throughout the lease term.\n. Annual lease payment of HK$600,000 is payable on 1 January each year.\n. The annual payment shall be reviewed at the end of the second year and adjusted by\nmaking reference to the Consumer Price Index, which stood at 103 on 1 January 2019.\nWPL has estimated that the index would become 107 by end of 31 December 2020.\n. WPL can request KAL to move to another retail space on condition that there is a similar\nretail space available. Information reveals that space no. 308 is the only 1,000 square\nfeet retail space in the shopping mall. All other retail spaces are with area much less\nthan 1,000 square feet and are mostly occupied. On average, the rent per square feet\nof small retail spaces is higher than that of the larger ones.\nKAL has incurred some costs associated with the lease, including legal fees of HK$20,000 to\nobtain and finalise the lease agreement and real estate agent fees of HK$50,000 for soliciting\nthe retail space. KAL did not know the exact implicit interest rate of the lease and thus\nadopted its incremental borrowing rate of 6% per annum.\nRequired:\n(a) Determine whether the lease agreement above contains a lease under HKFRS 16\nLeases.\n(6 marks)\n(b) On 1 January 2019, the accountant of KAL recorded the lease payment of\nHK$600,000 as an expense. Justify whether this accounting treatment is correct\nunder HKFRS 16 Leases. No calculation is required.\n(3 marks)\n(c) Prepare journal entries for KAL to record the lease during the year ended\n31 December 2019 under HKFRS 16 Leases.\n(11 marks)\nModule 6 (December 2020 Session) Page 6 of 7\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
