      "answer": "Module 6 (June 2021 Session) Page 9 of 9 Answer 5(c) During the year ended 30 April 2019 financial year, no significant increase occurred in the credit risk of the bonds, and consequently, UPL would have classified the bonds within Stage 1 of the expected credit loss model, with a loss allowance of HK$10,000 representing the 12-month expected credit losses. For the year ended 30 April 2020, since there was a significant increase in the credit risk of the bonds (downgrade of LUL's credit rating), the bonds were classified within Stage 2 of the expected credit loss model and would have a loss allowance equal to the lifetime expected credit losses of HK$35,000. For the year ended 30 April 2020, UPL would recognize an impairment loss in profit or loss for the amount of the expected credit losses that was required to adjust the loss allowance to the amount required to be recognised at the reporting date. Therefore, an amount of HK$25,000 (HK$35,000 – HK$10,000) would be recognised as an impairment loss by UPL in profit or loss for the financial year ended 30 April 2020. * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
