      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/M1-10LP+Past%20paper/1-10%20Past%20paper/m6/Module%206%20Question%20Jun%202025.pdf#question-q-p001-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 6 (June 2025 Session) Page 1 of 7 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (Total: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (28 marks – approximately 50 minutes) Peacock Limited (\"Peacock\") acquired 80% of the ordinary shares of Salmon Limited (\"Salmon\") and 40% of the ordinary shares of Alligator Limited (\"Alligator\") on 1 April 2023. Peacock, together with its subsidiary, is collectively known as the Peacock Group (the \"Group\"). Acquisition of the shares of Salmon On 1 April 2023, Peacock paid HK$109,140,000 for the acquisition of the shares of Salmon. Since then, Salmon has become a subsidiary of the Group. Peacock assessed that, on 1 April 2023, the fair values of Salmon's recorded net assets were equal to their carrying amounts, except for an owner-occupied property which had a carrying amount of HK$72,000,000 (\"Property S\"). Property S had a fair value of HK$96,000,000 on 1 April 2023 and was assessed, on the same day, to have a remaining useful life of 40 years with no residual value. Peacock chose to measure the non-controlling interest in Salmon at its fair value which was measured at HK$27,280,000 at the acquisition date. Goodwill arising from this acquisition has not been impaired since acquisition. On 1 July 2023, Peacock sold inventories to Salmon at a transfer price of HK$18,000,000. Such sales were made at a mark-up on cost of 20%. Salmon sold 75% of these inventories to its customers by 31 March 2024. Acquisition of the shares of Alligator On 1 April 2023, Peacock paid HK$55,110,000 for the acquisition of the shares of Alligator. Since then, Alligator has become an associate of the Group. On the same day, Peacock appointed two out of five directors to the board of Alligator. Peacock assessed that, on 1 April 2023, the fair values of Alligator's recorded net assets were equal to their carrying amounts. On top of the above, Alligator owned an internally generated customer database with a fair value of HK$6,400,000 on 1 April 2023. This database, which was assessed to be identifiable, was believed to have a useful life of 4 years with no residual value. On 1 January 2024, Alligator declared and distributed dividends to its shareholders. The companies in the Group have not issued any shares since 1 April 2023. Selected accounting policies • Properties, plant and equipment are measured using the cost model in accordance with HKAS 16 Property, Plant and Equipment . • Intangible assets are measured using the cost model in accordance with HKAS 38 Intangible Assets . • Non-current assets are depreciated/ amortised over their respective useful lives on a straight-line basis. • Depreciation and amortisation are recorded on a monthly basis. • The investments in subsidiary and associate are presented in the separate financial statements at cost.",
      "full": "Module 6 (June 2025 Session) Page 1 of 7 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (Total: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (28 marks – approximately 50 minutes) Peacock Limited (\"Peacock\") acquired 80% of the ordinary shares of Salmon Limited (\"Salmon\") and 40% of the ordinary shares of Alligator Limited (\"Alligator\") on 1 April 2023. Peacock, together with its subsidiary, is collectively known as the Peacock Group (the \"Group\"). Acquisition of the shares of Salmon On 1 April 2023, Peacock paid HK$109,140,000 for the acquisition of the shares of Salmon. Since then, Salmon has become a subsidiary of the Group. Peacock assessed that, on 1 April 2023, the fair values of Salmon's recorded net assets were equal to their carrying amounts, except for an owner-occupied property which had a carrying amount of HK$72,000,000 (\"Property S\"). Property S had a fair value of HK$96,000,000 on 1 April 2023 and was assessed, on the same day, to have a remaining useful life of 40 years with no residual value. Peacock chose to measure the non-controlling interest in Salmon at its fair value which was measured at HK$27,280,000 at the acquisition date. Goodwill arising from this acquisition has not been impaired since acquisition. On 1 July 2023, Peacock sold inventories to Salmon at a transfer price of HK$18,000,000. Such sales were made at a mark-up on cost of 20%. Salmon sold 75% of these inventories to its customers by 31 March 2024. Acquisition of the shares of Alligator On 1 April 2023, Peacock paid HK$55,110,000 for the acquisition of the shares of Alligator. Since then, Alligator has become an associate of the Group. On the same day, Peacock appointed two out of five directors to the board of Alligator. Peacock assessed that, on 1 April 2023, the fair values of Alligator's recorded net assets were equal to their carrying amounts. On top of the above, Alligator owned an internally generated customer database with a fair value of HK$6,400,000 on 1 April 2023. This database, which was assessed to be identifiable, was believed to have a useful life of 4 years with no residual value. On 1 January 2024, Alligator declared and distributed dividends to its shareholders. The companies in the Group have not issued any shares since 1 April 2023. Selected accounting policies • Properties, plant and equipment are measured using the cost model in accordance with HKAS 16 Property, Plant and Equipment . • Intangible assets are measured using the cost model in accordance with HKAS 38 Intangible Assets . • Non-current assets are depreciated/ amortised over their respective useful lives on a straight-line basis. • Depreciation and amortisation are recorded on a monthly basis. • The investments in subsidiary and associate are presented in the separate financial statements at cost.",
