      "answer": "Total number of Number of Weighted average\nordinary shares months number of shares\nPeriod outstanding outstanding outstanding\n1 January to 31 March 20,000,000 X 3/12 = 5,000,000\n1 April to 31 December (20,000,000 + X 9/12 = 16,500,000\n2,000,000) =\n22,000,000\n21,500,000\nBasic earnings per share for the year ended 31 December 2023 = HK$51,600,000 +\n21,500,000 = HK$2.4\nIn accordance with HKAS 33 Earnings per Share, options are dilutive when they would result\nin the issue of ordinary shares for less than the average market price of ordinary shares\nduring the period. In Gorilla's case, the exercise price of the Options (HK$4) was below the\naverage market price of its shares during the year ended 31 December 2023 (HK$7) and\ntherefore the Options are in-the-money and considered dilutive.\nThe amount of dilution is the average market price of ordinary shares during the period minus\nthe issue price. To calculate diluted earnings per share, potential ordinary shares are\ntreated as consisting of both the following:",
