      "prompt": "Module 6 (June 2025 Session) Page 7 of 7 Question 4 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) On 1 January 2023, Gorilla Limited (\"Gorilla\") had 20,000,000 ordinary HK$1 share in issue. On 1 April 2023, Gorilla issued 2,000,000 ordinary shares at their full market price of HK$5 per share. There has been no other share issue or repurchase of share during the year ended 31 December 2023. Gorilla had HK$51,600,000 profit for the year ended 31 December 2023. On 1 January 2023, Gorilla issued a total of 700,000 options (the \"Options\") to two of its executive directors, Mr. Oscar Choi and Ms. Jessie Yip. The Options can be converted into one ordinary share per option, at any time from the time of issue to 30 June 2024, with an exercise price of HK$4. Gorilla's average share price over the year ended 31 December 2023 was HK$7. Neither Oscar nor Jessie exercised the Options by 31 December 2023. Required: (a) Calculate Gorilla ' s basic earnings per share for the year ended 31 December 2023. (4 marks) (b) Explain, with reference to HKAS 33 Earnings per Share , how the Options affect the calculation of Gorilla ' s diluted earnings per share for the year ended 31 December 2023. (6 marks) (c) Explain whether the issue of the Options is a related party transaction with reference to HKAS 24 Related Party Disclosures . (2 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
