      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 5 (December 2021 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (Total: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (17 marks – approximately 31 minutes) Many companies and organisations have allowed their employees to work from home (\"WFH\") during the COVID-19 pandemic. These employees might use different remote communication and network connection technologies to complete tasks assigned by their bosses. Issues of data protection and systems security have been more and more critical and of concern in a WFH environment. A report has mentioned that lax password protection and social engineering attacks are some of the new risks of WFH. (a) Define the term \"social engineering\". (2 marks) (b) Demonstrate how attackers conduct social engineering attacks with any THREE examples. (6 marks) (c) Analyse why the following measures could enhance the strength of password authentication: (i) Requiring users to change their passwords every three months; (3 marks) (ii) Locking a user's account automatically if the user has provided an incorrect password three times consecutively for that user account in the login portal; and (3 marks) (iii) A new requirement to extend the length of a login password from 6 characters to 10 characters. (3 marks)",
      "full": "Module 5 (December 2021 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (Total: 80 marks) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (17 marks – approximately 31 minutes) Many companies and organisations have allowed their employees to work from home (\"WFH\") during the COVID-19 pandemic. These employees might use different remote communication and network connection technologies to complete tasks assigned by their bosses. Issues of data protection and systems security have been more and more critical and of concern in a WFH environment. A report has mentioned that lax password protection and social engineering attacks are some of the new risks of WFH. (a) Define the term \"social engineering\". (2 marks) (b) Demonstrate how attackers conduct social engineering attacks with any THREE examples. (6 marks) (c) Analyse why the following measures could enhance the strength of password authentication: (i) Requiring users to change their passwords every three months; (3 marks) (ii) Locking a user's account automatically if the user has provided an incorrect password three times consecutively for that user account in the login portal; and (3 marks) (iii) A new requirement to extend the length of a login password from 6 characters to 10 characters. (3 marks)",
