      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 5 (December 2021 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 2 (19 marks – approximately 34 minutes) (a) In the retail industry, managers and proprietors think about how their company can perform better than its competitors in order to obtain competitive advantages. Required: State and describe any THREE areas of competitive advantage which a company can develop, achieve or maintain. (6 mark) (b) Categorise the THREE types of reports which can be generated by a management information system (\"MIS\"). (3 marks) (c) Based on the answers in part (b), demonstrate each type of report with an example. (6 marks) (d) Contrast the TWO differences between predictive data analytics and prescriptive data analytics. (4 marks) Question 3 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) (a) Summarise the primary and secondary activities under Porter's value chain model. (3 marks) (b) Outline any TWO primary duties or responsibilities of a production department in a manufacturing company and any TWO types of its information needs. (4 marks) (c) Classify any THREE basic functions of a computer network with brief descriptions. (6 marks) (d) List and describe the THREE common cloud deployment models. (3 marks) (e) List and describe any TWO benefits of using cloud storage services. (4 marks)",
