      "prompt": "Module 5 (December 2021 Session) Page 3 of 4 Question 4 (11 marks – approximately 20 minutes) (a) The waterfall model is a popular and traditional system development life cycle approach that was used for software development. This model required significant system analysis and system design before starting system implementation. However, programmers or system analysts now may consider adopting other software development models for their software development projects. Required: Apart from the waterfall model, state and describe any TWO other software development models. (4 marks) (b) A common approach to evaluate suitability among different packaged accounting software is to identify and compare the features among the software comprehensively. To speed up this evaluation process, we can categorise the features into three types: essential features, value adding features and non-essential features. Required: Demonstrate any ONE essential feature and any ONE value adding feature of a packaged accounting software. (4 marks) (c) List any THREE common sources of system change requests. (3 marks)",
