      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 5 (December 2021 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 5 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) (a) State any FOUR reasons why Hong Kong is perfectly suited and situated for e- commerce imports and exports. (4 marks) (b) Imagine that you are a general manager of a new online home appliance store. In a monthly meeting, you suggested selling some fancy and innovative home appliance products from Japan and South Korea in order to compete with other well-established retailers in the market. However, one of the directors worried that some customers may be displeased with these fancy and innovative products after receipt and that they may then ask to return the product during the guaranteed seven-day return period. Required: Justify the importance of the following areas that an e-commerce retailer should consider to reduce the possibility of receiving non-defect products from displeased customers: (i) Managing customer expectations; and (3 marks) (ii) Training customers for better product knowledge. (3 marks) (c) Knowledge management systems (\"KMS\") are usually used in customer service or support activities. A customer service representative can get reliable answer(s) or solution(s) quickly by simply typing a customer's question in the full-text search function of an internal KMS. Required: List the sequence of the SIX major steps under the knowledge management system cycle. (3 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
      "full": "Module 5 (December 2021 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 5 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) (a) State any FOUR reasons why Hong Kong is perfectly suited and situated for e- commerce imports and exports. (4 marks) (b) Imagine that you are a general manager of a new online home appliance store. In a monthly meeting, you suggested selling some fancy and innovative home appliance products from Japan and South Korea in order to compete with other well-established retailers in the market. However, one of the directors worried that some customers may be displeased with these fancy and innovative products after receipt and that they may then ask to return the product during the guaranteed seven-day return period. Required: Justify the importance of the following areas that an e-commerce retailer should consider to reduce the possibility of receiving non-defect products from displeased customers: (i) Managing customer expectations; and (3 marks) (ii) Training customers for better product knowledge. (3 marks) (c) Knowledge management systems (\"KMS\") are usually used in customer service or support activities. A customer service representative can get reliable answer(s) or solution(s) quickly by simply typing a customer's question in the full-text search function of an internal KMS. Required: List the sequence of the SIX major steps under the knowledge management system cycle. (3 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
