      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 5 (June 2022 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 3 (16 marks – approximately 29 minutes) (a) Analyse each of the following situations of a point-of-sales (POS) system and apply an appropriate input control to prevent each of them from happening again. Justify your answers with explanations. (i) The VIP code of Customer X was used and applied to a sales transaction of Customer Y. (3 marks) (ii) A salesperson input the wrong discount rate in a sales transaction, which resulted in selling an item at a discounted price that was far below its unit cost. (3 marks) (iii) A customer service representative officer accepted and recorded a returned item which had not been kept and sold by the company. (3 mark) (b) State any TWO advantages of implementing segregation of duties among employees using information systems. (4 marks) (c) Contrast on the operation of symmetric and asymmetric key encryption. (3 marks)",
