      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/M1-10LP+Past%20paper/1-10%20Past%20paper/m4/Module%204%20Question%20Jun%202021.pdf#question-q-p001-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 4 (June 2021 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 MARKS) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Giosinni Company Limited (\"Giosinni\") is an apparel brand retailer, headquartered in Hong Kong, with its main markets in Hong Kong and mainland China. Giosinni was founded in 1985, and it has quickly grown to 235 locations in Hong Kong and mainland China, with a mix of directly managed and franchised stores. The major product of Giosinni is casual wear apparel, including men ' s, ladies ' , youth s ' , and children ' s wear. Giosinni will sometimes cooperate with famous designers to produce cross - over wear to attract new customers. Giosinni understands that the management of internal stakeholders is important in creating a good working atmosphere. Moreover, Giosinni considers customer satisfaction to be equally important. Thus, the company wants to track and analyse its internal environments and hopes to create a customer-oriented culture. Required: (a) State and describe the internal environment of Giosinni. (8 marks) (b) Define customer satisfaction and customer loyalty. State the implication of creating a customer-oriented culture at Giosinni in terms of these two aspects. (2 marks) Question 2 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Happy Homes Properties (\"HHP\") is committed to developing quality residential estates, offices and shopping malls for citizens of Hong Kong. Apart from properties, HHP also provides other services, including investment, information technology, and telecommunications. HHP is committed to prudent financial policies with the aim of maintaining high liquidity and low gearing. Because of its excellent financial policies, HHP has earned high credit ratings from noted credit rating agencies. Required: Being the Chief Financial Officer of HHP, apart from basic financial ratios, leverage ability, asset management, and profitability of the company, identify and explain FIVE other factors that you should consider when making debt financing decisions. (10 marks)",
      "full": "Module 4 (June 2021 Session) Page 1 of 4 SECTION B – WRITTEN QUESTIONS (TOTAL: 80 MARKS) Answer ALL questions in this section. Marks are indicated at the end of each question. Together they are worth 80% of the total marks for this examination. Question 1 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Giosinni Company Limited (\"Giosinni\") is an apparel brand retailer, headquartered in Hong Kong, with its main markets in Hong Kong and mainland China. Giosinni was founded in 1985, and it has quickly grown to 235 locations in Hong Kong and mainland China, with a mix of directly managed and franchised stores. The major product of Giosinni is casual wear apparel, including men ' s, ladies ' , youth s ' , and children ' s wear. Giosinni will sometimes cooperate with famous designers to produce cross - over wear to attract new customers. Giosinni understands that the management of internal stakeholders is important in creating a good working atmosphere. Moreover, Giosinni considers customer satisfaction to be equally important. Thus, the company wants to track and analyse its internal environments and hopes to create a customer-oriented culture. Required: (a) State and describe the internal environment of Giosinni. (8 marks) (b) Define customer satisfaction and customer loyalty. State the implication of creating a customer-oriented culture at Giosinni in terms of these two aspects. (2 marks) Question 2 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Happy Homes Properties (\"HHP\") is committed to developing quality residential estates, offices and shopping malls for citizens of Hong Kong. Apart from properties, HHP also provides other services, including investment, information technology, and telecommunications. HHP is committed to prudent financial policies with the aim of maintaining high liquidity and low gearing. Because of its excellent financial policies, HHP has earned high credit ratings from noted credit rating agencies. Required: Being the Chief Financial Officer of HHP, apart from basic financial ratios, leverage ability, asset management, and profitability of the company, identify and explain FIVE other factors that you should consider when making debt financing decisions. (10 marks)",
      "options": [],
