      "sourceMode": "text",
      "ocrUsed": false,
      "answer": "Module 4 (June 2021 Session) 9 of 9 Answer 6(c) Identification of the levels fulfilled in Maslow’s hierarchy of needs:  It is assumed that most of the employees are satisfied with the physiological, safety, and affiliation needs. With regard to the appraisal results, Ho Lok should focus on the following two needs:  Esteem needs  When employees have high ratings in their appraisals, Ho Lok can, for example, promote the employees, provide higher bonuses, and publicise the names of these excellent employees. This can satisfy the esteem needs of employees.  Self-actualisation needs  Managers should have appraisal discussions with employees during the appraisal process, where managers can, for example, set challenging goals for the employees and provide employees with necessary training to improve their weaknesses and skill-sets. This can satisfy the self-actualisation needs. * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
