      "prompt": "Module 4 (June 2021 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 3 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) All You Can Cook (\"AYCC\") is a newly established company providing fresh food packs preparation and delivery services to busy households and young families. All food packs are made-to-order every morning and can be ordered online or via WhatsApp. Because of this, AYCC tries to select high quality and safe raw materials. Simple cooking methods and full recipes are prepared for all customers so that they can have an enjoyable and simple cooking experience. AYCC understands that customers always want to enjoy low-priced food packs, but with good service and quality. However, this is a dilemma for the top management of AYCC. Thus, they need to adopt a good control system to make sure all products and services they provide are of good quality. Required: (a) Explain the dilemma faced by AYCC. (2 marks) (b) State and explain the importance of implementing control systems for AYCC. (8 marks) Question 4 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Excellent Food (\"EF\") is a food provider established in Hong Kong. EF wholesales the seafood to restaurants in the city. It also has retail shops selling seafood directly to families. The vision of EF is to be the leading seafood provider and to help create an excellent lifestyle for their customers. Recently, EF has received some complaints about the quality of their seafood, and thus, sales volumes have reduced. As the Marketing Director of EF, the Chief Executive Officer has asked you to investigate the problem and suggest ways to improve the quality of their seafood provided to customers. Required: You would like to adopt a breakthrough strategy under Six Sigma. List and explain the FIVE steps of this strategy that EF can follow. (10 marks)",
