      "prompt": "Module 4 (June 2021 Session) Page 3 of 4 Question 5 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) PetPet is a new start-up company in Hong Kong. This company mainly sells pet food and related products to customers. In view of the high cost of rent in Hong Kong, PetPet sells its products online to reduce costs. The products it sells include some licensed pet food, pet wears, and pet toys, among others. In order to prepare the launch of the company and promote its brand to customers, PetPet would like to design a better promotion and pricing strategy so that its customers can know and try its products. PetPet has conducted simple marketing research to understand the needs of customers. This research has found that most customers are quite price-sensitive with regards to pet products, and thus, they would look for licensed foods offered at a good price by the company. Moreover, the research has also found that customers no longer rely on traditional promotion methods, such as TV commercials or newspapers. Instead, they spend more time on social media and with instant communication tools. In the short-term, PetPet would like to become one of the preferred pet brands among its customers. Required: (a) Based on the results of the marketing research, explain what marketing channels PetPet should adopt to attract new customers. (2 marks) (b) List and describe FIVE types of pricing strategies. Identify and explain which pricing strategy is the most appropriate for PetPet. (12 marks) (c) E-commerce has been a popular way to sell products globally. Explain the challenges that PetPet will encounter when it sells products online. (6 marks)",
