      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 4 (December 2021 Session) Page 3 of 6 Question 3 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Rose Aviation Limited (\"Rose\") is a traditional airline company developed and based in Hong Kong since 1984. It aims to provide excellent services and an enjoyable flying experience for individual and business passengers through its worldwide route coverage and comprehensive in-flight services. Rose believes that carrying passengers from one place to another place safely is of top priority. Thus, they regularly conduct flight maintenance and systems upgrades to ensure service quality. Moreover, all staff members are trained professionally to make sure the services provided are of excellent standards. They are also required to attend annual refresher courses related to safety and service issues. Rose also introduced technology to ensure accurate and on-time flight schedules, ticketing services, and baggage claims for each passenger. With the adoption of technology, Rose has been able to reduce service failure by 85% this year. Staff members are important elements in ensuring the provision of excellent service. Apart from comprehensive training programmes, including induction training for new hires, on-the-job training, periodic training, and refresher courses are provided to all staff in order to make sure their skills and services are current. Rose has also adopted attractive compensation and benefits packages for their staff members. Every staff member is eligible for an annual bonus and salary adjustments based on their individual- and team-based performance. Outport allowances are also reviewed every year based on different factors. Senior staff members are also given an opportunity to enjoy stock options based on the results of performance appraisals. With all these comprehensive HR policies adopted by Rose, they have been able to attract high quality candidates for every hiring exercise. Once the job advertisement is posted on their company website, many applications are received. Moreover, Rose has opened many opportunities for promotion and transfer, and thus cabin crews can request to be transferred back to the office when there are vacancies. Required: (a) State and explain the service element adopted by Rose. (2 marks) (b) Identify and explain any TWO functions of human resource management involved in Rose. (8 marks)",
      "full": "Module 4 (December 2021 Session) Page 3 of 6 Question 3 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Rose Aviation Limited (\"Rose\") is a traditional airline company developed and based in Hong Kong since 1984. It aims to provide excellent services and an enjoyable flying experience for individual and business passengers through its worldwide route coverage and comprehensive in-flight services. Rose believes that carrying passengers from one place to another place safely is of top priority. Thus, they regularly conduct flight maintenance and systems upgrades to ensure service quality. Moreover, all staff members are trained professionally to make sure the services provided are of excellent standards. They are also required to attend annual refresher courses related to safety and service issues. Rose also introduced technology to ensure accurate and on-time flight schedules, ticketing services, and baggage claims for each passenger. With the adoption of technology, Rose has been able to reduce service failure by 85% this year. Staff members are important elements in ensuring the provision of excellent service. Apart from comprehensive training programmes, including induction training for new hires, on-the-job training, periodic training, and refresher courses are provided to all staff in order to make sure their skills and services are current. Rose has also adopted attractive compensation and benefits packages for their staff members. Every staff member is eligible for an annual bonus and salary adjustments based on their individual- and team-based performance. Outport allowances are also reviewed every year based on different factors. Senior staff members are also given an opportunity to enjoy stock options based on the results of performance appraisals. With all these comprehensive HR policies adopted by Rose, they have been able to attract high quality candidates for every hiring exercise. Once the job advertisement is posted on their company website, many applications are received. Moreover, Rose has opened many opportunities for promotion and transfer, and thus cabin crews can request to be transferred back to the office when there are vacancies. Required: (a) State and explain the service element adopted by Rose. (2 marks) (b) Identify and explain any TWO functions of human resource management involved in Rose. (8 marks)",
      "options": [],
