      "sourceMode": "text",
      "ocrUsed": false,
      "answer": "Module 4 (December 2021 Session) 9 of 9 7. Aesthetics How a product looks, feels, sounds, smells, or tastes. Since most of the electronic components are installed inside the machine or devices, whether the components are light in weight and small in size would be the major concern to Ng Wah. 8. Safety Assurance that the customer will not suffer injury or harm from a product. Ng Wah should make sure their electronic components are of good quality and no injury or damage to the devices or customers are incurred. 9. Other perceptions Subjective perceptions based on brand name, advertising and the like. Ng Wah may also need to consider its company image and brand awareness among target customers. * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
      "answerSource": "",
      "hasAnswer": true
