      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 4 (December 2021 Session) Page 5 of 6 Question 5 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) Easy Fitness (\"E&F\") was founded in Hong Kong in 2016. It was born out of a passion for fresh and healthy food and started with a small retail store in Lan Kwai Fong. In 2018, because of technological advancement and a change in the market environment, E&F started to expand its business to fitness lovers through a mobile application which provides recipes and suggestions to people who want to maintain a healthy body and figure. E&F also provides food delivery through the application. The work-from-home trend has enabled E&F to further develop and enhance its application's functions. Apart from providing fitness food and recipes to fitness lovers, E&F has also designed fitness programme to fit the needs of the people who stay at home but still want to maintain a healthy and fit lifestyle. Therefore, E&F's application has quickly become the top ranked application in most mobile application stores. Initially, sales through the application kept increasing, but later E&F found that many similar applications entered the market, slowing the growth rate of E&F down in 2020. Due to the slowing growth of revenue, E&F is thinking of expanding its market from Hong Kong to other territories. Indeed, some of the food ingredients are sourced from other areas as well, and thus E&F has already developed networks and relationships with these suppliers overseas. To reduce the potential risks and challenges in the developing countries, E&F would like to enter some countries in the Asia Pacific region, where economies are growing and political states are stabler. E&F hopes that its application, along with its recipes, can provide a better choice for overseas customers. Required: (a) Identify and explain FOUR stages of product life cycle and state with reason which stage the E&F application belongs to. (10 marks) (b) Explain the importance of globalisation for E&F. (2 marks) (c) Identify and explain TWO factors to be considered when entering a new country for E&F. (4 marks) (d) Describe TWO potential risks that E&F should pay attention to when entering international markets. (4 marks)",
