      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 4 (December 2021 Session) Page 6 of 6 Question 6 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) Ng Wah Electronics Limited (\"Ng Wah\") is a company listed on the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong. Ng Wah was founded in 1980, and its main business is the design, development, manufacture, and sale of a wide range of electronic components, including different types of inductors, transformers, electrolytic capacitors, and electroceramics materials, among others. Its products have been widely adopted in different industry segments, including power supply devices, telecommunication equipment, digital audio-visual products, and handheld multimedia equipment. Ng Wah understands that product quality is of paramount importance, and thus, they have invested a lot on research and development to upgrade and streamline their production processes and systems. Due to its dedicated team of research engineers, Ng Wah has become one of the major electronic components suppliers in Hong Kong. Because of its success with manufacturing electronic components and its years of experience in the electronics industry, Ng Wah has started to consider providing consulting services to clients. Ng Wah believes this new initiative can help further develop the company. Ng Wah understands that producing electronic components and providing professional consulting services are completely different; thus, the senior management of the company is now formulating a proposal for this new initiative. Required: (a) Producing products and providing services are different. With reference to Ng Wah's situation, explain how services are distinct from products. (8 marks) (b) Ng Wah understands the importance of producing high quality electronic components to customers. Describe any SIX dimensions of quality for manufactured products that Ng Wah's customers may look for. (12 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
