      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 4 (June 2022 Session) Page 2 of 6 Question 2 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) Simply Snack (\"SS\") is a snack company that sells snacks to local customers in Country A. It operates across different cities and has more than 50 stores. Because of the boom of the culture of Country A over the world, SS is preparing for its international expansion. SS would like to start its expansion with the nearest countries first because SS believes that the national culture should be similar. Country B and Country C would be the first two choices. To do so, SS has hired Chris to be the General Manager to manage the international expansion. Chris thought that it would be easier for SS to enter these two countries by selling their snack products to the distributors and supermarket chains in Country B and Country C, so he has contacted several targets for this arrangement. However, the distributors were worried about all the issues related to the origin of the products. Both Country B and Country C have had historical conflicts with Country A in the past, so some local citizens in Country B and Country C have boycotted the products manufactured in Country A before. Moreover, Chris was not familiar with the policies of selling products in the host countries and this further creates troubles to the expansion. Worse still, the products themselves are the traditional snack of Country A and Chris was not sure about the issue of previous warfare between Country A, Country B, and Country C. On the packing of the products, all ingredients were shown in the language of Country A and thus, Chris was also considering if the package needs redesigning. Required: (a) Identify the approach that SS used to enter the business in Country B and Country C. (1 mark) (b) State and explain THREE issues mentioned in the case information that Chris faced during the start of his international trade. (9 marks)",
