      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 4 (June 2022 Session) Page 5 of 6 Question 5 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) With more than 150 hotels in different countries, Romantic Hotels Group (\"RH\") aims to deliver exceptional guest experiences. Through the values of integrity, passionate, excellence, and leadership, RH aims to become the world leader in the hospitality industry. The mission statement of RH is \"As a business of serving people, our service is beyond the boundary of people, culture, and everything\". As such, RH has emphasised delivering excellent services to the guests, aiming to provide the best memory and experiences before, during, and after their stay in RH. The top management has recently projected that there will be a boom in the tourism industry, RH would like to develop its brands as well, aiming to provide reasonable price but excellent services to their guests. Peter Lo, the Chief Financial Officer, understands that this requires better financial risk planning and control procedures to ensure the smooth development of RH. Moreover, it is important to display a healthy financial performance to their shareholders. Required: (a) State and describe any TWO elements of service concept. Then explain with examples how RH applies the TWO elements you mentioned. (8 marks) (b) State and describe any THREE techniques to measure and interpret financial risks facing RH. (6 marks) (c) When making financing decision for the future development of RH, list and summarise any THREE factors that the Chief Financial Officer needs to take into consideration. (6 marks)",
