      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 4 (June 2022 Session) Page 6 of 6 Question 6 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) Cup Daily (\"CD\") is a retailer selling coffee beans and coffee products. To ensure the finest quality of coffee beans, they have forged a good relationship with the coffee bean farmers from various places, for examples, Argentina, Brazil, etc. The coffee beans are then transported to its manufacturing plants to process and pack. In the manufacturing plants, CD uses automation and efficient manufacturing layout to speed up the operation. All processes and packed coffee beans products are then transported to logistics centres to maintain quality products from sourcing to the end users. CD operates in Hong Kong, Japan, and Taiwan through company-owned stores or licensees. It also adopts efficient and automatic delivery network to ensure reliable and secured storage and delivery of the products either from the coffee beans farmers to the manufacturing plants or from the plants to the stores and end users. Recently, CD found that the cost of coffee beans storage is extremely high, which seriously affects the profits generated. Therefore, the Operation Manager would like to adopt a just-in-time system to solve the high storage cost problem. Required: (a) Identify and explain the THREE types of primary activities described in the information provided by CD. (6 marks) (b) It is important to understand the external environment when running a business. Based on PESTLE analysis, state and illustrate any THREE of the elements of PESTLE for CD. (6 marks) (c) Define the just-in-time system. (2 marks) (d) Explain ONE major advantage of adopting just-in-time system, and TWO potential disadvantages for CD. (6 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
      "full": "Module 4 (June 2022 Session) Page 6 of 6 Question 6 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) Cup Daily (\"CD\") is a retailer selling coffee beans and coffee products. To ensure the finest quality of coffee beans, they have forged a good relationship with the coffee bean farmers from various places, for examples, Argentina, Brazil, etc. The coffee beans are then transported to its manufacturing plants to process and pack. In the manufacturing plants, CD uses automation and efficient manufacturing layout to speed up the operation. All processes and packed coffee beans products are then transported to logistics centres to maintain quality products from sourcing to the end users. CD operates in Hong Kong, Japan, and Taiwan through company-owned stores or licensees. It also adopts efficient and automatic delivery network to ensure reliable and secured storage and delivery of the products either from the coffee beans farmers to the manufacturing plants or from the plants to the stores and end users. Recently, CD found that the cost of coffee beans storage is extremely high, which seriously affects the profits generated. Therefore, the Operation Manager would like to adopt a just-in-time system to solve the high storage cost problem. Required: (a) Identify and explain the THREE types of primary activities described in the information provided by CD. (6 marks) (b) It is important to understand the external environment when running a business. Based on PESTLE analysis, state and illustrate any THREE of the elements of PESTLE for CD. (6 marks) (c) Define the just-in-time system. (2 marks) (d) Explain ONE major advantage of adopting just-in-time system, and TWO potential disadvantages for CD. (6 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
