      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 3 (December 2022 Session) Page 3 of 5 Question 3 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) In a management context, statistics is a subject (a branch of mathematics) concerned with studying and developing methods for collecting, analysing, interpreting, and presenting data to facilitate decision making. Required: (a) Explain what sampling is and how it is related to inferential statistics. (4 marks) (b) Continued with part (a). Analyse how statistical analysis can be used to assist decision making by stating the appropriate sequence with the terms provided below: (_______)  ( _______)  ( _______)  ( _______)  ( _______)  ( _______)  Sampled data  ___?___ sampling  Information  Statistical inference  Raw data  Population ___?___ (4 marks) (c) Explain the key differences between time-series and cross-sectional data. (2 marks) (d) State and describe the FOUR components of time series. (6 marks) (e) Country A's economic activities have been severely disrupted since the beginning of 2020 by the lockdown measures brought about by the covid-19 pandemic. With an overwhelming percentage of the country's population having received full vaccination by the end of 2020, the country's tourism industry had gradually recovered since the first quarter of 2021. The following table shows the quarterly data (2020-21) on the dollar sales of the leisure and hospitalization sector. Sales (Leisure & Hospitalisation Sector) Period Sales ($ billion) Q1/2020 8 Q2/2020 4 Q3/2020 3 Q4/2020 2 Q1/2021 3 Q2/2021 4 Q3/2021 5 Q4/2021 6 Compute the quarterly sales growth rates of the last two quarters of 2021 on a year-over-year and quarter-over-quarter (i.e., sequential) basis. (4 marks)",
      "full": "Module 3 (December 2022 Session) Page 3 of 5 Question 3 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) In a management context, statistics is a subject (a branch of mathematics) concerned with studying and developing methods for collecting, analysing, interpreting, and presenting data to facilitate decision making. Required: (a) Explain what sampling is and how it is related to inferential statistics. (4 marks) (b) Continued with part (a). Analyse how statistical analysis can be used to assist decision making by stating the appropriate sequence with the terms provided below: (_______)  ( _______)  ( _______)  ( _______)  ( _______)  ( _______)  Sampled data  ___?___ sampling  Information  Statistical inference  Raw data  Population ___?___ (4 marks) (c) Explain the key differences between time-series and cross-sectional data. (2 marks) (d) State and describe the FOUR components of time series. (6 marks) (e) Country A's economic activities have been severely disrupted since the beginning of 2020 by the lockdown measures brought about by the covid-19 pandemic. With an overwhelming percentage of the country's population having received full vaccination by the end of 2020, the country's tourism industry had gradually recovered since the first quarter of 2021. The following table shows the quarterly data (2020-21) on the dollar sales of the leisure and hospitalization sector. Sales (Leisure & Hospitalisation Sector) Period Sales ($ billion) Q1/2020 8 Q2/2020 4 Q3/2020 3 Q4/2020 2 Q1/2021 3 Q2/2021 4 Q3/2021 5 Q4/2021 6 Compute the quarterly sales growth rates of the last two quarters of 2021 on a year-over-year and quarter-over-quarter (i.e., sequential) basis. (4 marks)",
      "options": [],
      "sourcePage": 3,
      "sourceMode": "text",
      "ocrUsed": false,
      "answer": "p = 480/500 = 0.96, n=500, Zoos = 1.96\n= (0.96 — 1.96 9960-096) ( 9544 gg 0.96(1-096),\n500 500\n=(0.96 — 0.0172, 0.96 + 0.0172)\n=(0.942, 0.9772)\nFalse. Just as with any statistic estimated from a (random) sample, the upper and lower\nbounds of the confidence interval will vary from sample to sample. It follows that a 95% level\nof confidence means that 95% of the intervals calculated from the random samples will\ncontain the true population mean.\n* * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *\nModule 3 (December 2022 Session) Page 6 of 6\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
