      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 3 (June 2021 Session) Page 2 of 5 Question 2 (16 marks – approximately 29 minutes) International trade has long been one of the key engines for national and global economic growth. In recent years, nationalism and protectionism have been gaining more momentum even among developed economies. Required: (a) Define gains from international trade and state any TWO of its sources. (3 marks) (b) Compare tariff and quota as trade protectionist measures. (4 marks) (c) Hong Kong has long been a highly externally-oriented economy that relies on international trade and finance to flourish. (i) Describe a commonly-used measure for an economy's \"degree of trade openness\". (2 marks) (ii) Based on the measure in part (c)(i), compare the degree of trade openness between Hong Kong and the US. (1 mark) (iii) State the TWO fundamental types of exchange rate systems. (2 marks) (iv) Describe the exchange rate system adopted by Hong Kong in relation to the answer to part (c)(iii). (1 mark) (v) State ONE advantage and ONE disadvantage of Hong Kong's exchange rate system to the territory. (3 marks)",
