      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 3 (June 2021 Session) Page 4 of 5 Question 4 (24 marks – approximately 43 minutes) (a) Statistics, as a discipline, is typically divided into two categories: descriptive and inferential. (i) Describe inferential statistics and random sampling methods. (4 marks) (ii) List TWO advantages and TWO disadvantages of random sampling method in statistical inference. (2 marks) (iii) State and describe any TWO random sampling methods. (6 marks) (b) State and describe the two defining characteristics of public goods. (4 marks) (c) Jocelyn is an economics lecturer. She has ranked her three options of what she can do during the summer in the following order: (1) work as a consultant full-time and earn HK$35,000; (2) teach summer school for the first eight weeks of summer and earn HK$20,000 and spend the rest of the summer travelling; and (3) write textbook supplements for a publisher full-time and earn HK$30,000. Required: Explain the opportunity cost of Jocelyn's choice. (8 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
