      "prompt": "Module 2 (June 2021 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 2 (28 marks – approximately 50 minutes) Pinky Products Limited (\"PPL\") manufactures two products: Premium and Deluxe. Details of the two products for next year are estimated as follows: Premium Deluxe Production units 100,000 200,000 Machine hours per unit 2 1.5 Direct materials per unit HK$20 HK$10 Direct labour per unit HK$30 HK$60 A traditional absorption costing is used at present. Production overheads are absorbed on a machine hour basis. The estimated production overheads for next year are HK$6,400,000. An executive director of PPL has challenged the appropriateness of using the current overhead absorption system and has recommended that the activity-based costing (\"ABC\") system would provide more relevant and accurate product cost information. Further analysis was provided by the management accountant to facilitate the use of ABC to absorb production overheads for next year. HK$ Costs relating to machinery 2,000,000 Costs relating to set up 1,800,000 Costs relating to materials handling 1,400,000 Costs relating to inspection 1,200,000 Total 6,400,000 Premium Deluxe Number of set up 410 190 Number of materials handling 920 1,080 Number of inspection 670 330 The selling price for each product is set at a uniform mark-up of 25%. Required: (a) Calculate the selling price per unit for each product for next year using the traditional system of absorbing production overheads on a machine hour basis. (8 marks) (b) Applying activity-based costing, calculate the cost driver rate for each of the four production overheads and selling price per unit for each product for next year. (16 marks) (c) Contrast the selling price per unit for each product for next year calculated in Questions 2(a) and 2(b) above. (4 marks)",
