      "prompt": "Module 2 (June 2021 Session) Page 3 of 4 Question 3 (20 marks – approximately 36 minutes) Sapphire Company Limited (\"SCL\") manufactures an organic health food product and has recently introduced a system of standard costing. The standard variable cost for the product is as follows: HK$ Direct materials (10 kgs at HK$20 per kg) 200 Direct labour (3 hours at HK$80 per hour) 240 Variable manufacturing overheads (3 hours at HK$50 per direct labour hour) 150 ___ 590 59,000 kgs raw materials were purchased at a cost of HK$1,298,000 and 5,600 units of the health food product were produced during last month. Other actual data for last month were as follows: Raw materials used 54,000 kgs Direct labour paid (18,000 hours) HK$1,350,000 Actual direct labour hours worked 17,800 hours Variable manufacturing overheads incurred HK$860,000 Variable manufacturing overheads are absorbed based on actual direct labour hour worked. Budgeted normal capacity expressed in direct labour hours for last month is 18,300 hours. SCL decides to calculate the price variance of direct materials at the time of receipt. Required: (a) Calculate the price and quantity variances for direct materials. (4 marks) (b) Calculate the rate, idle time and efficiency variances for direct labour. (6 marks) (c) Calculate the spending and efficiency variances for variable manufacturing overheads. (4 marks) (d) Justify the policy of SCL to calculate direct materials price variance at the time of receipt. (2 marks) (e) Calculate the labour production volume ratio and labour capacity ratio. (4 marks)",
