      "answer": "Zhuhai Chongqing\nDivision Division\nHK$ HK$\nInvestment 3,600,000 — 2,100,000 2,200,000 — 900,000\n(Total assets — current liabilities) =1,500,000 =1,300,000\nReturn on investment (\"ROI\") 250,000 / 1,500,000 x 180,000 / 1,300,000 x\n100% = 16.67% 100%\n= 13.85%\nRequired return (15% x investment) 225,000 195,000\nResidual income (\"RI\") 250,000 — 225,000 180,000 — 195,000\n= 25,000 = (15,000)\nAn acceptable investment should have an ROI that exceeds the firm's required rate of return\n(\"RRR\"), which is the minimum return a firm's management will accept for an investment.\nEqually, an acceptable investment has a positive RI. A positive Rl indicates a return greater\nthan a firm's RRR.\nThe Zhuhai Division has a better performance. Its ROI is higher than the RRR and it has\na positive RI, which is acceptable to the management.\nThe Chongqing Division has an ROI lower than the RRR and a negative RI.\nThe management of the company may consider shutting down the division and putting\nthe investment thereon to other profitable use or to explore new geographical markets.\n* * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *\nModule 2 (December 2020 Session) Page 6 of 6\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
