      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 2 (December 2021 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 4 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) Headey Development Limited (\"HDL\") is a group of retail chain stores of luxury products for high end customers in the East Asia region. It is evaluating the performance of one of its chain stores with the following information for the year just ended. HDL's weighted average cost of capital is 12%. HK$ Statement of profit or loss: Sales 2,480,000 Gross profit 1,460,000 Net operating profit before tax 1,020,000 Net operating profit after tax 828,000 Statement of financial position: Total assets 4,800,000 Current liabilities 1,200,000 Long-term liabilities 2,000,000 Required: (a) Compute the economic value added of the chain store and interpret the result. (6 marks) (b) The management considers setting key performance indicators (\"KPIs\") for the whole group. Explain to the management what KPIs are, the distinction between operational KPIs and strategic KPIs, and state THREE features of a good KPI. (6 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * *",
