      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 2 (June 2022 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 2 (26 marks – approximately 47 minutes) Fontaine Manufacturing Limited (\"FML\") manufactures bathroom utensils. Its factory in Tseung Kwan O Industrial Estate is producing two types of basin cabinets with the following cost and sales forecasts for next quarter. Aluminium Plywood Sales demand (units) 12,000 10,000 HK$ per unit HK$ per unit Selling price 2,900 4,000 Direct material cost 850 1,400 Direct labour cost 300 400 Variable production overhead 250 600 Fixed production overhead 600 500 FML's production capacity is estimated at 62,000 direct labour hours for next quarter. Direct labour will be paid at HK$100 per hour. Required: (a) Calculate the shortage in direct labour hours for FML if production is scheduled to meet all the expected sales demands of the two products. (4 marks) (b) Determine the production priority of the two products in view of the labour constraint. Prepare an optimal production plan and calculate the total contribution margin of each product and the profit of FML as a whole for next quarter to maximise company profit. (16 marks) (c) In view of the shortage in direct labour hours to meet all the sales demands, explain to the management of FML THREE ways to overcome the labour shortage. (6 marks)",
      "full": "Module 2 (June 2022 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 2 (26 marks – approximately 47 minutes) Fontaine Manufacturing Limited (\"FML\") manufactures bathroom utensils. Its factory in Tseung Kwan O Industrial Estate is producing two types of basin cabinets with the following cost and sales forecasts for next quarter. Aluminium Plywood Sales demand (units) 12,000 10,000 HK$ per unit HK$ per unit Selling price 2,900 4,000 Direct material cost 850 1,400 Direct labour cost 300 400 Variable production overhead 250 600 Fixed production overhead 600 500 FML's production capacity is estimated at 62,000 direct labour hours for next quarter. Direct labour will be paid at HK$100 per hour. Required: (a) Calculate the shortage in direct labour hours for FML if production is scheduled to meet all the expected sales demands of the two products. (4 marks) (b) Determine the production priority of the two products in view of the labour constraint. Prepare an optimal production plan and calculate the total contribution margin of each product and the profit of FML as a whole for next quarter to maximise company profit. (16 marks) (c) In view of the shortage in direct labour hours to meet all the sales demands, explain to the management of FML THREE ways to overcome the labour shortage. (6 marks)",
