      "answer": "Module 2 (June 2022 Session) Page 7 of 7 Answer 4(b) The advantages include: - While financial metrics focus on an accounting period, non-financial measures can be used to track performance over a much longer period of time and without necessarily comparing how that metric performed in relation to competitors, thus providing a window into the progress of accomplishing long-term company strategies. - Non-financial measures may allow companies to track intangible assets such as intellectual capital or customer loyalty. Companies have grown to value performance measurement indicators that track innovation, capabilities of management, employee relations, brand quality, etc. - Non-financial measures may be better indicators of future performance than financial measures. For example, investment in research is more likely to provide a better indication of how companies will perform in the future than sales and profit in the last quarter. - Non-financial measures may provide measures that are not tied to the many factors that can distort financial measures, such as changes in economic circumstances, which may have little or nothing to do with company performance. (Any three advantages. Other reasonable answers are also accepted.) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
      "answerSource": "",
      "hasAnswer": true
