      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 2 (June 2023 Session) Page 2 of 4 Question 2 (18 marks – approximately 32 minutes) Gwenda Company Limited (\"GCL\") receives a special order for 20,000 units of one of its former products, Ruby, at HK$70 each from an overseas company. The order requires 12,000 kg of material A. There are 2,000 kg of material A in inventory which are not required for normal production. These materials were purchased at a cost of HK$21,000. If these materials are not used in this order, they could be sold for HK$10 per kg. The current replacement cost of material A is HK$12 per kg. The order also requires 21,000 kg of material B. There are 1,800 kg of material B in inventory which were purchased at a cost of HK$32,400. Material B is used regularly by GCL in other production. Currently, the price for material B has increased by HK$2 per kg. The order requires 1,500 hours of skilled labour. There is a limited supply of skilled labour, and all the available skilled labour is fully engaged in the production of another product, Mazarine. Mazarine is sold at HK$500 per unit and its production costs are as follows: HK$ per unit Direct material C 120 Skilled labour (2 hours) 160 Variable production overheads 40 Fixed production overheads 60 380 Variable production overheads of HK$11 will be incurred per unit of Ruby. Additional fixed production overheads of HK$100,000 will be incurred if the special order is taken and the fixed production overheads will be absorbed at HK$8 per direct labour hour. An additional selling and distribution overhead of HK$60,000 will also be incurred for the order. An income tax of 2% on the sales value of the order will be payable to the tax authority of the overseas customer. Required: (a) Calculate the relevant costs of direct materials, direct labour, variable production overheads, fixed production overheads, selling and distribution overhead, income tax and opportunity cost, if any, for the special order. Justify whether the special order should be taken, based on financial consideration only. (12 marks) (b) Define fixed costs and justify whether fixed costs are relevant in short-term decision-making. (6 marks)",
