      "ocrUsed": false,
      "answer": "Module 2 (June 2023 Session) Page 4 of 4 Answer 3(b) Ideal standards represent optimal levels of performance under perfect operating conditions. They allow for no machine breakdowns or other work interruptions, and they call for a level of effort that can be attained only by the most skilled and efficient employees working at peak effort continuously. Currently attainable standards are those standards that are reasonable but challenging. They allow for normal machine downtime and employee rest periods. They can be attained through reasonable, but highly efficient, efforts of the average worker. Currently attainable standards are usually used in setting standards costs as they can signal abnormal conditions and can result in realistic planning and forecasting figures. Answer 4(a) Beauty Division Spa Division Return on investment HK$550,000 / HK$5,000,000 x 100% = 11% HK$1,560,000 / HK$12,000,000 x 100% = 13% Required return (Investment × 12%) HK$5,000,000 x 12% = HK$600,000 HK$12,000,000 x 12% = HK$1,440,000 Residual income (\"RI\") HK$550,000 – HK$600,000 = (HK$50,000) HK$1,560,000 – HK$1,440,000 = HK$120,000 Answer 4(b) Customer perspective - Customer retention - Percentage of customers who would recommend the service to a friend Internal process perspective - Consumable waste reduction - Booking accuracy Learning and growth perspective - Number of cross-trained employees - Percentage of employees leaving in less than one year (other relevant measures are also accepted) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *\nIdeal standards represent optimal levels of performance under perfect operating conditions.\nThey allow for no machine breakdowns or other work interruptions, and they call for a level\nof effort that can be attained only by the most skilled and efficient employees working at peak\neffort continuously.\nCurrently attainable standards are those standards that are reasonable but challenging.\nThey allow for normal machine downtime and employee rest periods.\nThey can be attained through reasonable, but highly efficient, efforts of the average worker.\nCurrently attainable standards are usually used in setting standards costs as they can signal\nabnormal conditions and can result in realistic planning and forecasting figures.\nBeauty Division Spa Division\nReturn on investment HK$550,000 / HK$5,000,000 HK$1,560,000 / HK$12,000,000\nx 100% = 11% x 100% = 13%\nRequired return HK$5,000,000 x 12% HK$12,000,000 x 12%\n(Investment x 12%) = HK$600,000 = HK$1,440,000\nResidual income (\"RI\") HK$550,000 — HK$600,000 HK$1,560,000 — HK$1,440,000\n= (HK$50,000) = HK$120,000\nCustomer perspective\n- Customer retention\n- Percentage of customers who would recommend the service to a friend\nInternal process perspective\n- Consumable waste reduction\n- Booking accuracy\nLearning and growth perspective\n- Number of cross-trained employees\n- Percentage of employees leaving in less than one year\n(other relevant measures are also accepted)\n* * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *\nModule 2 (June 2023 Session) Page 4 of 4\nCPA hid pibiic Accountants\n-_ SERNGLR",
