      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 2 (June 2023 Session) Page 3 of 4 Question 3 (22 marks – approximately 40 minutes) Jeanette Technology Limited (\"JTL\") is a leading manufacturer for micro automatic guided vehicles. JTL uses a standard costing system, and the standard cost information for its single product for the year is as follows: HK$ Direct materials (10 kg at HK$15 per kg) 150 Direct labour (2 hours at HK$60 per hour) 120 Variable production overheads (2.5 machine hours at HK$20 per hour) 50 Fixed production overheads 80 Standard production cost per unit 400 Planned and actual production for the year was 30,000 units. There was no opening inventory of direct materials and there was a 40,000 kg closing inventory of direct materials. JTL calculates the price variance of direct materials at the time of purchase. The following variances for the year are provided: Direct materials price variance HK$320,000 (Adverse) Direct materials quantity variance HK$300,000 (Favourable) Direct labour rate variance HK$122,000 (Favourable) Direct labour efficiency variance HK$60,000 (Adverse) Variable production overheads spending variance Nil Variable production overheads efficiency variance HK$100,000 (Favourable) Fixed production overheads spending variance HK$500,000 (Adverse) Required: (a) Calculate the following: (i) Direct materials used in kg; (ii) Direct materials purchased in kg; (iii) Direct materials purchased in dollars; (iv) Actual direct labour cost; (v) Actual direct labour hours used; (vi) Actual direct labour rate per hour; (vii) Actual variable production overheads; (viii) Actual machine hours used; and (ix) Actual fixed production overheads. (14 marks) (b) Describe ideal standards and currently attainable standards. Explain which types of standards are used in setting standard costs for most companies. (8 marks)",
      "full": "Module 2 (June 2023 Session) Page 3 of 4 Question 3 (22 marks – approximately 40 minutes) Jeanette Technology Limited (\"JTL\") is a leading manufacturer for micro automatic guided vehicles. JTL uses a standard costing system, and the standard cost information for its single product for the year is as follows: HK$ Direct materials (10 kg at HK$15 per kg) 150 Direct labour (2 hours at HK$60 per hour) 120 Variable production overheads (2.5 machine hours at HK$20 per hour) 50 Fixed production overheads 80 Standard production cost per unit 400 Planned and actual production for the year was 30,000 units. There was no opening inventory of direct materials and there was a 40,000 kg closing inventory of direct materials. JTL calculates the price variance of direct materials at the time of purchase. The following variances for the year are provided: Direct materials price variance HK$320,000 (Adverse) Direct materials quantity variance HK$300,000 (Favourable) Direct labour rate variance HK$122,000 (Favourable) Direct labour efficiency variance HK$60,000 (Adverse) Variable production overheads spending variance Nil Variable production overheads efficiency variance HK$100,000 (Favourable) Fixed production overheads spending variance HK$500,000 (Adverse) Required: (a) Calculate the following: (i) Direct materials used in kg; (ii) Direct materials purchased in kg; (iii) Direct materials purchased in dollars; (iv) Actual direct labour cost; (v) Actual direct labour hours used; (vi) Actual direct labour rate per hour; (vii) Actual variable production overheads; (viii) Actual machine hours used; and (ix) Actual fixed production overheads. (14 marks) (b) Describe ideal standards and currently attainable standards. Explain which types of standards are used in setting standard costs for most companies. (8 marks)",
