      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 2 (June 2023 Session) Page 4 of 4 Question 4 (15 marks – approximately 27 minutes) Veronica Beauty Group (\"VBG\") is a leading beauty and wellness services provider in Hong Kong and mainland China that targets high-end customers. VBG has two business segments: Beauty Division and Spa Division. The financial results for last year of the two divisions are as follows: Beauty Division Spa Division HK$ HK$ Operating assets 5,000,000 12,000,000 Operating profit 550,000 1,560,000 Required: (a) Calculate the return on investment in percentage and the residual income for each division. The required rate of return of VBG is 12%. (6 marks) (b) VBG is considering using a Balanced Scorecard to evaluate its performance. The management accountant has determined that VBG will use the net profit and the residual income as two measures under the financial perspective of the Balanced Scorecard. List the other THREE perspectives in the Balanced Scorecard and identify TWO measures for VBG for each of the THREE perspectives. (9 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
