      "sourceMatch": "Module 13 (December 2024 Session) Page 4 of 11 Question 1 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) (a) Identify Jeng's external and internal factors which increase its risk of fraud. ",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Dec%2024%20Question.pdf#question-q-p004-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 13 (December 2024 Session) Page 4 of 11 Question 1 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) (a) Identify Jeng's external and internal factors which increase its risk of fraud. Explain your answers. (6 marks) (b) The audit team has determined that revenue is impacted by fraud risks. Based on your assessment in Question 1(a) above, identify which related assertions of revenue are impacted. Explain how these assertions are impacted. (6 marks) Question 2 (14 marks – approximately 24 minutes) Jeng has implemented a fully automated application which records each sale and customer payment transaction from both its online platform and kiosks. All retail prices are set by the system and all discounts are automatically calculated upon successful log in by members. Each sale item is assigned a unique bar code, and the price is linked to the data centre. Purchased goods and consignment goods are coded with different prefixes. Each self-checkout machine at kiosks is equipped with CCTV. No cashier counter is required to process any check-out for its customers at the kiosks. The audit team has evaluated this application and concluded that the respective general controls are effective. As application controls are fully automated, which is particular to this application, they have a direct impact on the processing of individual transactions. The audit team is going to identify and test the effectiveness of the application controls. Required: Based on the case background and the additional information as set out above, (a) Identify the application controls established in Jeng's revenue and receipt cycle for its online and kiosks sales, covering both the sales of Jeng's own goods and the consignment sales. (5 marks) (b) Design your audit procedures to test the application controls implemented in Jeng's revenue and receipt cycle. (5 marks) (c) Advise the audit team on which criteria can be used to determine which kiosks from the total of more than 50 kiosks, should be used for testing the application controls. Explain your answers. (4 marks)",
      "full": "Module 13 (December 2024 Session) Page 4 of 11 Question 1 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) (a) Identify Jeng's external and internal factors which increase its risk of fraud. Explain your answers. (6 marks) (b) The audit team has determined that revenue is impacted by fraud risks. Based on your assessment in Question 1(a) above, identify which related assertions of revenue are impacted. Explain how these assertions are impacted. (6 marks) Question 2 (14 marks – approximately 24 minutes) Jeng has implemented a fully automated application which records each sale and customer payment transaction from both its online platform and kiosks. All retail prices are set by the system and all discounts are automatically calculated upon successful log in by members. Each sale item is assigned a unique bar code, and the price is linked to the data centre. Purchased goods and consignment goods are coded with different prefixes. Each self-checkout machine at kiosks is equipped with CCTV. No cashier counter is required to process any check-out for its customers at the kiosks. The audit team has evaluated this application and concluded that the respective general controls are effective. As application controls are fully automated, which is particular to this application, they have a direct impact on the processing of individual transactions. The audit team is going to identify and test the effectiveness of the application controls. Required: Based on the case background and the additional information as set out above, (a) Identify the application controls established in Jeng's revenue and receipt cycle for its online and kiosks sales, covering both the sales of Jeng's own goods and the consignment sales. (5 marks) (b) Design your audit procedures to test the application controls implemented in Jeng's revenue and receipt cycle. (5 marks) (c) Advise the audit team on which criteria can be used to determine which kiosks from the total of more than 50 kiosks, should be used for testing the application controls. Explain your answers. (4 marks)",
