      "sourceMatch": "Module 13 (December 2024 Session) Page 9 of 11 Question 6 (7 marks – approximately 12 minutes) You are an auditor conducting an audit on the financial statements of Farma Corporati",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Dec%2024%20Question.pdf#question-q-p009-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 13 (December 2024 Session) Page 9 of 11 Question 6 (7 marks – approximately 12 minutes) You are an auditor conducting an audit on the financial statements of Farma Corporation (\"Farma\"), for the year ended 31 December 2023. Farma's primary business involves owning and operating an \"Amusement Park\", which boasts a variety of attractions. Required: During the audit, you have identified issues that may impact the true and fair view of Farma's financial statements. Advise and explain the appropriate auditor's opinion for each of the scenarios below. The audit materiality level applied for this year's audit is HK$5 million. (a) Farma owns property, plant and equipment (\"PPE\") which were accounted as the material component of its statement of financial position. In recent years, Farma has faced challenges due to intense competition and the impact of the pandemic, which significantly affected its business performance. Currently, there is a positive trend of gradual recovery as the post-pandemic situation continues to improve. An impairment loss on these assets was recorded during the pandemic years. As of 31 December 2023, the balance of PPE was HK$75 million, which included a reversal of impairment amounting to HK$25 million. However, Farma was unable to explain and provide evidence to support whether certain assumptions used for the impairment assessment for the PPE are appropriate. (4 marks) (b) At the beginning of the financial year, Farma purchased a large quantity of bond securities which are accounted for as financial assets at fair value through profit or loss. The directors recorded them at cost at HK$30 million, under the assumption that the fair value should be approximately equal to the cost, given the recency of the transaction. However, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority has sharply increased the Base Interest Rate for the year. The estimated fair value of the bond securities as at 31 December 2023 is approximately HK$15 million. (3 marks)",
      "full": "Module 13 (December 2024 Session) Page 9 of 11 Question 6 (7 marks – approximately 12 minutes) You are an auditor conducting an audit on the financial statements of Farma Corporation (\"Farma\"), for the year ended 31 December 2023. Farma's primary business involves owning and operating an \"Amusement Park\", which boasts a variety of attractions. Required: During the audit, you have identified issues that may impact the true and fair view of Farma's financial statements. Advise and explain the appropriate auditor's opinion for each of the scenarios below. The audit materiality level applied for this year's audit is HK$5 million. (a) Farma owns property, plant and equipment (\"PPE\") which were accounted as the material component of its statement of financial position. In recent years, Farma has faced challenges due to intense competition and the impact of the pandemic, which significantly affected its business performance. Currently, there is a positive trend of gradual recovery as the post-pandemic situation continues to improve. An impairment loss on these assets was recorded during the pandemic years. As of 31 December 2023, the balance of PPE was HK$75 million, which included a reversal of impairment amounting to HK$25 million. However, Farma was unable to explain and provide evidence to support whether certain assumptions used for the impairment assessment for the PPE are appropriate. (4 marks) (b) At the beginning of the financial year, Farma purchased a large quantity of bond securities which are accounted for as financial assets at fair value through profit or loss. The directors recorded them at cost at HK$30 million, under the assumption that the fair value should be approximately equal to the cost, given the recency of the transaction. However, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority has sharply increased the Base Interest Rate for the year. The estimated fair value of the bond securities as at 31 December 2023 is approximately HK$15 million. (3 marks)",
