      "year": 0,
      "session": "Dec",
      "resourceId": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Dec%2025%20Question.pdf",
      "resourceName": "M13 Dec 25 Question.pdf",
      "resourcePath": "F:/hkicpa LP+Past paper/11-14LP+Past paper/m13past paper/M13/M13 Dec 25 Question.pdf",
      "previewAvailable": true,
      "groupKey": "11-14|M13|0|Dec",
      "resourceKind": "q",
      "kind": "Question",
      "sourceMatch": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 3 of 10 Question 1 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) You are auditing the financial statements of Sub Ace. In view of the closure plan of",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Dec%2025%20Question.pdf#question-q-p003-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 3 of 10 Question 1 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) You are auditing the financial statements of Sub Ace. In view of the closure plan of the Swiss factory of Sub Ace as announced by Kooma on 1 May 2025, management has conducted an impairment assessment. The property, plant and equipment (PPE) mainly comprise of the factory premises and machinery. You understand from management that they have been seeking potential buyers for the purchase of its Swiss factory but no one has approached Ace to indicate any interest yet. Management therefore provided an estimation of its market value by reference to the secondhand market and noted that a shortfall of HK$5 million resulted. However, management considered that it is not material, and therefore no impairment provision has been made. Required: (a) Advise which assertion(s) of its PPE should be designated as a significant risk of material misstatements. Explain your answers. (7 marks) (b) Evaluate the effect of the unrecorded misstatements, from qualitative and quantitative perspectives, relating to the shortfall of the PPE's market value by HK$5 million on the financial statements of Sub Ace. (6 marks) Question 2 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) You are auditing the intangible assets (i.e. patents) of Sub Bee. You noted that the legal titles of the patents have not yet been transferred to Sub Bee by Beetle, the third party. Management advised that this was due to the fact that Beetle had not settled the long overdue levies payable to the respective government, therefore a legal restriction on the transfer of Beetle's patents was imposed. As management was not aware of this restriction prior to the purchases of the patents, Sub Bee had already paid Beetle the consideration in full, which cannot be refunded. In this regard, management has obtained a confirmation signed by Beetle confirming that Sub Bee has the sole rights to use, control and execute these patents, including subsequent disposals. Required: (a) Analyse the above situation and explain why the lack of a proper legal title of these patents may have a material impact on the financial statements of Sub Bee. (3 marks) (b) Determine appropriate audit procedures and advise additional audit evidence to be obtained for auditing the patents. (10 marks)",
      "full": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 3 of 10 Question 1 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) You are auditing the financial statements of Sub Ace. In view of the closure plan of the Swiss factory of Sub Ace as announced by Kooma on 1 May 2025, management has conducted an impairment assessment. The property, plant and equipment (PPE) mainly comprise of the factory premises and machinery. You understand from management that they have been seeking potential buyers for the purchase of its Swiss factory but no one has approached Ace to indicate any interest yet. Management therefore provided an estimation of its market value by reference to the secondhand market and noted that a shortfall of HK$5 million resulted. However, management considered that it is not material, and therefore no impairment provision has been made. Required: (a) Advise which assertion(s) of its PPE should be designated as a significant risk of material misstatements. Explain your answers. (7 marks) (b) Evaluate the effect of the unrecorded misstatements, from qualitative and quantitative perspectives, relating to the shortfall of the PPE's market value by HK$5 million on the financial statements of Sub Ace. (6 marks) Question 2 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) You are auditing the intangible assets (i.e. patents) of Sub Bee. You noted that the legal titles of the patents have not yet been transferred to Sub Bee by Beetle, the third party. Management advised that this was due to the fact that Beetle had not settled the long overdue levies payable to the respective government, therefore a legal restriction on the transfer of Beetle's patents was imposed. As management was not aware of this restriction prior to the purchases of the patents, Sub Bee had already paid Beetle the consideration in full, which cannot be refunded. In this regard, management has obtained a confirmation signed by Beetle confirming that Sub Bee has the sole rights to use, control and execute these patents, including subsequent disposals. Required: (a) Analyse the above situation and explain why the lack of a proper legal title of these patents may have a material impact on the financial statements of Sub Bee. (3 marks) (b) Determine appropriate audit procedures and advise additional audit evidence to be obtained for auditing the patents. (10 marks)",
      "options": [],
