      "resourceKind": "q",
      "kind": "Question",
      "sourceMatch": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 4 of 10 Question 3 (14 marks – approximately 26 minutes) You are an audit manager who is auditing the goodwill and intangibles of Sub Cow. Fo",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Dec%2025%20Question.pdf#question-q-p004-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 4 of 10 Question 3 (14 marks – approximately 26 minutes) You are an audit manager who is auditing the goodwill and intangibles of Sub Cow. For the impairment test of the goodwill and intangibles of Sub Cow, management adopted an income approach to determine the recoverable amount of Sub Cow's business. They provided you a cash flow forecast with the following key management assumptions of this cash flow forecast, as follows: (a) Revenue will be subject to an annual growth rate of 5%. (b) Production costs will remain stable. (c) General and administrative expenses will remain stable. (d) Gross margin will increase by 2%, 4%, and 8% for the first three years, then will remain stable thereafter. (e) Accounts receivable and payable will remain stable. (f) No significant capital commitments are foreseen. (g) The terminal growth rate is 5% and the discount rate is 10%. (h) No external financing is needed. (i) Some of the patents will be sold to the market which approximates the current carrying amounts. Based on the cash flow forecast, the projected cash flows as compared with the carrying amounts are stated as follows: HK$'million Recoverable amounts 43 Carrying amount of Goodwill and Intangibles (HK$26 million + HK$15 million) 41 Headroom 2 Required: Prepare a memo to your Audit Partner evaluating the management assumptions as set above and propose a list of questions with your rationale or additional audit evidence that you should enquire or request from the management. Explain your answers in the memo. Note: A maximum of 2 marks for analytical skills and 2 marks for communication skills will be awarded. (14 marks)",
      "full": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 4 of 10 Question 3 (14 marks – approximately 26 minutes) You are an audit manager who is auditing the goodwill and intangibles of Sub Cow. For the impairment test of the goodwill and intangibles of Sub Cow, management adopted an income approach to determine the recoverable amount of Sub Cow's business. They provided you a cash flow forecast with the following key management assumptions of this cash flow forecast, as follows: (a) Revenue will be subject to an annual growth rate of 5%. (b) Production costs will remain stable. (c) General and administrative expenses will remain stable. (d) Gross margin will increase by 2%, 4%, and 8% for the first three years, then will remain stable thereafter. (e) Accounts receivable and payable will remain stable. (f) No significant capital commitments are foreseen. (g) The terminal growth rate is 5% and the discount rate is 10%. (h) No external financing is needed. (i) Some of the patents will be sold to the market which approximates the current carrying amounts. Based on the cash flow forecast, the projected cash flows as compared with the carrying amounts are stated as follows: HK$'million Recoverable amounts 43 Carrying amount of Goodwill and Intangibles (HK$26 million + HK$15 million) 41 Headroom 2 Required: Prepare a memo to your Audit Partner evaluating the management assumptions as set above and propose a list of questions with your rationale or additional audit evidence that you should enquire or request from the management. Explain your answers in the memo. Note: A maximum of 2 marks for analytical skills and 2 marks for communication skills will be awarded. (14 marks)",
