      "sourceMatch": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 7 of 10 SECTION B – ESSAY / SHORT QUESTIONS ( TOTAL: 50 marks) Answer ALL of the following questions. Marks will be awarded for logical argum",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Dec%2025%20Question.pdf#question-q-p007-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 7 of 10 SECTION B – ESSAY / SHORT QUESTIONS ( TOTAL: 50 marks) Answer ALL of the following questions. Marks will be awarded for logical argumentation/ calculations and appropriate presentation of the answers. Question 5 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) As the audit engagement manager for Guyi Holdings Limited (\"Guyi\"), a listed company in Hong Kong, you are currently performing the audit planning for the upcoming 2024 audit year. You have noted that there is an overdue payment for the 2023 audit fee from Guyi, which accounts for 3% of the total audit fee. During the preliminary audit planning call with Guyi, you reminded them about the overdue payment. In response, Guyi stated that they plan to settle the remaining audit fee, together with the 2024 audit fee for administrative convenience, after the completion of the 2024 audit. You believe there is no significant risk of default as the outstanding amount is not substantial, and Kenny Lee, the audit engagement partner, and several audit team members, have maintained a strong relationship with Guyi since their involvement in the first-year audit as engagement partner in 2017. After the call, you reported these issues and findings to Kenny Lee. He emphasised the importance of maintaining a professional and positive relationship with Guyi, especially since the firm has lost several significant audit clients over the past two years. Currently, Guyi's audit fee represents over 18% of the firm's total fees for the year (2023: 16%). Required: Evaluate if there is any independence threat in the cases and propose safeguards to mitigate these threats (Limit to THREE safeguards for each threat identified). (10 marks)",
      "full": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 7 of 10 SECTION B – ESSAY / SHORT QUESTIONS ( TOTAL: 50 marks) Answer ALL of the following questions. Marks will be awarded for logical argumentation/ calculations and appropriate presentation of the answers. Question 5 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) As the audit engagement manager for Guyi Holdings Limited (\"Guyi\"), a listed company in Hong Kong, you are currently performing the audit planning for the upcoming 2024 audit year. You have noted that there is an overdue payment for the 2023 audit fee from Guyi, which accounts for 3% of the total audit fee. During the preliminary audit planning call with Guyi, you reminded them about the overdue payment. In response, Guyi stated that they plan to settle the remaining audit fee, together with the 2024 audit fee for administrative convenience, after the completion of the 2024 audit. You believe there is no significant risk of default as the outstanding amount is not substantial, and Kenny Lee, the audit engagement partner, and several audit team members, have maintained a strong relationship with Guyi since their involvement in the first-year audit as engagement partner in 2017. After the call, you reported these issues and findings to Kenny Lee. He emphasised the importance of maintaining a professional and positive relationship with Guyi, especially since the firm has lost several significant audit clients over the past two years. Currently, Guyi's audit fee represents over 18% of the firm's total fees for the year (2023: 16%). Required: Evaluate if there is any independence threat in the cases and propose safeguards to mitigate these threats (Limit to THREE safeguards for each threat identified). (10 marks)",
