      "resourceKind": "q",
      "kind": "Question",
      "sourceMatch": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 9 of 10 Question 7 (11 marks – approximately 20 minutes) You are an audit manager and conducting an audit of the financial statements of H-Te",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Dec%2025%20Question.pdf#question-q-p009-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 9 of 10 Question 7 (11 marks – approximately 20 minutes) You are an audit manager and conducting an audit of the financial statements of H-Tech Limited (\"H-Tech\") for the year ended 31 December 2024. H-Tech is a publicly listed software company specializing in developing mobile applications for the food and beverage industry. One of H-Tech's most well-known applications is \"Let Eat.\" On 30 November 2024, H-Tech was sued by C-Tech Limited (\"C-Tech\"), a competitor in the same industry, alleging that H-Tech unlawfully obtained proprietary information and used it to develop Let Eat. C-Tech claims that Let Eat closely resembles its flagship product, \"Eat Anywhere.\" As a result, C-Tech is seeking HK$100 million in compensation and a ban on Let Eat for alleged intellectual property infringement. As of the financial statement period-end date, the lawsuit remains ongoing. H-Tech has not engaged an external lawyer to assist with the case, instead relying on their in-house legal counsel, who specializes in general commercial law. The in-house legal counsel has estimated that H-Tech is likely to win the case. As a result, no provisions have been made in the financial statements. Required: (a) Propose audit procedures to address the above litigation. (8 marks) (b) Despite your request to the Chief Financial Officer of H-Tech for more details about the case and for the company to consider engaging an external lawyer to provide an opinion, the in-house counsel refused to provide further information to you, citing the highly sensitive nature of the case and declining to disclose additional details. As an audit manager, propose further actions to address the above situation, both internally and externally. (3 marks)",
      "full": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 9 of 10 Question 7 (11 marks – approximately 20 minutes) You are an audit manager and conducting an audit of the financial statements of H-Tech Limited (\"H-Tech\") for the year ended 31 December 2024. H-Tech is a publicly listed software company specializing in developing mobile applications for the food and beverage industry. One of H-Tech's most well-known applications is \"Let Eat.\" On 30 November 2024, H-Tech was sued by C-Tech Limited (\"C-Tech\"), a competitor in the same industry, alleging that H-Tech unlawfully obtained proprietary information and used it to develop Let Eat. C-Tech claims that Let Eat closely resembles its flagship product, \"Eat Anywhere.\" As a result, C-Tech is seeking HK$100 million in compensation and a ban on Let Eat for alleged intellectual property infringement. As of the financial statement period-end date, the lawsuit remains ongoing. H-Tech has not engaged an external lawyer to assist with the case, instead relying on their in-house legal counsel, who specializes in general commercial law. The in-house legal counsel has estimated that H-Tech is likely to win the case. As a result, no provisions have been made in the financial statements. Required: (a) Propose audit procedures to address the above litigation. (8 marks) (b) Despite your request to the Chief Financial Officer of H-Tech for more details about the case and for the company to consider engaging an external lawyer to provide an opinion, the in-house counsel refused to provide further information to you, citing the highly sensitive nature of the case and declining to disclose additional details. As an audit manager, propose further actions to address the above situation, both internally and externally. (3 marks)",
