      "sourceMatch": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 10 of 10 Question 8 (17 marks – approximately 31 minutes) You are an auditor conducting an audit of the financial statements of Woo Wah Limit",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Dec%2025%20Question.pdf#question-q-p010-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 13 (December 2025 Session) Page 10 of 10 Question 8 (17 marks – approximately 31 minutes) You are an auditor conducting an audit of the financial statements of Woo Wah Limited (\"WW Ltd\") for the year ended 31 December 2024. WW Ltd is an artificial intelligence (\"AI\") company that recently launched its advanced AI solution, \"WuWa Talk\". This solution specialises in natural language processing, machine learning, and predictive analytics. It utilises self-developed AI models to store and process large volumes of sensitive training data, ensuring that each subscriber's information remains confidential and accessible only to them. WuWa Talk offers subscription plans for its users, ranging from daily, monthly, to yearly plans. The back-end financial reporting system (\"FR System\") automatically extracts data from WuWa Talk to calculate monthly revenue amounts. Due to high staff turnover, the IT Committee at WW Ltd is currently prioritising the design of a backup and contingency plan for WuWa Talk; however, most of the plan has not yet been fully implemented. However, the removal of former employees' access to the WuWa Talk and FR System has been assigned a lower priority. Since the launch of WuWa Talk, WW Ltd's client base has rapidly expanded and now serves over 200 companies worldwide. To manage the unexpected surge in demand, WW Ltd has rented servers from Farma Limited (\"Farma\"), an IT solution provider founded just one year ago. These rented servers are housed at Farma's office premises. In February 2024, two instances of data leakage were identified by Farma and reported to WW Ltd's IT Committee in December 2024. Required: (a) Propose relevant audit procedures to test the operating effectiveness of the IT general controls of WuWa Talk. (6 marks) (b) Identify the potential control weaknesses on the IT general controls and propose remediation plans to improve the IT general controls over the WuWa Talk and FR System. (11 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
