      "sourceMatch": "Module 13 (June 2025 Session) Page 7 of 9 (5 marks) Question 7 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) Star Medical Clinic is exploring implementing a new operational system to impro",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Question%20Jun%202025.pdf#question-q-p007-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 13 (June 2025 Session) Page 7 of 9 (5 marks) Question 7 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) Star Medical Clinic is exploring implementing a new operational system to improve its internal controls. Management expects this new system to assign an account for each patient who registers with the clinic, track and record a completed process comprising the doctor's diagnosis and medication prescription, calculation of fees charged and recording of the distribution of prescribed medication for each patient. Required : (a) Describe the expected general controls in this new system which can: (i) prevent and identify unauthorised access; (ii) prevent unauthorised alternation of programme and data; and (iii) ensure continuity of the system operation. Note: A maximum of 2 marks are awarded for each of (i), (ii) and (iii) above. (6 marks) (b) Describe the expected application controls in this new system to ensure: (i) the completeness, accuracy, and authorisation over input and process in the system; and (ii) appropriate alternation of master files and data in the system. Note: A maximum of 3 marks are awarded for each of (i) and (ii) above. (6 marks)",
      "full": "Module 13 (June 2025 Session) Page 7 of 9 (5 marks) Question 7 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) Star Medical Clinic is exploring implementing a new operational system to improve its internal controls. Management expects this new system to assign an account for each patient who registers with the clinic, track and record a completed process comprising the doctor's diagnosis and medication prescription, calculation of fees charged and recording of the distribution of prescribed medication for each patient. Required : (a) Describe the expected general controls in this new system which can: (i) prevent and identify unauthorised access; (ii) prevent unauthorised alternation of programme and data; and (iii) ensure continuity of the system operation. Note: A maximum of 2 marks are awarded for each of (i), (ii) and (iii) above. (6 marks) (b) Describe the expected application controls in this new system to ensure: (i) the completeness, accuracy, and authorisation over input and process in the system; and (ii) appropriate alternation of master files and data in the system. Note: A maximum of 3 marks are awarded for each of (i) and (ii) above. (6 marks)",
