      "sourceMatch": "Module 13 (June 2025 Session) Page 9 of 9 Question 9 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) The board of directors of Friendly Bank (the \"bank\"), comprised three executive directors",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/m13past%20paper/M13/M13%20Question%20Jun%202025.pdf#question-q-p009-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 13 (June 2025 Session) Page 9 of 9 Question 9 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) The board of directors of Friendly Bank (the \"bank\"), comprised three executive directors and two independent directors, has recently been sanctioned with a fine of HK$500,000 due to the bank's breach of directors' duties and responsibility without safeguarding the bank's assets. It was uncovered that the bank has granted significant amounts of loans to three overseas entities during the years between 2022 to 2024 without going through the normal due diligence procedures by branch level. The approval of these loans was approved by one of the directors. Significant amounts of loan defaults were subsequently found which are associated with individual borrowers who were the related parties of one of the directors. The incidents were reported by the bank's internal audit department head to that director, but no course of action has been taken. The regulator has asked the board of directors to review the bank's existing corporate governance structure including its internal control process on granting the loans and take necessary remediation. Required: Propose actions that the board of directors of the bank should consider in response to the regulator's request. (10 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
      "full": "Module 13 (June 2025 Session) Page 9 of 9 Question 9 (10 marks – approximately 18 minutes) The board of directors of Friendly Bank (the \"bank\"), comprised three executive directors and two independent directors, has recently been sanctioned with a fine of HK$500,000 due to the bank's breach of directors' duties and responsibility without safeguarding the bank's assets. It was uncovered that the bank has granted significant amounts of loans to three overseas entities during the years between 2022 to 2024 without going through the normal due diligence procedures by branch level. The approval of these loans was approved by one of the directors. Significant amounts of loan defaults were subsequently found which are associated with individual borrowers who were the related parties of one of the directors. The incidents were reported by the bank's internal audit department head to that director, but no course of action has been taken. The regulator has asked the board of directors to review the bank's existing corporate governance structure including its internal control process on granting the loans and take necessary remediation. Required: Propose actions that the board of directors of the bank should consider in response to the regulator's request. (10 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
