      "prompt": "Module C (December 2019 Session) Page 2 of 9 The management and administrative staff receive fixed monthly salaries, which are also paid on the 25 th of each month via bank transfer. The account clerk records the fixed monthly salaries for management and administrative staff every month. The management and administrative staff are entitled to discretionary bonus and retirement benefits. The account clerk will estimate the year end amounts of the discretionary bonus and retirement benefits before Fortune closes the books. Discretionary bonus is determined by the management, depending on the profitability of Fortune in that year, and is paid in February every year. Although it is on discretionary basis, Fortune never stops paying this bonus to its employees since it was established. Fortune has offered a retirement scheme for its management and administrative staff where Fortune is obliged to contribute a fixed percentage of the employee ’ s month ly salary as the retirement benefits. Below is the information of Fortune ’ s direct labour wages for the year ended 31 December 2019 obtained from its relevant records: Number of workers Working days per worker Total wages HK$ ’ 000 Monthly wages per worker (HK$) A B C C/A January 50 34 1,540 30,800 February 59 34 625 10,593 March 62 26 1,235 19,919 April 81 24 1,240 15,309 May 86 24 1,255 14,593 June 88 24 1,200 13,636 July 88 22 3,375 38,352 August 77 24 1,335 17,338 September 85 23 1,390 16,353 October 88 24 1,485 16,875 November 78 26 1,520 19,487 December 62 41 1,835 29,597 18,035 Monthly average 75 27 1,503 20,238 You are the auditor of Fortune and have been engaged to perform the audit of its financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2019.",
