      "prompt": "Module C (December 2019 Session) Page 6 of 9 SECTION B – ESSAY / SHORT QUESTIONS (Total 50 marks) Answer ALL of the following questions. Marks will be awarded for logical argumentation and appropriate presentation of the answers. Question 5 (9 marks – approximately 16 minutes) Company X is a private company incorporated in Hong Kong. Michael Lee is the Chief Financial Controller of Company X and a good friend of Charles Chan. Chan & Co is a certified public accountant firm registered in Hong Kong. Charles Chan, one of the partners of Chan & Co, provides audit services. Recently, Michael reached out to Charles and requested Chan & Co for proposal of the following services: (1) Advising Company X on possible corporate restructuring and providing related audit service for potential Initial Public Offering. (2) Assisting Company X to prepare the annual tax return. (3) Representing Company X in a court case on a tax dispute with the Inland Revenue Department of Hong Kong. Required: Advise whether Chan & Co should participate in the service proposals. Explain any ethical and professional issues and the possible safeguards for Chan & Co when considering the proposal of the above services. (9 marks)",
