      "prompt": "Module C (December 2019 Session) Page 7 of 9 Question 6 (11 marks – approximately 20 minutes) Sweet Limited is principally engaged in the trading and distribution of chocolates and candies. You are the auditor of Sweet Limited. (a) During the course of an audit, you inquired the management of Sweet Limited whether they were aware of any significant events that happened after the year end. The management stated that they were not aware of any. Required: Propose audit procedures to corroborate the management’s statement. (5 marks) (b) After performing the audit procedures on corroborating the management’s statement, you noted certain findings. Required: Propose follow up audit procedures in respect of these findings. (i) Certain popular chocolates were sold below cost after the year end but there was no inventory provision made against these chocolate inventories as the management considered that they were still popular items. (4 marks) (ii) Sweet Limited acquired 51% of equity interest of Choco Limited, a major competitor of similar size of Sweet Limited, after the year end. (2 marks)",
