      "prompt": "Module C (December 2019 Session) Page 8 of 9 Question 7 (17 marks – approximately 31 minutes) Company A is a garment manufacturing and trading company. It has a factory in mainland China and a trading office in Hong Kong. Fast-end, a packaged software with customisation, is the IT system currently used by Company A. Company A keeps all general ledger, sales and receivable ledger, inventory and payable ledger in Fast-end. Company A recruited no internal IT personnel in the past. Company A engaged an external service provider to maintain Fast-end. All data were stored in the server of the external service provider. In the current year, Company A has no longer engaged the external service provider but recruited one of the programmers from the external service provider to help maintain Fast-end and the data in-house and starts to build a small IT team with three people. The programmer from the external service provider has years of experience in developing and maintaining Fast-end for Company A and other companies using Fast-end. There were no significant IT control deficiencies reported by the predecessor auditor. Wong & Co is the new auditor of Company A. Required: (a) Consider the procedures that Wong & Co should perform before determining the audit approach on the IT system audit. (5 marks) (b) Assume that you are the audit manager of Wong & Co; during the initial meeting with Company A’s IT team, you noted the following: - IT control environment of Company A was less structured. - The IT controls in place were less formal and loosely documented. - There were minor programme changes made by the programmer to Fast-end during the year. - All IT staff had full access to Fast-end. (i) Evaluate the risk of material misstatements in terms of IT risk based on the fact and circumstance provided in the case. (6 marks) (ii) In response to the risk of material misstatements identified in Question 7(b)(i), propose relevant audit procedures in addressing the risks identified. (6 marks)",
      "full": "Module C (December 2019 Session) Page 8 of 9 Question 7 (17 marks – approximately 31 minutes) Company A is a garment manufacturing and trading company. It has a factory in mainland China and a trading office in Hong Kong. Fast-end, a packaged software with customisation, is the IT system currently used by Company A. Company A keeps all general ledger, sales and receivable ledger, inventory and payable ledger in Fast-end. Company A recruited no internal IT personnel in the past. Company A engaged an external service provider to maintain Fast-end. All data were stored in the server of the external service provider. In the current year, Company A has no longer engaged the external service provider but recruited one of the programmers from the external service provider to help maintain Fast-end and the data in-house and starts to build a small IT team with three people. The programmer from the external service provider has years of experience in developing and maintaining Fast-end for Company A and other companies using Fast-end. There were no significant IT control deficiencies reported by the predecessor auditor. Wong & Co is the new auditor of Company A. Required: (a) Consider the procedures that Wong & Co should perform before determining the audit approach on the IT system audit. (5 marks) (b) Assume that you are the audit manager of Wong & Co; during the initial meeting with Company A’s IT team, you noted the following: - IT control environment of Company A was less structured. - The IT controls in place were less formal and loosely documented. - There were minor programme changes made by the programmer to Fast-end during the year. - All IT staff had full access to Fast-end. (i) Evaluate the risk of material misstatements in terms of IT risk based on the fact and circumstance provided in the case. (6 marks) (ii) In response to the risk of material misstatements identified in Question 7(b)(i), propose relevant audit procedures in addressing the risks identified. (6 marks)",
      "options": [],
      "sourcePage": 8,
      "sourceMode": "text",
      "ocrUsed": false,
      "answer": "Module C (December 2019 Session) Page 13 of 13  validate if the management of Universe Limited discuss and challenge the key assumptions and estimates provided by Sky Limited for the cash flow projection;  meet with the management of Sky Limited to discuss and understand the key assumptions and estimates used in the cash flow forecast;  inquired with Sky Limited management if there are new rounds of financial funding obtained by Sky Limited after June 2018 that may be a good reference for estimating the latest fair value of Sky Limited;  perform an analytical review or audit procedures for the 2018 actual results of Sky Limited if feasible;  compare the 2018 actual results of Sky Limited to its budget to assess the reliability of management’s estimates;  compare the key assumptions and estimates used by the management with public available industry and market data. For example, compare the net profit margin percentage and discount rate applied with companies that engage in similar industry and of similar size;  as Universe Limited only holds 15% equity interest in Sky Limited, consider whether the management has applied appropriate minority shareholding discount in the valuation;  test the mathematical accuracy of the discounted cash flow calculation; and  test if the management of Universe Limited has applied the appropriate percentage of shareholding in calculating their share of the fair value of Sky Limited. * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
