      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module C (December 2019 Session) Page 9 of 9 Question 8 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) Sky Limited is a start-up technology company providing IT solutions on artificial intelligence, computer vision and 3D visualisation. Sky Limited was founded in 2017 and has been loss making. 15% equity interest in Sky Limited was recently acquired by Universe Limited in June 2018. In Universe Limited’s financial statements, Sky Limited is accounted for as financial assets at fair value through other comprehensive income in accordance with HKFRS 9 Financial Instruments . For the purpose of preparing the financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2018, Universe Limited has engaged an external valuer to assist on the valuation of Sky Limited as at 31 December 2018 using discounted cash flow calculation with key assumptions and estimates provided by the management of Sky Limited. Extract of the discounted cash flow calculation: Actual Actual Forecast Forecast Forecast 2017 2018 2019 2020 2021 HK$’000 HK$’000 HK$’000 HK$’000 HK$’000 Revenue 2,000 5,000 15,000 30,000 60,000 Net (loss) profit (4,000) (3,500) 4,000 15,000 30,000 Net cash (outflow) inflow from operating activities (3,600) (3,000) 4,400 15,600 30,800 Terminal growth rate 3% Discount rate 10% Business value of Sky Limited as at 31 December 2018: HK$484 million Required: Assume you are the auditor of Universe Limited for the year ended 31 December 2018. (a) Based on the information provided, in order to understand the key assumptions and estimates used in the discounted cash flow calculation, recommend the questions that you would ask the management of Sky Limited. (6 marks) (b) Apart from understanding the key assumptions and estimates used in the discounted cash flow calculation, propose the audit procedures that you would perform to assess the fair value of 15% equity interest of Sky Limited held by Universe Limited. (7 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
      "full": "Module C (December 2019 Session) Page 9 of 9 Question 8 (13 marks – approximately 23 minutes) Sky Limited is a start-up technology company providing IT solutions on artificial intelligence, computer vision and 3D visualisation. Sky Limited was founded in 2017 and has been loss making. 15% equity interest in Sky Limited was recently acquired by Universe Limited in June 2018. In Universe Limited’s financial statements, Sky Limited is accounted for as financial assets at fair value through other comprehensive income in accordance with HKFRS 9 Financial Instruments . For the purpose of preparing the financial statements for the year ended 31 December 2018, Universe Limited has engaged an external valuer to assist on the valuation of Sky Limited as at 31 December 2018 using discounted cash flow calculation with key assumptions and estimates provided by the management of Sky Limited. Extract of the discounted cash flow calculation: Actual Actual Forecast Forecast Forecast 2017 2018 2019 2020 2021 HK$’000 HK$’000 HK$’000 HK$’000 HK$’000 Revenue 2,000 5,000 15,000 30,000 60,000 Net (loss) profit (4,000) (3,500) 4,000 15,000 30,000 Net cash (outflow) inflow from operating activities (3,600) (3,000) 4,400 15,600 30,800 Terminal growth rate 3% Discount rate 10% Business value of Sky Limited as at 31 December 2018: HK$484 million Required: Assume you are the auditor of Universe Limited for the year ended 31 December 2018. (a) Based on the information provided, in order to understand the key assumptions and estimates used in the discounted cash flow calculation, recommend the questions that you would ask the management of Sky Limited. (6 marks) (b) Apart from understanding the key assumptions and estimates used in the discounted cash flow calculation, propose the audit procedures that you would perform to assess the fair value of 15% equity interest of Sky Limited held by Universe Limited. (7 marks) * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
