      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/M14%20past%20paper/M14%20Question%20Jun%202025.pdf#question-q-p001-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 1 of 10 SECTION A – CASE QUESTIONS (Total: 50 marks) Answer ALL of the following questions. Marks will be awarded for logical argumentation and appropriate presentation of the answers. CASE Kim residing in Country S is the sole shareholder of Kim Pte Limited, a pure investment holding company incorporated in Country S that does not have a double taxation agreement with Hong Kong. Kim Pte Limited has a wholly owned subsidiary K Limited, a Hong Kong incorporated company carrying on a business in Hong Kong in the following manner: 1. K Limited rented an office in Hong Kong with three full time staff members serving as office manager, business manager, and IT technician. The office manager and IT technician are based in Hong Kong, whilst the business manager is a business traveller (see below). 2. K Limited's business involves licensing copyrights of novels written by non-resident authors from all over the world, digitalising the novels in the form of e-books, and storing the e-books on a website for download by readers who are individuals residing all over the world for a fixed fee (for each download) after membership registration. 3. Readers are only allowed to download copy onto their computers and read the e-books on their own computers registered with K Limited. They are not allowed to modify the e-books or distribute the e-books to any other readers. 4. The website is hosted on a dedicated server at the disposal of and owned by K Limited only, and the server is located in a third party data centre in Country S. K Limited does not have any other form of physical presence in Country S. 5. All tasks from membership registration, ordering of e-books, payment, downloading of e-books, and customer service, are fully automated by the website hosted on the above Country S server without any human intervention needed. The IT technician nonetheless will digitalize the content in e-book format, update the e-book database and perform routine system updates of the server remotely from Hong Kong. 6. The business manager travels overseas from time to time, attending book exhibition events with the purpose of meeting new authors. After the initial encounter, the authors are invited to come to K Limited's Hong Kong office for a formal interview and for the negotiation, conclusion, and execution of a licensing contract. 7. The office manager handles daily office work including administration, accounting and bookkeeping, bank account operation, etc.",
      "full": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 1 of 10 SECTION A – CASE QUESTIONS (Total: 50 marks) Answer ALL of the following questions. Marks will be awarded for logical argumentation and appropriate presentation of the answers. CASE Kim residing in Country S is the sole shareholder of Kim Pte Limited, a pure investment holding company incorporated in Country S that does not have a double taxation agreement with Hong Kong. Kim Pte Limited has a wholly owned subsidiary K Limited, a Hong Kong incorporated company carrying on a business in Hong Kong in the following manner: 1. K Limited rented an office in Hong Kong with three full time staff members serving as office manager, business manager, and IT technician. The office manager and IT technician are based in Hong Kong, whilst the business manager is a business traveller (see below). 2. K Limited's business involves licensing copyrights of novels written by non-resident authors from all over the world, digitalising the novels in the form of e-books, and storing the e-books on a website for download by readers who are individuals residing all over the world for a fixed fee (for each download) after membership registration. 3. Readers are only allowed to download copy onto their computers and read the e-books on their own computers registered with K Limited. They are not allowed to modify the e-books or distribute the e-books to any other readers. 4. The website is hosted on a dedicated server at the disposal of and owned by K Limited only, and the server is located in a third party data centre in Country S. K Limited does not have any other form of physical presence in Country S. 5. All tasks from membership registration, ordering of e-books, payment, downloading of e-books, and customer service, are fully automated by the website hosted on the above Country S server without any human intervention needed. The IT technician nonetheless will digitalize the content in e-book format, update the e-book database and perform routine system updates of the server remotely from Hong Kong. 6. The business manager travels overseas from time to time, attending book exhibition events with the purpose of meeting new authors. After the initial encounter, the authors are invited to come to K Limited's Hong Kong office for a formal interview and for the negotiation, conclusion, and execution of a licensing contract. 7. The office manager handles daily office work including administration, accounting and bookkeeping, bank account operation, etc.",
      "options": [],
