      "answer": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 17 of 17 - As the PASPs, each forms part of a larger transaction or series of transactions in respect of which the amount or value, or the aggregate amount or value, of the consideration does not exceed HK$9,000,000, they should be chargeable with stamp duty under Scale 2(g) of Head 1(1A) in the First Schedule of the SDO as follows: • The Flat: HK$180,000 (HK$6,000,000 x 3%) • The CPS: HK$24,000 (HK$800,000 x 3%) - Provided that the PASPs are duly stamped, each of the two assignments will be chargeable with stamp duty of HK$100 [s.29D(2)(a) of the SDO]. * * * END OF EXAMINATION PAPER * * *",
