      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 2 of 10 Below is K Limited's income statement for the financial year ended 31 December 2024: HK$ HK$ Download fee income from readers (Note 1) 10,000,000 Sub-license fee income from Tao Limited (Note 2) 2,000,000 12,000,000 Expense: Salaries 2,200,000 Office rent and administrative expenses 800,000 License fees to authors (Note 3) 3,860,000 Withholding tax (Note 4) 140,000 (7,000,000) Profit before tax 5,000,000 Note 1: This is the gross income from readers without any deduction of fees, expenses and tax. Note 2: Tao Limited is a company tax resident in mainland China, which sub-licenses the copyrights of novels from K Limited to publish paperback editions of the novels for sale to readers in mainland China. This is the gross amount billed to Tao Limited without any deduction of fees, expenses and tax. The sub-licensing contracts were negotiated, concluded and executed by the business manager in Hong Kong. Note 3: License fees are paid annually to unrelated authors based on a pre-agreed fixed amount for the annual right to use the copyright on their writings. Note 4: This is the 7% withholding tax deducted by Tao Limited in mainland China from the gross sub-license fee income billed by K Limited. For cost control reason, the following business restructuring measures have been implemented from 1 January 2025: (a) The employment contracts for the business manager, office manager and IT technician, together with the office lease, have been terminated. Bookkeeping and accounting functions have been outsourced to the parent company Kim Pte Limited, in Country S, for an annual fee of HK$8,000,000. Kim Pte Limited has no employee in Country S and hence the work has been further outsourced to a local accounting firm in Country S. K Limited no longer maintains any physical presence in Hong Kong except for a server (see below). (b) No further updates and routine maintenance are conducted for the e-book database, operating system, and website. Nonetheless, the website operates as normal, earning the same income as that for the financial year 2024. (c) K Limited's bank account is operated by Kim remotely from Country S. (d) The website has been relocated and hosted on a dedicated server owned by and at the disposal of K Limited, located in a data centre in Hong Kong.",
      "full": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 2 of 10 Below is K Limited's income statement for the financial year ended 31 December 2024: HK$ HK$ Download fee income from readers (Note 1) 10,000,000 Sub-license fee income from Tao Limited (Note 2) 2,000,000 12,000,000 Expense: Salaries 2,200,000 Office rent and administrative expenses 800,000 License fees to authors (Note 3) 3,860,000 Withholding tax (Note 4) 140,000 (7,000,000) Profit before tax 5,000,000 Note 1: This is the gross income from readers without any deduction of fees, expenses and tax. Note 2: Tao Limited is a company tax resident in mainland China, which sub-licenses the copyrights of novels from K Limited to publish paperback editions of the novels for sale to readers in mainland China. This is the gross amount billed to Tao Limited without any deduction of fees, expenses and tax. The sub-licensing contracts were negotiated, concluded and executed by the business manager in Hong Kong. Note 3: License fees are paid annually to unrelated authors based on a pre-agreed fixed amount for the annual right to use the copyright on their writings. Note 4: This is the 7% withholding tax deducted by Tao Limited in mainland China from the gross sub-license fee income billed by K Limited. For cost control reason, the following business restructuring measures have been implemented from 1 January 2025: (a) The employment contracts for the business manager, office manager and IT technician, together with the office lease, have been terminated. Bookkeeping and accounting functions have been outsourced to the parent company Kim Pte Limited, in Country S, for an annual fee of HK$8,000,000. Kim Pte Limited has no employee in Country S and hence the work has been further outsourced to a local accounting firm in Country S. K Limited no longer maintains any physical presence in Hong Kong except for a server (see below). (b) No further updates and routine maintenance are conducted for the e-book database, operating system, and website. Nonetheless, the website operates as normal, earning the same income as that for the financial year 2024. (c) K Limited's bank account is operated by Kim remotely from Country S. (d) The website has been relocated and hosted on a dedicated server owned by and at the disposal of K Limited, located in a data centre in Hong Kong.",
