      "sourceMatch": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 4 of 10 Question 1 (14 marks – approximately 25 minutes) Before 1 January 2025 (i.e. for the original full scope Hong Kong business model): (a) D",
      "id": "file:///F:/hkicpa%20LP+Past%20paper/11-14LP+Past%20paper/M14%20past%20paper/M14%20Question%20Jun%202025.pdf#question-q-p004-1",
      "number": "1",
      "prompt": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 4 of 10 Question 1 (14 marks – approximately 25 minutes) Before 1 January 2025 (i.e. for the original full scope Hong Kong business model): (a) Determine the nature (i.e. business income vs royalty) of the download fee income and sub-license fee income under Hong Kong profits tax in light of the Inland Revenue Department (\"IRD\")'s assessing practice. (6 marks) (b) Based on your answer in (a) above, evaluate the source of the download fee income and sub-license fee income under Hong Kong profits tax in light of the IRD's assessing practice and case law. (8 marks) Question 2 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) Regarding the withholding tax of HK$140,000 paid in mainland China: (a) Advise whether it is deductible in computing the assessable profits of K Limited under s.16(1) of the Inland Revenue Ordinance (\"IRO\"). Note: Further discussion on the application of subsections (a) to (h) of s.16(1) of the IRO is not required. (4 marks) (b) Explain how K Limited can obtain tax relief in Hong Kong for such withholding tax paid under the provisions of the double taxation agreement between Hong Kong and mainland China. Compute the profits tax liability of K Limited at the normal tax rate of 16.5% for the year of assessment 2024/25, taking into account the tax relief you discussed above. Note: You should (1) assume there is no capital expenditure included in K Limited's operating expenses; (2) assume expense attributable to the earning of the sub-license fee income is HK$1,200,000; and (3) ignore the Two-tiered Profits Tax Rates Regime and tax reduction. (8 marks)",
      "full": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 4 of 10 Question 1 (14 marks – approximately 25 minutes) Before 1 January 2025 (i.e. for the original full scope Hong Kong business model): (a) Determine the nature (i.e. business income vs royalty) of the download fee income and sub-license fee income under Hong Kong profits tax in light of the Inland Revenue Department (\"IRD\")'s assessing practice. (6 marks) (b) Based on your answer in (a) above, evaluate the source of the download fee income and sub-license fee income under Hong Kong profits tax in light of the IRD's assessing practice and case law. (8 marks) Question 2 (12 marks – approximately 22 minutes) Regarding the withholding tax of HK$140,000 paid in mainland China: (a) Advise whether it is deductible in computing the assessable profits of K Limited under s.16(1) of the Inland Revenue Ordinance (\"IRO\"). Note: Further discussion on the application of subsections (a) to (h) of s.16(1) of the IRO is not required. (4 marks) (b) Explain how K Limited can obtain tax relief in Hong Kong for such withholding tax paid under the provisions of the double taxation agreement between Hong Kong and mainland China. Compute the profits tax liability of K Limited at the normal tax rate of 16.5% for the year of assessment 2024/25, taking into account the tax relief you discussed above. Note: You should (1) assume there is no capital expenditure included in K Limited's operating expenses; (2) assume expense attributable to the earning of the sub-license fee income is HK$1,200,000; and (3) ignore the Two-tiered Profits Tax Rates Regime and tax reduction. (8 marks)",
