      "prompt": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 7 of 10 SECTION B – ESSAY / SHORT QUESTIONS (Total: 50 marks) Answer ALL of the following questions. Marks will be awarded for logical argumentation and appropriate presentation of the answers. Question 5 (12 marks – approximately 21 minutes) YEAH Limited (\"the Company\") was incorporated in the Cayman Islands and was registered in Hong Kong as a non-Hong Kong company under the Companies Ordinance. The particulars of information of the Company are as follows: (1) Its shares are listed on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange (\"HKEX\") to raise funds from the capital market in Hong Kong, and to invest in the business units in Singapore and in mainland China. (2) Its principal activities are investment holdings with investments in Singapore and in mainland China. (3) It maintains its Branch Share Registrar and Transfer Office in Hong Kong. (4) In its annual report for the year ended 31 March 2023, the Company stated that its principal place of business was Address D in Hong Kong and its head office was in mainland China. (5) Its financial statements were audited by a certified public accountant in Hong Kong. It maintains bank accounts in Hong Kong and in mainland China. (6) The Hong Kong Office is rented and used to maintain books and records of the Company and for coordination with HKEX. (7) It employs a compliance manager, company secretary and secretary to work at Address D. (8) The board of directors are made up of Hong Kong residents and non-Hong Kong residents. The Company appointed Mr Chen as an independent non-executive director who received a director fee of HK$3,000,000 for the year of assessment 2022/23. Mr Chen is a mainland Chinese resident and stayed in Hong Kong for 10 days during the year of assessment 2022/23. Mr Chen attended the director's meetings of the Company held in Hong Kong via tele-conferencing. He claimed that he did not render any services for the Company when he stayed in Hong Kong. Required: Assume that you are Kitty Wong, the tax advisor of Mr Chen. With reference to the relevant IRO provisions and legal principles, write an email to Mr Chen to give advice on the following: • the source of income from office; • whether the director fee received by Mr Chen from the Company is chargeable to salaries tax in Hong Kong; and • relevance of s.8(1A)(b) of the IRO in the present case. Note: A maximum of 2 marks for communication skills and 2 marks for analytical skills will be awarded. (12 marks)",
