      "prompt": "Module 14 (June 2025 Session) Page 8 of 10 Question 6 (23 marks – approximately 42 minutes) Mr Poon and Mrs Poon (\"the Couple\") are husband and wife. The following information is provided by them for the year ended 31 March 2024: (1) The Couple, as joint tenants, purchased a residential property ( \" Flat S \" ) and borrowed a mortgage loan from a bank to finance the acquisition. Thereafter, they resided at Flat S until 30 September 2023. They paid mortgage loan interest of HK$80,000 for the period from 1 April 2023 till 30 September 2023. (2) On 1 October 2023, the Couple sold Flat S and entered into a tenancy to lease a residential property with a monthly rent of HK$16,000 for the period from 1 October 2023 to 30 September 2024. The tenancy agreement was properly stamped. The Couple agreed that they should claim the rent paid in equal shares. (3) Mr Poon is employed as a finance manager in Hong Kong. His salaries income for the year ended 31 March 2024 was HK$910,000. During the year, he donated HK$30,000 to approved charitable donations. He also contributed HK$18,000 to a recognised mandatory provident fund (\"MPF\") scheme and made voluntary contributions of HK$24,000 to a tax deductible MPF scheme. (4) Mr Poon had been constantly living with his father for many years. Unfortunately, his father passed away on 15 February 2024 at the age of 80. Mr Poon's mother was 75 years old and lived in an elderly residential care home. Mr Poon incurred residential care expenses of HK$120,000 for the year ended 31 March 2024. (5) Mrs Poon is a primary school teacher. Her salaries income and contributions to a recognised MPF scheme were HK$720,000 and HK$18,000 respectively for the year ended 31 March 2024. (6) Mrs Poon and Mrs Poon's sister purchased a Voluntary Health Insurance Scheme policy for their father. They paid as the policy holders and a qualifying premium of HK$10,000 was paid by Mrs Poon and Mrs Poon's sister in the proportion of 7 to 3. Required: (a) Analyse, with reference to the relevant provisions of the IRO and legal principles, whether the following items could be deducted under salaries tax for Mr Poon and Mrs Poon for the year of assessment 2023/24, and, if so, the amount of deduction allowable: (i) Mrs Poon has been diagnosed with breast cancer and incurred medical expenses of HK$200,000 for the treatments for the year ended 31 March 2024. She would like to claim deduction of the medical expenses as she claims that she could not perform her duties at her primary school without receiving the treatments. (3 marks) (ii) Mr Poon and Mr Poon's mother purchased a qualifying deferred annuity policy as joint policy holders. Mr Poon was the sole annuitant, and a qualifying annuity premium of HK$60,000 was paid by him on 1 July 2023. (2 marks)",
